{"id": "14486", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14486", "title": "Flind", "text": "Flinds are much more powerful variants of the common &lt;a href=\"Gnoll\"&gt;Gnoll&lt;/a&gt; found in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\". They're distinguishable from their brethren by way of their dark blue-ish skin-tone. They also noteably wield &lt;a href=\"Two-handed%20Sword\"&gt;Two-handed Sword&lt;/a&gt;s, as opposed to the common &lt;a href=\"Halberd\"&gt;Halberd&lt;/a&gt;, which they are particularly skilled with.\nThey cast weapon entanglement with each successful hit, which gives +4 penalty to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;, unless a successful save vs wands is performed that stacks. It's easy to miss due to lack of feedback on a successful throw in &lt;a href=\"Dialogue%20Window\"&gt;Dialogue Window&lt;/a&gt;.\nPolymorph Self Version.\nFlind is one of the creatures &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;s can &lt;a href=\"Polymorph%20Self\"&gt;polymorph&lt;/a&gt; into. This version comes equipped with a &lt;a href=\"Halberd%20%2B3\"&gt;magic halberd that hits as +3&lt;/a&gt; and adds +1 fire damage instead of the common Greatsword and a &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;Haste&lt;/a&gt; spell effect for the duration of the spell."}
