{"id": "39309", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39309", "title": "Foehammer's Blessing", "text": "Foehammer's Blessing is a side quest in that requires traveling between the &lt;a href=\"Coalition%20Camp\"&gt;Coalition Camp&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Exterior\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Exterior&lt;/a&gt;.\nAcquiring.\nThis quest can be acquired from Crusade Recruits Kjarvan and Qing, in the northern rubble area of the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Exterior\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Exterior&lt;/a&gt;. They explain they have found the remnants of an icon of &lt;a href=\"Tempus\"&gt;Tempus&lt;/a&gt; and seek to restore it in order to seek his divine blessing.\nCompleting.\nThe player must retrieve &lt;a href=\"First%20Stone%20Fragment\"&gt;First&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Second%20Stone%20Fragment\"&gt;Second Stone Fragment&lt;/a&gt;s of the Icon of Tempus. The first can be found in a pile of rubble to the west of the recruits. The second must be acquired from &lt;a href=\"Deneld\"&gt;Deneld&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce the missing pieces are retrieved, they must be blessed by a priest of Tempus. Talk to &lt;a href=\"Mizhena\"&gt;Mizhena&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Coalition%20Camp\"&gt;Coalition Camp&lt;/a&gt; to achieve this and combine the fragments into the &lt;a href=\"Sanctified%20Shards\"&gt;Sanctified Shards&lt;/a&gt;.\nOnce the Sanctified Shards are blessed, return to the recruits and inform them of what has been achieved. Place the Sanctified Shards in the stone icon, and they will pray to Tempus. This causes the icon to speak with the Voice of Tempus, which offers a blessing by combat.\nIf this challenge is accepted, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; must defeat the &lt;a href=\"Sentry%20of%20Tempus\"&gt;Sentry of Tempus&lt;/a&gt;. In addition to the 6,000 EXP granted for completing the quest, they gain an additional 5,000 EXP for defeating the sentry, as well as &lt;a href=\"The%20Bloodied%20Guardian\"&gt;The Bloodied Guardian&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the challenge is refused, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; simply gains 6,000 EXP.\nFailing.\nIf the player expresses doubt in Caelar's righteousness when first talking to the recruits or reveals that they had the restored icon blessed by &lt;a href=\"Mizhena\"&gt;Mizhena&lt;/a&gt;, they will attack &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;. They are worth 420 EXP each and drop minor loot. No other reward is attained if this happens."}
{"id": "38381", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38381", "title": "Fog Cloud", "text": "Fog Cloud is a &lt;a href=\"wizard%20spell\"&gt;wizard spell&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"alteration\"&gt;alteration&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Schools%20of%20magic\"&gt;school&lt;/a&gt; that was &lt;a href=\"Cut%20content\"&gt;cut&lt;/a&gt; from the . Only for it exists, text and entries for the spellname, and a to the also cut &lt;a href=\"Spell%20scrolls\"&gt;spell scroll&lt;/a&gt;.\nStatistics.\nBased on filenames for the &lt;a href=\"spell\"&gt;spell&lt;/a&gt;'s , an entry in a &lt;a href=\"random%20treasure\"&gt;random treasure&lt;/a&gt; and the order of &lt;a href=\"Spell%20scrolls\"&gt;spell scroll&lt;/a&gt; names in the game-text defining file, codice_1, Fog Cloud was planned to be a &lt;a href=\"wizard%20spell\"&gt;wizard spell&lt;/a&gt; of . The colors used for its may confirm &lt;a href=\"alteration\"&gt;alteration&lt;/a&gt; as its intended &lt;a href=\"Schools%20of%20magic\"&gt;school&lt;/a&gt;.\nValues to the right and the following description are taken from the \"&lt;a href=\"Player%27s%20Handbook\"&gt;Player's Handbook&lt;/a&gt;\", an \"&lt;a href=\"Advanced%20Dungeons%20%26amp%3B%20Dragons\"&gt;Advanced Dungeons &amp; Dragons&lt;/a&gt;\" , the ruleset which the is based on.\nAcquisition.\nAs the &lt;a href=\"spell\"&gt;spell&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20scrolls\"&gt;scroll&lt;/a&gt; for it were &lt;a href=\"Cut%20content\"&gt;cut&lt;/a&gt; from the before release, it is not possible in any way to have Fog Cloud scribed into the mage book (see also the &lt;a href=\"%23SR\"&gt;notes&lt;/a&gt;).\nThe scroll was intended to be found as &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%232nd-level%20scrolls\"&gt;random treasure&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 at a chance of 5% among other scrolls, resulting in no find at all in the original \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" and ' if a six is rolled for this . In the ' and \"\", this result is replaced with a scroll for &lt;a href=\"Detect%20Invisibility\"&gt;Detect Invisibility&lt;/a&gt;, and with one for &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Hakeashar\"&gt;Summon Hakeashar&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "25924", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25924", "title": "Fog of War", "text": "The fog of war (or fog-of-war) is a black shading meant to represent the player's knowledge of a map's terrain. It obscures unexplored regions of the area map and must be cleared to interact with the region. &lt;a href=\"Coordinates\"&gt;Coordinates&lt;/a&gt; for these areas cannot be manually selected until the fog has been cleared. Previously explored areas are denoted with a tinted overlay: coordinates may be selected and party members may retreat back to these explored areas.\nFog of war is distinct from line of sight: even if a player has the entire area map \"visible\", they are not able to execute actions beyond the line of sight. Attempting to do so will cause the player to move within proper range to execute the action.\nThe spell &lt;a href=\"Clairvoyance\"&gt;Clairvoyance&lt;/a&gt; will flag the entire map as \"explored\", clearing the fog but leaving the tinted overlay.\nThe spell &lt;a href=\"Farsight\"&gt;Farsight&lt;/a&gt; will flag the targeted region as \"explored\" and \"visible\", with no tinted overlay while the spell is active. The advantage of this is that NPCs are visible and can be targeted for actions while Farsight is active."}
