{"id": "4595", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4595", "title": "Forest of Tethir (Shadows of Amn)", "text": "The Forest of Tethir is a location accessible during the events in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; of the .\nThis area is only reachable after having passed through the &lt;a href=\"Small%20Teeth%20Pass\"&gt;Small Teeth Pass&lt;/a&gt; area. Once that has been done, the Forest of Tethir can be selected as a valid travel destination on the &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;World Map&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nVisiting this area is optional by the party during chapter 6. There will not be a quest reason to be here in the unmodified game until after the party has delivered the &lt;a href=\"Rhynn%20Lanthorn\"&gt;Rhynn Lanthorn&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Elhan\"&gt;Elhan&lt;/a&gt; as part of &lt;a href=\"The%20Elven%20City%20Requires%20My%20Aid\"&gt;The Elven City Requires My Aid&lt;/a&gt; questline.\nHowever, the player can direct the party to this location before that time if desired. There is some freelance adventuring, exploring and a small side quest available in the forest. Visiting the area early won't spoil or harm any later quests, so go ahead and do it if you want to. \nGameplay walkthrough.\nThe Forest.\nThe party will enter the map on the north edge of the area.\nThe Forest is much denser than the &lt;a href=\"North%20Forest%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;North Forest&lt;/a&gt; area. Huge ancient trees grow here, towering well over a hundred feet tall. The canopy of foliage blocks all but limited speckled sunlight on the forest floor. Still ponds of silent water abound. This forest is very old indeed.\nVarious wildlife is present in the forest. Some will be predatory and hostile, as well as many passive birds, moose, deer, rabbit and squirrel animals.\nWhen ready, begin exploring. As the party maneuvers across the spongy and damp forest floor, pressing through bramble and thick ferns - they will come upon gigantic fallen trees with vast trunks. If the party can clamber up some side branches, they can use the trees as a pathway to navigate past the undergrowth and move about the area.\nHostile encounters in the Forest.\nThroughout the area there are several spawn zones that will generate hostile creatures. They may be natural creatures such as a stalking &lt;a href=\"Panther\"&gt;Panther&lt;/a&gt;, a group of armed &lt;a href=\"Goblin%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Goblin&lt;/a&gt; bowmen and foot soldiers, horrible mist creatures of various types, perhaps even a &lt;a href=\"Wolfwere\"&gt;Wolfwere&lt;/a&gt; pack or a &lt;a href=\"Yuan-ti\"&gt;Yuan-ti&lt;/a&gt; war party. Be ever on the lookout for these attackers.\nThe time of day/night influences the probability and type of spawns generated. \nThe Cabin.\nOn the western side of the map (see the Automap marker on the players \"World Map\" tab) is a location marked \"Cabin\". Descending on a huge branch will lead down to a slightly cleared area with a cabin structure. You'll probably spot a lone male elf dressed in leather armor and a hood - when within a specific distance the familiar face of &lt;a href=\"Coran\"&gt;Coran&lt;/a&gt; from Baldur's Gate will address the party, he'll say:\nA back-and-forth dialogue will continue here. In essence, Coran needs help rescuing &lt;a href=\"Safana\"&gt;Safana&lt;/a&gt; from some wolfweres that have captured her. Coran isn't strong enough to do it alone, and requests the assistance of &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;. The player can refuse, or agree. If the party says no, Coran says if you change your mind he'll be heading over to the Wolfwere Camp location to see about attempting a rescue. If the party agrees he'll be pleased and will meet the party at the camp. The player's Journal registers the &lt;a href=\"Coran%20and%20the%20Wolfweres\"&gt;Coran and the Wolfweres&lt;/a&gt; side quest.\nCoran then departs for the Wolfwere Camp. Meet him there when you are ready to do so (there is no time limit).\nThe Cave.\nOn the eastern and slightly south side of the map is an Automap Marker on the player's world map marked as \"Cave\".\nTo investigate this, find the door on a hillside, open it and enter within.\nSee the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Tethir%20Cave\"&gt;Forest of Tethir Cave&lt;/a&gt; for more details. What's inside?\nReturn to the Forest.\nOnce the party has returned the &lt;a href=\"Rhynn%20Lanthorn\"&gt;Rhynn Lanthorn&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Elhan\"&gt;Elhan&lt;/a&gt; - the elven commander transports the party back to the forest. The lanthorn buzzes with power and penetrates the illusionary ward placed by &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt; to reveal the hidden entrance to &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt;.\nElhan enters the gateway and asks the party to follow when they are ready.\nIf the player wishes to finish any tasks in chapter 6, go ahead and do that now, before transitioning through the gate and beginning &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt;. \nTrivia.\nLooks like the developers went with the dwarven spelling on the World Map, as it's titled \"Forest of Tethyr\" - according to the Forgotten Realms Wiki, the correct spelling for the forest is the elvish spelling \"Tethir\", named after an elvish hero.\nMod content.\nMods.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises the AI scripts for most creatures on the map for smarter tactical behavior. The Yuan-ti mage is a potent spell caster. Various mist creatures will have new innate abilities, such as the Mist Horror. The spell casting Wyvern cultist has a large repertoire of magic.\n&lt;a href=\"https%3A//github.com/RoxanneSHS/LensHunt\"&gt;The Broken Lanthorn&lt;/a&gt; mod will require the party to find another missing lens piece for the &lt;a href=\"Rhynn%20Lanthorn\"&gt;Rhynn Lanthorn&lt;/a&gt; in this area."}
{"id": "54999", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54999", "title": "Forest of Tethir Cave", "text": "This Cave is found within the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Tethir%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Forest of Tethir&lt;/a&gt;, which is reachable during the events in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; of the .\nBackground.\nThe location of this area is in the southeast portion of the forest (marked on the player's \"Automap\", titled as \"Cave\").\nGameplay walkthrough.\nA door can be found, somewhat camouflaged to blend in with the hillside it's mounted to.\nEntering through the door leads to a limestone cave. It smells musty from the natural dampness as your eyes become accustom to the low-level illumination that softly emanates from phosphorescent fungi growing on rocky surfaces. Insects such as beetles, cockroaches, centipedes, along with various unknown types of bugs, scatter in front of you - fleeing from your entry. \nA natural pool of fresh water is seen on the western side of the cave, with a constant drip of condensate falling from the cave ceiling. To the north of the cave is observed a break in the north wall, some kind of opening possibly leading to another cave chamber.\nExplore further to the north and eventually you'll discover a group of various armed Kuo-toa creatures. The group is comprised of a &lt;a href=\"Kuo-toan%20Captain\"&gt;Captain&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Kuo-toan%20Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Kuo-toan%20Warrior\"&gt;Warrior&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Kuo-toan%20Priest\"&gt;Priest&lt;/a&gt; and a couple of &lt;a href=\"Kuo-toan%20Whip\"&gt;Whips&lt;/a&gt;. \nExpect a chain of spell casts from the wizard, the whip will be invisible, the group will be manifesting a recurring &lt;a href=\"True%20Seeing\"&gt;True Seeing&lt;/a&gt; effect. The various creatures will likely be firing &lt;a href=\"Kuo-toan%20Bolt\"&gt;Kuo-toan Bolt&lt;/a&gt; missiles and or stabbing with their spears in melee range.\nWhen the men-fish are put down, sort through their dropped loot and take what is desired.\nReturn to the first chamber and ensure the pool of water is searched. It's likely now that a second group of kuo-toa will be awaiting the party in the chamber. This group of kuo-toa include a &lt;a href=\"Kuo-toan%20Lieutenant\"&gt;Lieutenant&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Kuo-toan%20Monitor\"&gt;Monitor&lt;/a&gt;, Wizard, a Whip and two Warriors. Battle the \"gogglers\" and bring peace to this once quiet cave.\nMod content.\nMods.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod overhauls the scripts and creature design of the Kuo-toans in various moderate ways to make them more effective in battle, and smarter in a tactical sense. Spell casters do a better job of preparatory buffing and selecting appropriate targets for spells (that aren't immune or protected)."}
{"id": "36513", "revid": "5653418", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36513", "title": "Forest of Wyrms", "text": "The Forest of Wyrms is an in \"\".\nDescription.\nIt is a forested area around a mountain that hides a &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Ruined Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt;, now converted to worship of &lt;a href=\"Cyric\"&gt;Cyric&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; believes the thief who stole the &lt;a href=\"wardstone\"&gt;wardstone&lt;/a&gt; needed to access the teleportation circle into the fort at &lt;a href=\"Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Boareskyr Bridge&lt;/a&gt; likely has fled here.\nEncounters.\nDirectly east of the entrance lies a &lt;a href=\"Hill%20Giant\"&gt;Hill Giant&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"Dire%20Wolf\"&gt;Dire Wolf&lt;/a&gt; pets. Once slain, the corpse of a nearby slain adventurer will have &lt;a href=\"Stalker%20Gauntlets\"&gt;Stalker Gauntlets&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Composite%20Longbow%20%2B1\"&gt;Composite Longbow +1&lt;/a&gt;, 20 &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Piercing\"&gt;Arrows of Piercing +1&lt;/a&gt;, and 5 &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20of%20Dispelling\"&gt;Arrows of Dispelling&lt;/a&gt;\nTo the south of the entrance, &lt;a href=\"Coogan\"&gt;Coogan&lt;/a&gt; will warn the party that spiders are everywhere and to not go into any caves they find.\nFurther south of that, a pair of &lt;a href=\"Wyvern\"&gt;Wyvern&lt;/a&gt;s attack, as does the &lt;a href=\"Baby%20Wyvern\"&gt;Baby Wyvern&lt;/a&gt; with them. Strangely, they do not give &lt;a href=\"Wyvern%20Head\"&gt;Wyvern Head&lt;/a&gt;s.\nThe path will split south of that, leading to three &lt;a href=\"Displacer%20Beast\"&gt;Displacer Beast&lt;/a&gt;s to the west and a group of &lt;a href=\"Small%20Spider\"&gt;Small Spider&lt;/a&gt;s that will immediately retreat to a &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Lair\"&gt;nearby cave&lt;/a&gt;. Up the mountain from there are several &lt;a href=\"Phase%20Spider\"&gt;Phase Spider&lt;/a&gt;s, then four &lt;a href=\"Bugbear\"&gt;Bugbear&lt;/a&gt;s right outside &lt;a href=\"Wyrm%20Cave\"&gt;another cave&lt;/a&gt;."}
