{"id": "45325", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45325", "title": "Frag Grenade", "text": "The Frag Grenade is a special type of ammunition that explodes upon hitting its target, damaging all creatures within a &lt;a href=\"Skull%20Trap\"&gt;Skull Trap&lt;/a&gt; sized radius, allies included. Like the &lt;a href=\"Case%20of%20Plenty\"&gt;Case of Plenty&lt;/a&gt;, this item must be equipped in a character's ammo slot, can be fired using a (or the &lt;a href=\"Big%20Metal%20Rod\"&gt;Big Metal Rod&lt;/a&gt;), and provides unlimited ammunition.\nGameplay.\nThough not &lt;a href=\"enchanted\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt;, this grenade is a &lt;a href=\"magical%20item\"&gt;magical item&lt;/a&gt; that, for all intents and purposes, will behave like a weapon with a +1 enchantment. The projectile provides a +10 bonus to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and attempts to get through the target's &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt; vs &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;Piercing damage&lt;/a&gt;. If successful, it explodes and deals 1d12 &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; in an &lt;a href=\"Game%20Terminology%23A\"&gt;AoE&lt;/a&gt; that bypasses &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;. Certain effects can be carried along with the AoE to affect multiple targets, unless they are protected by &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt;. This applies to abilities like &lt;a href=\"Called%20Shot\"&gt;Called Shot&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Weapon\"&gt;Poison Weapon&lt;/a&gt;, but also to the grenade launcher's eventual piercing damage bonus or the &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20proficiency\"&gt;proficiency&lt;/a&gt; of the character using it.\nOnce the main target is hit and the projectile is not \"ineffective\", the explosion ignores the weapon immunities of secondary targets, like &lt;a href=\"Protection%20From%20Magical%20Weapons\"&gt;Protection From Magical Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, so it is possible to fire at a vulnerable target and catch a nearby enemy with immunity to +1 weapons in the blast."}
