{"id": "55262", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55262", "title": "Freeing Queen Ellesime", "text": "This is part of the main quest for &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt;. \nAquisition.\nWhen the party first enters the &lt;a href=\"Tree%20of%20Life\"&gt;Tree of Life&lt;/a&gt; area, there is dialogue with a projected image of &lt;a href=\"Ellesime\"&gt;Ellesime&lt;/a&gt;. When the dialogue is finished, the image disappears and the player has this quest registered in their Journal, as follows:\nWalkthrough (very abbreviated).\nFind and destroy the three parasites on the Tree of Life.\nWhen the second parasite is destroyed, Ellesime's projected image makes contact again and urges the party to continue and gives some encouragement. A small Journal update is registered at this juncture:\nAfter the third and final parasite is destroyed, the party is transferred to the central area with Irenicus and Ellesime in her cage.\nJon and the Bhaalspawn, and then Jon and the Queen have dialogue. Ellesime is now freed and disappears from the map.\nA final Journal entry registers for this quest, as follows:\nIreinicus and the party have dialogue (some interjections by key Bioware companions occurs).\nIrenicus turns hostile and battles the party.\nIf the party is successful, Irenicus is killed, the bhaalspawn and party is soon tugged down into &lt;a href=\"The%20Abyss\"&gt;The Abyss&lt;/a&gt; {AKA Hell) to start Chapter 7, Part 2 as it is referred to in the player's game text.\nThe player's Journal then updates and registers the &lt;a href=\"Finding%20Irenicus%20in%20Hell\"&gt;Finding Irenicus in Hell&lt;/a&gt; Questline.\nSee &lt;a href=\"The%20Abyss\"&gt;The Abyss&lt;/a&gt; page for that stage of the saga."}
{"id": "35195", "revid": "26939652", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35195", "title": "Freeing Yoshimo's Soul", "text": "Freeing Yoshimo's Soul is a side-quest in and its Enhanced Edition.\nAcquisition.\nTo acquire this side quest, &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo\"&gt;Yoshimo&lt;/a&gt; must be in the party when it travels to &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt; in Chapter 4 of \"Shadows of Amn\". Towards the climax of the main quest &lt;a href=\"Escaping%20the%20Asylum\"&gt;Escaping the Asylum&lt;/a&gt;, the party will be forced to fight and kill Yoshimo, who will explain about his being under a Geas beforehand and beg &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to take &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo%27s%20Heart\"&gt;his heart&lt;/a&gt; to a &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Ilmater\"&gt;Temple of Ilmater&lt;/a&gt; to have his soul freed should the &lt;a href=\"Bhaalspawn\"&gt;Bhaalspawn&lt;/a&gt; triumph.\nMissing.\nIf Yoshimo is not brought to Brynnlaw, then this quest will be missed; when the party first returns to the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; during Chapter 6, Yoshimo will perish in a scripted event and be unable to be resurrected.\nSolving.\nTo solve this quest, after killing Yoshimo in Chapter 4, take his heart from his loot-pile. Keep the heart in your inventory until you reach Chapter 6 and are able to return to &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; again. Once there, simply go to either of the two temples of Ilmater - &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Ilmater%20%28Slums%20District%29\"&gt;the one in the&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Slums district&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Ilmater%20%28Waukeen%27s%20Promenade%29\"&gt;the one in&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; - and speak to the priest there. \nDiscuss Yoshimo's heart and the priest will take it from your inventory to perform a cleansing rite that will break the Geas, allowing Yoshimo's soul to find peace in the afterlife at last.\nReward.\nYou will gain 200,000 Quest EXP for completing this quest."}
