{"id": "8099", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8099", "title": "Frennedan", "text": "&lt;br&gt;\nFrennedan is a &lt;a href=\"doppelganger\"&gt;doppelganger&lt;/a&gt; found on the second level of &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon%202nd%20Floor\"&gt;Irenicus' Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;. He first disguises himself as an innocent old man, who will beg to be freed. If he is refused to be freed, he will take the form of a young boy, seeing if you will free him then. If you refuse a second time, or attack him in a human form, he will transform into his normal doppelganger form and attack. If you let him out without harm, he will follow you around a little before reverting into his true form and then attacking. Progress of his imprisonment is tracked through a mini quest \"Find the key to release Frennedan\".\nHis entire imprisonment is a ruse. If you engage in hostilities by casting something like &lt;a href=\"Grease\"&gt;Grease&lt;/a&gt; with the door still locked, he will open the door himself. This is one way to defeat him if you (temporarily) lack tanking."}
{"id": "51370", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51370", "title": "Freshwater Troll", "text": "Freshwater Troll is a category of &lt;a href=\"Troll\"&gt;Troll&lt;/a&gt; very similar to the standard version found in the game, with a superior strength and dexterity. It is unremarkable in other ways from the average troll, although its appearance is colored in more green hues.\nWhen they are brought near to death (a minimum of 1 hit point) they fall unconscious to the ground. They can be killed permanently in that state, but only by &lt;a href=\"Acid%20damage\"&gt;acid&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; damage, and if not done quickly, they recover heath and consciousness. There are many spells and items that deal these types of damage, so it should be relatively easy to finish them off."}
