{"id": "44457", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44457", "title": "Dermin Courtierdale", "text": "Dermin Courtierdale is a &lt;a href=\"Bard\"&gt;Bard&lt;/a&gt; and an agent of the &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harpers&lt;/a&gt; in the vicinity of the city of &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; in the nation of &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nDermin will appear three times during &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;Companion&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Summoned%20to%20the%20Harper%20Hold\"&gt;Summoned to the Harper Hold&lt;/a&gt;. Each appearance will be in the Wilderness after the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; has rested; never in a city or town.\n As conversation between Dermin and Jaheira will reveal, Dermin is an old Harper Mentor of Jaheira. However, when he appears the first time, he tells Jaheira that it is, \"not...to rehash our friendship... I have been sent to kill you, or otherwise seek your downfall... you travel with a killer of Harpers... your own have died. What do you intend to do about it?\" This gives the \"killer of Harpers\" a chance to respond.\nThe second time, he returns and warns that Jaheira's death has been arranged unless she goes with him back to &lt;a href=\"Galvarey%20Estate\"&gt;Galvarey Estate&lt;/a&gt;, which she agrees to think about. When the party arrives there, they face an ambush by &lt;a href=\"Mercenary%20%28Galvarey%20Estate%29\"&gt;mercenaries&lt;/a&gt;, presumably hired by Dermin.\nThe third and last time, Jaheira and Dermin have a war of words that eventually concludes in a battle between Dermin's Party, and the &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Protagonist's&lt;/a&gt; Party.\nJaheira, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;, and the rest of the party will face Dermin and his cohorts, a &lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Lennah\"&gt;Lennah&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Dwarf\"&gt;Dwarven&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Fighter\"&gt;Fighter&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Thenry\"&gt;Thenry&lt;/a&gt;, an &lt;a href=\"Elf\"&gt;Elven&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;Conjurer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Jeremon\"&gt;Jeremon&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Fighter\"&gt;Fighter&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Cleric\"&gt;Cleric&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Chrost\"&gt;Chrost&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "8832", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8832", "title": "Dermod Ophal", "text": "Lord Dermod Ophal and his wife, &lt;a href=\"Shareen%20Ophal\"&gt;Lady Shareen Ophal&lt;/a&gt;, are aristocrats who can be found sitting atop a platform in the southern part of &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.\nInteractions.\nIf spoken to, Lord Ophal will initiate a conversation seconds before realizing that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and their party are lacking 'social status,' at which point he will question (while whispering) his wife on whether to keep talking to them or not. The two will then try to guess the party's place of origin. After a short discussion on the party, the Lord will proclaim that the conversation is over as Gorion's Ward is lacking in social status."}
{"id": "50750", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50750", "title": "Derrick", "text": "Derrick is an elven &lt;a href=\"Ranger\"&gt;Ranger&lt;/a&gt; that can be encountered during &lt;a href=\"The%20Hunt%20for%20Valygar%20Corthala\"&gt;The Hunt for Valygar Corthala&lt;/a&gt; questline as part of \" campaign. \nYour responses to the dialogue options offered after the initial challenge will determine if the Ranger turns hostile, or if he just makes a declaratory statement and then leaves the map. \nIf hostilities ensue, he will be joined by two other \"Rangers\" (VALRAN02.CRE and 03.CRE). One is actually a Cleric with a Priest script including spell casting. The other is a Ranger class who is mostly identical to Derrick, except for some very minor equipment differences. \nMod content.\nPeople involved.\nInstallation of &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Unfinished Business (Baldur's Gate II)&lt;/a&gt; mod will restore a few lines of dialogue, as well as the &lt;a href=\"Boots%20of%20the%20West\"&gt;Boots of the West&lt;/a&gt; dropped by one of the Rangers if defeated. If the Rangers leave, the Boots will never be seen in the Saga again.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some minor changes to select creature scripts, and abilities. An SCS tactical Ranger script is supplied for more intelligent attack and defense behavior. Derrick now has 2-pips in Longbow and Long Sword weapon proficiency, and 2 pips in single-weapon fighting style. These adjustments slightly change the Ranger's THAC0, damage, weapon speed and Armor Class in melee. Derrick is scripted to be a missile firing combatant unless cornered in close quarters combat, and then will engage in melee.\nThe Cleric \"Ranger\" will have an assigned \"Smarter Priests\" script, and open with a buff or two if combat begins. The Cleric will cast spells as able and if not disrupted and heal or try to cast disabling type priest spells, of which there is an assortment to go with in the script. The other Ranger will fight the same way as Derrick, with missile fire first and then in melee if you close on him. Random SCS treasure is placed on Derrick and the other two creature's inventory.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod is installed the Priest's spell casts will be the SR versions."}
{"id": "19601", "revid": "174260", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19601", "title": "Derro", "text": "The Derro are a race of &lt;a href=\"dwarves\"&gt;dwarves&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"underdark\"&gt;underdark&lt;/a&gt;. A group of them can be found working as slaves for &lt;a href=\"Sendai\"&gt;Sendai&lt;/a&gt;. They are directed to attack the party by the Drow &lt;a href=\"Slavemaster\"&gt;Slavemaster&lt;/a&gt;. The Derro come in two forms, a ranged &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Berserker\"&gt;Berserker&lt;/a&gt;. They come in never ending waves as long as the party stays in the tunnel."}
