{"id": "35052", "revid": "246875", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35052", "title": "Desharik", "text": "Pirate Lord Desharik, sometimes also referred to as Pirate Lord, is a &lt;a href=\"male\"&gt;male&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 of &lt;a href=\"lawful%20neutral\"&gt;lawful neutral&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt; in the original ', but with a better fitting &lt;a href=\"chaotic%20evil\"&gt;chaotic evil&lt;/a&gt; in the ' \u2013 and the ruler of the pirate-controlled island of &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt; in 1369 DR, which means that he becomes a potential obstacle to &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%204\"&gt;Chapter 4&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nWhen spoken to, &lt;a href=\"Golin\"&gt;Golin&lt;/a&gt; will explain that there are two ways for &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; to get into &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;. The first is to confront &lt;a href=\"Perth%20the%20Adept\"&gt;Perth the Adept&lt;/a&gt;, a local representative of the &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Wizards\"&gt;Cowled Wizards&lt;/a&gt; and obtain the &lt;a href=\"Wardstone%20for%20Asylum\"&gt;Asylum Wardstone&lt;/a&gt; that he possesses. The other way is to speak to Captain Desharik and convince him that you are someone who needs to be interred into the asylum due to madness or another mental affliction.\nDesharik's Estate is located in the extreme northwest of Brynnlaw, and is most prominent structure. To get inside to speak with Desharik, the player must get the &lt;a href=\"Pirate%20Door%20Guard\"&gt;Pirate Door Guard&lt;/a&gt; to allow entry. There are three ways to do this: \nConvincing Desharik to send you to the asylum is more difficult than one may think. He's not eager to send anyone there, and he's nervous about upsetting the Cowled Wizards, and possibly a bit paranoid. You have three options to convince him that the party belongs there (there is a fourth option in the Enhanced Edition):\nIf none of your attempts work, Desharik will close off any chance of letting you into the Asylum. Your only method to get within now is to see about contacting the Brynnlaw Cowled Wizard representative and seek a solution to enter the asylum, &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;.\nContainers and loot within the Estate.\nDesharik's bedroom includes four containers, some &lt;a href=\"Find%20Traps%20%28skill%29\"&gt;trapped&lt;/a&gt; and/or &lt;a href=\"Open%20Locks\"&gt;locked&lt;/a&gt;, with several &lt;a href=\"potions%20of%20Extra%20Healing\"&gt;potions of Extra Healing&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gold%20Piece\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20Weapon\"&gt;+2&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20%2B2\"&gt;arrows&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bolt%20%2B2\"&gt;bolts&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Light%20Crossbow%20%2B1\"&gt;Light Crossbow +1&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Longbow%20%2B2\"&gt;Longbow +2&lt;/a&gt;; he personally wears &lt;a href=\"Studded%20Leather%20Armor%20%2B1\"&gt;Studded Leather Armor +1&lt;/a&gt; and dual-wields &lt;a href=\"Scimitar%20%2B1\"&gt;+1 scimitars&lt;/a&gt; in either hand.\nAfter Spellhold/Escaping Brynnlaw.\nIf the party opts to trust &lt;a href=\"Saemon%20Havarian\"&gt;Saemon Havarian&lt;/a&gt; after making &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt; flee from &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;, they will learn that Desharik has confiscated Saemon's ship, so he needs them to steal a signal horn from Desharik's mistress &lt;a href=\"Cayia\"&gt;Cayia&lt;/a&gt; so they can escape Brynnlaw on his ship. If Desharik was not killed before the party entered the asylum, he will appear as the party prepares to set sail and will most likely lead to a final confrontation of Desharik and loyal pirates vs. Saemon (and your party). Kill Desharik (after his dialogue is finished) before defeating his accompanying pirates - doing so allows you to loot his possessions and get some additional XP. See also the &lt;a href=\"Leaving%20the%20island\"&gt;Leaving the island&lt;/a&gt; page for this.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod assigns a new default SCS Fighter AI to Desharik, as well as 5 pips in scimitar weapon proficiency and 3 pips in two weapon fighting style. He'll now get 5 APR with his dual wielding scimitar attacks, 4 with the main hand and 1 with the off-hand."}
{"id": "51228", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51228", "title": "Desharik's Estate", "text": "Desharik's Estate is a prominent home on the Northwest Part of Brynnlaw, high up on a hillside. This home was commandeered by the Pirate Lord Desharik as his own residence and Head Quarters. The former Mayor of Brynnlaw once lived here but is now displaced and could very well been sold into slavery or murdered. Such is the way of Pirates.\nDescription.\nThis multi-level structure is quite ornate and well made, with the trappings of a wealthy owner. For game playing purposes only a portion of the home is available for exploration on the ground floor. The internal layout has four distinct rooms - a reception room with marble pool and statue fountain, a dining and guest parlor, a fully equipped kitchen and larder, and finally, a large bed chamber. \nGameplay.\nAssuming the party has managed to get past the &lt;a href=\"Pirate%20Door%20Guard\"&gt;Pirate Door Guard&lt;/a&gt;, then upon entry is seen &lt;a href=\"Desharik\"&gt;Desharik&lt;/a&gt;, standing in the room with a fountain and pool. There is no way to get inside except by the doorman, including picking the door lock or crashing the door open. See his article page for details, and also the &lt;a href=\"Getting%20inside%20the%20asylum\"&gt;Getting inside the asylum&lt;/a&gt; information for Desharik's role in that.\nContainers.\nThere are several containers that can be examined within the area. These can be rummaged through, and anything found can be removed without any reaction from Desharik, as odd and unexplained as that may seem. It's all basically free loot - roleplay this as your party wishes. "}
{"id": "8873", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8873", "title": "Despana Treasury Key", "text": "The Despana Treasury Key is needed to open the easternmost door to the treasury room in &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Lolth\"&gt;Temple of Lolth&lt;/a&gt; that holds the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Eggs\"&gt;Dragon Eggs&lt;/a&gt;. \nIt is provided by &lt;a href=\"Phaere\"&gt;Phaere&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Female%20Fighters%27%20Society\"&gt;Female Fighters' Society&lt;/a&gt; after completing some tasks for her, as part of &lt;a href=\"The%20Drow%20Summoning%20Ritual\"&gt;The Drow Summoning Ritual&lt;/a&gt; questline."}
{"id": "8208", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8208", "title": "Desreta", "text": "Desreta is a worshiper of entropy who can be found on the second level of the &lt;a href=\"Low%20Lantern\"&gt;Low Lantern&lt;/a&gt;. If &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; agrees to feel the pleasures of entropy, she and &lt;a href=\"Vay-ya\"&gt;Vay-ya&lt;/a&gt; will attack. If you tell them to scram, they'll oblige. She carries the &lt;a href=\"Hands%20of%20Takkok\"&gt;Hands of Takkok&lt;/a&gt;, which are the only strength enhancing equippable item in the original &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;BG1&lt;/a&gt;.\nDialogue.\n\"You come in here for some purpose, no? Tell you the secret. There is no purpose, only entropy. Wondrous, sensuous entropy. My soul sister and I know entropy better than most. Perhaps we teach you some of its pleasures, no?\"\n\"I am Desreta. She is Vay-ya. We are one with void. We know life has no meaning. Let us show you entropic pleasure... Mm. It will delight you with its icy touch.\"\n\"No need to go to bedroom. We can show you... here. Not many agree to go to great void. They afraid. But what there be to be afraid of? Life is hollow. Better to end it soon, than endure its pain.\"\nNotes.\nHer gloves can be pickpocketed with a skill of 80, or looted from her dead corpse. If you do choose a fight, be aware she is a &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt; with mastery in swords and skilled enough to kill your softer characters. Due to the narrow layout of the ship, it's a good idea to send your tank/fighter ahead of the party and initiate dialogue. That way, they can tank her attacks whilst the rest of the party is safely behind. "}
