{"id": "4633", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4633", "title": "Detect Evil (priest)", "text": "Detect Evil is a 1st level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt;. It reveals whether creatures in an area are evil.\nThis spell is identical to its 2nd level &lt;a href=\"Detect%20Evil%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;wizard counterpart&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced \"Detect Evil\" with this new divine spell. See below:\nDetect Alignment\nLevel: 1\nSchool: Divination\nSphere: Divination\nRange: Personal\nDuration: Instant\nCasting Time: 1\nArea of Effect: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nThis spell allows the priest to search out the feelings of all creatures within the current area. When affected by this spell, a target will briefly glow red if he\u2019s evil, green if he\u2019s good, and white if he\u2019s neutral. Magic resistance does not affect this spell."}
{"id": "16159", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16159", "title": "Detect Evil (wizard)", "text": "Detect Evil is used by a wizard to detect any evil creature within range.\nGameplay.\nThis spell is automatically directed over the caster, and when it is finished the spell's effects are applied to every creature in a 60-foot radius.\nCreatures with evil alignment will briefly pulse with a red glow rendered on the creature's sprite.\nAdditionally, text is displayed identifying each creature (by name) who is evil.\n&lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; can block this spell, as can a &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immuity: Divination&lt;/a&gt;.\nA &lt;a href=\"Non-Detection\"&gt;Non-Detection&lt;/a&gt; spell will not shield against Detect Evil.\nAny information gleaned from this spell is up to the player to use as deemed necessary.\nWithin the game's plots and scenarios, the use of this spell has subjective benefit, and is never \"required\" in order to advance the game or solve a quest.\nUsage notes.\nAlthough Detect Evil functions like it does in pen-and-paper D&amp;D, it has unexpected utility in Baldur's Gate. The natural inclination would be to use it to detect potential threats, but there are many false positives using this method. There are numerous, helpful evil characters and many hostile ones of neutral alignment. Making decisions based purely on Detect Evil's results can be dangerous for the player. Additionally, Detect Evil will scan every creature on the map, thus giving the player immediate knowledge of what they could expect to encounter. The caster will also be made aware of magically resistant creatures, whether they are evil-aligned or not. It is best used on a new, unexplored map so the player can anticipate the size and power of random encounters. In Throne of Bhaal, use of this spell will call hostiles to the player's location, as being scanned will be interpreted as an attack.\nAdditional note.\nThis spell is incorrectly listed as a level 1 spell in its description in the original Shadows of Amn and Throne of Bhaal games.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has no direct equivalent to this spell, and this Wizard spell is removed from the game, including scrolls. \nThe mod's first level wizard spell &lt;a href=\"https%3A//gibberlings3.github.io/SpellRevisions/spells/arcane/level-1/detect-alignment\"&gt;Detect Alignment&lt;/a&gt; can fulfill the party's needs to determine evil, good or neutral alignment with this one spell."}
