{"id": "21287", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21287", "title": "Digger", "text": "A total of six Diggers are found in front of the Ruins in the &lt;a href=\"Archaeological%20Site\"&gt;Archaeological Site&lt;/a&gt; area. They have been hired by &lt;a href=\"Charleston%20Nib\"&gt;Charleston Nib&lt;/a&gt; to help him with the excavation of an ancient settlement. When the excavation of the inner chamber is complete, they will follow Charleston and the party (via a short cut scene) into the newly discovered room that Charleston surmises might have been a &lt;a href=\"Shaman\"&gt;Shaman's&lt;/a&gt; abode.\nOnce inside it doesn't take long for all of them to become overtaken by a mental derangement that appears to emanate from the ancient &lt;a href=\"Idol\"&gt;artifact&lt;/a&gt; that lies within a nearby stone sarcophagus. They begin to scream in an ancient tongue and fly into a fit of rage while turning evil and attacking the party. The only thing which prevents the party from taking serious damage is that they are armed only with spears and have a paltry amount hit points for a level 6 character.\nDialogue.\nOutside.\n\"Psst... 'ere, there. I would be leavin' as soon as ye can, mate. Bossman there is nice an' all, but he have no real idea what be going on. I tell you, there is some bad magic in the air.\"\n\"Best pay I ever got for slingin' shovel, but I'm leavin' today. Been having nightmares about this place so bad I can't sleep no more.\"\n\"Astor went missing last night. Charleston thinks it was bandits, but I says he just went mad. Tore off like the all the 9 hells were in 'im.\"\n\"My grammy tells some strange stories 'bout places like this. Used to be people here worshiping the OLD gods. Berserkers, they was. Killed everyone... then themselves.\"\n\"Charleston Nib is quite some fellow. That Gallor though, I'm not so keen on him. A little too precise counting the pay, if ye ask me.\"\nInside.\n\"Hey, boss man, I don't feel so good. How old is the air in this place?\"\n\"Is so... is so cold in here... I feel... strange.\"\n\"I hear... I hear a voice... in my head...\"\n\"I hear the hollow voice, but it is but a mumble! Speak up! Speak up and guide mine hands! RAAAAAAAGH!\"\n\"You... I see what you are! There is power to be had from your death! Your blood will quiet the voice! BLOOD WILL QUIET!\"\n\"KOZAH A PLET 'DAR CASS TOGLAH! KOZAH!\"\n\"Q' AL TE-PAH KOZAH! SHE CAL KOZAH!\""}
{"id": "34934", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34934", "title": "Dili", "text": "Dili is a &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Females\"&gt;girl&lt;/a&gt; with an unnatural affinity for magic whom &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; encounters as a resident at &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt; during the events of \"\". Differently from the other inmates, she does not actually appear during the fight against Irenicus, though she supposedly dies in that encounter.\nBiography.\nDili was born as an arcane prodigy, able to intuitively shape magical energy \u2013 presumably of the Transmutation school \u2013 to the extent that she could freely change her form into whatever she desired. This scared her parents so much that they willingly gave her up to the &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Wizards\"&gt;Cowled Wizards&lt;/a&gt;, who sought to study her powers in hopes of furthering their own understanding of such magic.\nGameplay.\nDili can be conversed with the party regardless of if the party arrived in Spellhold via Pirate Lord &lt;a href=\"Desharik\"&gt;Desharik&lt;/a&gt; or using the &lt;a href=\"Wardstone%20for%20Asylum\"&gt;Wardstone for Asylum&lt;/a&gt;.\nDili has no ability to fight or cast spells. She's only a \"special\" kid, after all.\nAs Dili is equipped with the &lt;a href=\"MINHP1.ITM\"&gt;MINHP1.ITM&lt;/a&gt; she can't be killed in the cell block. Even so, as an innocent, just attacking her can reduce party reputation. She's only a kid, after all. \nDili is removed from the game after the battle with Irenicus, although she doesn't take part in it. \nDialogue interactions.\nWhen the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; first arrives at the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Main%20Floor\"&gt;main floor of Spellhold&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%204\"&gt;chapter 4&lt;/a&gt;, they can talk with Dili. If they arrived by obtaining the Wardstone and coming through the front door, the &lt;a href=\"Coordinator\"&gt;Coordinator&lt;/a&gt; will introduce them to Dili and provide her history. If spoken to, Dili will briefly talk about her abilities at first, while later declaring \"Ooh, this face is boring. Now I'm...\", before polymorphing into one of several random &lt;a href=\"creature\"&gt;creature&lt;/a&gt;s:\nIn addition, she's also able to take the form of a &lt;a href=\"male\"&gt;male&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt; or an &lt;a href=\"ettercap\"&gt;ettercap&lt;/a&gt;, and she tells, that she even \"took face once. His punishment was...\"\nCompanions.\nIf available during the first conversation with Dili, some &lt;a href=\"companions\"&gt;companions&lt;/a&gt; might throw in their own thoughts:"}
