{"id": "27182", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27182", "title": "Director", "text": "The Director is a &lt;a href=\"Beholder\"&gt;Beholder&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThe party will find the Director in the maze when searching for the six pieces of a burial mask to complete the &lt;a href=\"Mask%20of%20King%20Strohm%20III\"&gt;Mask of King Strohm III&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Director is in a chamber on its own. Two doors can be used to enter the chamber, and one is locked.\nThe beholder will not hesitate very long before attacking. It does this by using \"force cast\" spells, meaning near instant deployment and no chance of spell interruption. If a valid targeted enemy is detected it will usually begin with a &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Storm\"&gt;Ice Storm&lt;/a&gt;, and if there are multiple opponents seen by the beholder it looks at the second nearest, and even third nearest target to determine which one it aims the spell at. \nThis creature will selectively launch &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hands\"&gt;Burning Hands&lt;/a&gt; and use one beholder eye ray, the &lt;a href=\"Slow\"&gt;Slow&lt;/a&gt; beam. It can get off another &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Storm\"&gt;Ice Storm&lt;/a&gt; during the battle as well, and it might be applied on top of an existing one. The AI has a safeguard targeting logic to try and avoid damaging itself with the Ice Storm, but it might not work, and it could end up in its own Area of Effect.\nThe beholder is scripted to recognize Mage class opponents and reserves attacking those with &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt;.\nAll of the beholders magic attacks are scripted and timed, and it doesn't run out of spells. They will stop when the creature is disabled or destroyed.\nThe creature has some unique physical damage resistances that most beholders don't possess - and it also has a slight &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; rating.\nMod content.\nIf the player has installed the &lt;a href=\"Ooze%27s%20Lounge\"&gt;Ooze's Lounge&lt;/a&gt; mod, then the Director's corpse will provide an item that will further a side quest introduced by that mod, involving the Beholder merchant and its sidekick immature small beholder.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a several changes to this Director. The beholder has a brighter tint to make it appear different than an ordinary beholder. The creature's immunities are standardized with SCS beholders, so it is immune to all movement and hold type spell effects and is under &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action\"&gt;Free Action&lt;/a&gt;. It is protected from &lt;a href=\"Backstab\"&gt;Backstab&lt;/a&gt;.\nSCS revised the AI script for the Director. The mod has melded the original Director's use of force cast spells with several other uses of Beholder eye ray attacks. Instead of &lt;a href=\"Ice%20Storm\"&gt;Ice Storm&lt;/a&gt; (which can harm itself), it uses an innate spell version of &lt;a href=\"Cone%20of%20Cold\"&gt;Cone of Cold&lt;/a&gt;. Rather than casting &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hands\"&gt;Burning Hands&lt;/a&gt;, the beholder uses the Beholder \"Burning Ray\" eye beam. \nThe creature will be firing an Eye beam called \"Enervation\", which is basically a &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 7 Death Ray, save vs. Death or be killed, magic resistance can block it. \nThere is a beholder &lt;a href=\"Paralyze\"&gt;Paralyze&lt;/a&gt; eye beam used, and force cast &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt; spells.\nAs all SCS beholders have, the creature has permanent Alacrity, allowing multiple eye beams/spells to be launched (2-3 per round) with no cool down period. Have fun adventurers!"}
{"id": "8240", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8240", "title": "Dirk", "text": "Dirk is a member of the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and one of the three partners of &lt;a href=\"Wiven\"&gt;Wiven&lt;/a&gt; who are in the process of robbing a &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23AR1101\"&gt;residence&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; when &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; enter the premises and interrupt them. Only Wiven is visible as Dirk and the other two thieves are lurking in the shadows. All three will step out at Wiven's command and attack the party if you don't choose to give up all of your money to her."}
{"id": "52141", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52141", "title": "Dirla", "text": "Dirla is a criminal who can be found looking for victims outside the &lt;a href=\"Three%20Old%20Kegs%20%28SoD%29\"&gt;Three Old Kegs&lt;/a&gt; in .\nIf any are talked to, a conversation begins which ends with an attack by &lt;a href=\"Dirla\"&gt;Dirla&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lluis\"&gt;Lluis&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Golt\"&gt;Golt&lt;/a&gt; and, depending on the conversation, &lt;a href=\"Asery\"&gt;Asery&lt;/a&gt;."}
