{"id": "5819", "revid": "284065", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5819", "title": "Disintegrate", "text": "A casting of Disintegrate literally turns the enemy to dust.\nGameplay.\nThe caster selects a single target creature to aim this spell towards.\nAfter the spell is finished casting, a projectile travels to the target unerringly and potentially affects the creature.\nContrary to the spell's description of a thin green ray, this spell instead uses a greenish energy orb projectile.\nA creature contacted by the orb must attempt a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spells or suffer a &lt;a href=\"Disintegrate%20effect\"&gt;Disintegrate effect&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the saving throw is failed, the creature is instantly killed and is reduced to a pile of fine dust.\nA disintegrated victim cannot be resurrected, and the spell can destroy carried items that are not flagged as \"critical\" in the game files - although turning off the \"gore\" option will prevent this, as will playing in \"Story Mode\"\nThis spell can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, or appropriate Spell protections that have a capacity to withstand a 6 spell &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt;, such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Alteration&lt;/a&gt; will negate this spell.\nA creature protected by a &lt;a href=\"Death%20Ward\"&gt;Death Ward&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Avoid%20Death\"&gt;Avoid Death&lt;/a&gt;, or the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt; will be immune to this particular disintegration spell.\nPsionic disintegrate.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Captain%20%28githyanki%20WK%29\"&gt;Githyanki Captain&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Githyanki%20Encampment\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Githyanki Encampment&lt;/a&gt;, as well as the Gith and Anti-Paladin from the , have a &lt;a href=\"Psionic%20Disintegrate\"&gt;Psionic Disintegrate&lt;/a&gt; attack. It is the same as the spell, except saving throw is made against Death instead of Spell.\nHive Mother disintegrate.\nA &lt;a href=\"Hive%20Mother\"&gt;Hive Mother&lt;/a&gt; employs a more potent version of an innate disintegration eye ray (using the beholder blast projectile), with a casting time of 1 and the save vs spell incurring a -4 penalty.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects, saving throw and description. See below:\nDisintegrate\nLevel: 6\nSchool: Alteration\nRange: Long\nDuration: Instant\nCasting Time: 6\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: Breath partial\nUpon casting this spell at another creature, a thin green ray shoots unerringly from the caster\u2019s fingertip toward the target. Upon contact, the creature must make a saving throw vs. breath at -2 or suffer 2d6 points of magic damage per caster level (to a maximum of 40d6). A creature that makes a successful save is partially affected, taking only 5d6 points of damage. The ray affects even objects constructed entirely of force, such as a Mordenkainen\u2019s Sword, which is automatically destroyed when struck. This spell has no effect on clothing or equipment carried by the target."}
{"id": "46181", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46181", "title": "Disintegrate effect", "text": "Disintegrate is a status effect that kills whichever creature it is applied to, unless they are explicitly immune to it. If gore is enabled in the game options, the creature's gold and/or non-critical equipment may be disintegrated along with their body. A companion who is killed by disintegration can not be revived on higher difficulties.\nNote: It is not the only status effect that kills a creature instantly -- other contenders are &lt;a href=\"Kill%20target\"&gt;Kill target&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Power%20Word%2C%20Kill%20%28effect%29\"&gt;Power Word Kill&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Slay\"&gt;Slay&lt;/a&gt;. The party should be immune to them in Story mode.\nGameplay.\nAs is true with all status effects, application details vary depending on source -- what is causing the effect. The source may allow a saving throw with or without a penalty, may or may not be able to apply Disintegrate through the &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Mirroring\"&gt;Cloak of Mirroring&lt;/a&gt;, ... Check the source you're interested in for such details. It is likely to help find ways to prevent Disintegrate from being applied to party members, so they don't have to resist it explicitly using one of the means described in this article."}
