{"id": "13596", "revid": "282904", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13596", "title": "Dorn's bloody path", "text": "Dorn's bloody path is a companion quest in \".\" Has a continuation in Throne of Bhaal extension. \nWalkthrough.\nAssassination of Guardian Trepfen.\nDorn will speak to you seven days later, if he is level 12 or higher.\nThrone of Bhaal.\nYou must have reputation below or equal 18 to recruit Dorn in ToB. He wont leave party if you increase reputation then.\nAfter Dorn has spent a week in your party in the extension, his script will force a special not-so-random encounter, an ambush from a &lt;a href=\"Planetar\"&gt;Planetar&lt;/a&gt; and several Crusaders. After killing the Crusaders and injuring the Planetar (who cannot be killed), the Planetar declares that both Gorion's Ward and Dorn have been put on the Scroll of Retribution, marking both for execution by celestial forces.\u00a0 One of the demons trapped in the Abyssal Blade suggests that you make an assault on Lunia in order to remove your name and Dorn's from the Scroll, and Dorn agrees.\u00a0 A portal at the ambush site can take you there.\nOnce in &lt;a href=\"Dorn%20-%20Lunia\"&gt;Lunia&lt;/a&gt;, another planetar can be found near the entrance giving &lt;a href=\"sigil%20of%20Tyr\"&gt;Sigils of Tyr&lt;/a&gt; to the assembled &lt;a href=\"Paladin%20of%20Tyr\"&gt;paladins&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Priest%20of%20Tyr\"&gt;priests of Tyr&lt;/a&gt;. You can either take one by force, steal it, or trick the planetar into giving you one (one way to accomplish this is to claim to be &lt;a href=\"Keldorn%20Firecam\"&gt;Keldorn&lt;/a&gt;, followed by explaining away the fact that Keldorn is a paladin of a different deity).\u00a0\nSome south from planetar is Bollard Firejaw (priest, killed in &lt;a href=\"High%20Hall%20of%20the%20Radiant%20Heart\"&gt;High Hall of the Radiant Heart&lt;/a&gt;). He will recognize Dorn and will want to kill your party. But there way to avoid confrontation (dialogue options 2-2-1-1-1).\nOn your way to the Scroll you may visit the Holy Tree in the northwest corner. From it you can obtain the unique &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Apple\"&gt;Silver Apple&lt;/a&gt;, although if Dorn remains alive and still tied to Ur-Gothoz, he will defile the tree and make the apples unobtainable no matter the conversation path (to avoid this, you need to go to tree in invisibility to avoid conversation with monks that stay near tree). On your way back from the Scroll, a gathering of a dozen people will appear near the tree: a planetar and several priests, paladins and onlookers; they will recognize Dorn as the defiler and attack (a bug will cause this even if you went to the Scroll via the southeastern stairs and never saw the tree before)(and another bug that's add dialogue option from another demon to defile tree).\nThe Scroll is in the northeast, guarded by several Paladins and the scribe &lt;a href=\"Naiman%20Alore\"&gt;Naiman Alore&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0Again, you can either kill the scribe or trick him into removing your names by claiming that the gods have ordered this and that they must be obeyed or trick him to get inks (then you can remove your names and add 2 too).\u00a0If you take the violent approach, you may add two other names to the scroll; After short time planetar and 3 priests will teleport near to you to revenge for rescribbed scroll. if you add the names of Bhaalspawn you have yet to fight, then during those fights you will be aided by a Planetar.\nIn any way, &lt;a href=\"Ixthezzys\"&gt;Ixthezzys&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dolrassa\"&gt;Dolrassa&lt;/a&gt;, two silver dragons, will try to prevent your escape.\u00a0You may prevent confrontation said that you are bhaalspawn, they will teleport away. They can optionally be killed; both drop &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Dragon%20Scales\"&gt;Silver Dragon Scales&lt;/a&gt; which &lt;a href=\"Cespenar\"&gt;Cespenar&lt;/a&gt; can forge into &lt;a href=\"Silver%20Dragon%20Scale\"&gt;Silver Dragon Scale armor&lt;/a&gt; for 5,000 gold each.\nAnd after dragons will be party of Baldwin (10 000xp) with 3 priests (22 000xp each) and 3 crusaders (8 000xp each). They guarding portals. You can kill them or avoid. If you said dragons that you are bhaalspawn, guards will attack you anyway.\nOnce you leave Lunia after removing your names from the Scroll, Dorn will proclaim victory, and the quest is complete."}
{"id": "43961", "revid": "5305940", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43961", "title": "Dorn - Lunia", "text": ""}
{"id": "7200", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7200", "title": "Dorn II-Khan", "text": ""}
{"id": "5123", "revid": "275446", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5123", "title": "Dorn Il-Khan", "text": "Dorn Il-Khan is a &lt;a href=\"male\"&gt;male&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"half-orc\"&gt;half-orc&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"neutral%20evil\"&gt;neutral evil&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"blackguard\"&gt;blackguard&lt;/a&gt; in the ', ' and the \"\".\n&lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; may choose him as a &lt;a href=\"companion\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt;.\nRecruitment.\nDorn is available to recruit in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20One\"&gt;Chapter One&lt;/a&gt;. You first meet him on the ground floor of the &lt;a href=\"The%20Friendly%20Arm\"&gt;The Friendly Arm&lt;/a&gt; where he scolds you for bothering him. You must later trigger his side quest to invite him to join at the cost of losing 2 &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt; points, which is regained when he leaves the party. He will return to the Friendly Arm when he is removed from the party. He will refuse to rejoin the party if your reputation is above 18.\nGameplay.\nA half-orc blackguard is a race/class combination off-limits to the player &lt;a href=\"Character%20Generation\"&gt;character generation&lt;/a&gt;.\nHis &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; of 19 points means that he can serve as a good melee fighter and the best pack mule. By attacking doors/locks he can open them as effectively as a thief with an Open Locks skill of 50.\nHis &lt;a href=\"charisma\"&gt;charisma&lt;/a&gt; of 16 makes him a decent \"face\" character for an evil party, granting you a good reaction adjustment and a minor discount on shop prices.\nAs a &lt;a href=\"blackguard\"&gt;blackguard&lt;/a&gt;, his &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Weapon\"&gt;poison weapon&lt;/a&gt; ability is immensely helpful in battles with enemy mages, unfortunately this ability has been severely nerfed by later patches in EE, restricting the gameplay strategies and usefulness of both blackguards and &lt;a href=\"assassin\"&gt;assassin&lt;/a&gt;s, who are the exclusive poison weapon ability users in original games.\nDorn\u2019s passive fear immunity makes him the only companion in game able to quaff &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Goblet\"&gt;Durlag's Goblet&lt;/a&gt; without the aid from &lt;a href=\"Kiel%27s%20Helmet\"&gt;Kiel's Helmet&lt;/a&gt;. Give the helmet to somebody else and you immediately have two party members who fully healed in seconds, you may also import this combo to SoD to extend its uses\nHis starting equipment is &lt;a href=\"Splint%20Mail\"&gt;Splint Mail&lt;/a&gt; and a two-handed sword +1, &lt;a href=\"Rancor\"&gt;Rancor&lt;/a&gt;, which gives him a +1 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus or +2 THAC0 bonus if he kills someone wielding the weapon in 24 hours. His proficiency points are two in each of Two-Handed Swords and the Two-Handed Weapon Style.\nRestrictions for alignment can be bypassed using the &lt;a href=\"Helmet%20of%20Opposite%20Alignment\"&gt;Helmet of Opposite Alignment&lt;/a&gt; to use his excellent stats in a Good party. It also allows you to romance him, if you like bad boys. \n\nRecruitment.\nDorn is available to recruit in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Nine%20%E2%80%93%20Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Chapter Nine&lt;/a&gt;, he's held captive by &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar&lt;/a&gt;'s crusaders and you'll find him inside a prison cell in the crusader camp at &lt;a href=\"Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Boareskyr Bridge&lt;/a&gt;. Thankfully, releasing him won't draw hostage attentions from the crusaders, but any items you placed in his inventory prior to his departure in Chapter 7 (SoD) are in a box just above the cage and his level is reset to default.\n\nRecruitment.\nDorn is available to recruit in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;. Travel to the southern part of &lt;a href=\"Temple%20District\"&gt;Temple District&lt;/a&gt;, talk to him to let him join, recruiting him will initiate a number of &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt;-damaging but rewarding quests. If dismissed at this stage, he will return to his original spot (Temple District).\nGameplay.\nAt the culminating point of his companion quest, you acquire the &lt;a href=\"Abyssal%20Blade\"&gt;Abyssal Blade&lt;/a&gt;, a blackguard-only +3 two-handed sword with additional effects depending on how you chose to complete his quest chain. The effects carry over into \"\". Siding with &lt;a href=\"Ur-Gothoz\"&gt;Ur-Gothoz&lt;/a&gt; will also earn him the powerful helmet &lt;a href=\"The%20Visage\"&gt;The Visage&lt;/a&gt;. If you decide to kill both Ur-Gothoz and Azothet, the Abyssal Blade will be imbued with the\u00a0souls of both patrons (+5 vs. good aligned, +5 vs demons and +5 vs devils) but Dorn will become a fallen blackguard and lose all his powers, turning him into a pure fighter of the same level. In addition, you will lose his final quest in Throne of Bhaal. If you leave at least one of them alive, be it Ur-Gothoz or Azothet, you unlock his final quest in the godly plane of Lunia. In &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Watcher's Keep&lt;/a&gt;, the player can get him the blackguard-only sword &lt;a href=\"Ir%27revrykal\"&gt;Ir'revrykal&lt;/a&gt;, effectively an\u00a0evil version of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Carsomyr\"&gt;Carsomyr&lt;/a&gt;. As the only party member with a natural 19 Strength, he is also the only character who can use the &lt;a href=\"Strong%20Arm\"&gt;Strong Arm&lt;/a&gt; bow without a strength-enhancing item.\nDefensively speaking, his 14 Constitution and 16 Dexterity put him at a disadvantage as a tank, but these can be compensated for with the &lt;a href=\"Girdle%20of%20Fortitude\"&gt;Girdle of Fortitude&lt;/a&gt;, which sets his Constitution to 18 for eight hours. Dorn is the only companion other than &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and &lt;a href=\"Valygar\"&gt;Valygar&lt;/a&gt; that can use &lt;a href=\"Defender%20of%20Easthaven\"&gt;Defender of Easthaven&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Hardiness\"&gt;Hardiness&lt;/a&gt;, making him an excellent physical damage tank. &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Draw Upon Holy Might&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0allows him to reach 25 Strength at level 26 without the use of magical equipment, which can be saved for other party members, along with 22 Dexterity and 20 Constitution.\nAt protagonist level 9, he starts with proficiencies in Two-Handed Sword, Crossbow, and Two-Handed Weapon Style. His starting equipment is &lt;a href=\"Plate%20Mail\"&gt;Plate Mail&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Basic%20Helmets%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%29\"&gt;Helmet&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Rancor\"&gt;Rancor&lt;/a&gt; (a +1 or +2 two-handed sword). As a level 8 Blackguard, he has the innate abilities &lt;a href=\"Resist%20Fear\"&gt;Resist Fear&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Negative%20Plane%20Protection\"&gt;Negative Plane Protection&lt;/a&gt;.\nBugs.\nAs of BG2EE 2.6, Dorn's first talk with the PC is supposed to be one of three, depending on your reputation and whether you known him from the events in BG. However, his script is always setting the variable that you knew him, so you always get one of the three banters and never see the other two options. This is identified for correction in the pending Enhanced Edition Fix Pack (EEFP). Ref: (dorn.bcs)"}
{"id": "47007", "revid": "27501436", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47007", "title": "Dorn Il-Khan/Quotes", "text": "Dorn Il-Khan's quotes presents lines spoken by &lt;a href=\"Dorn\"&gt;Dorn&lt;/a&gt;, together with the associated sound files.\nA half-orc of few words, Dorn generally keeps to himself, and replies to the remarks of the most eccentric members of the party either with terse answers or threats of physical harm. He is much friendlier with evil-aligned companions, exchanging playful banter with them and even giving them advice.\nDorn will have access to more dialog options after he finishes his personal quest, tempting good-aligned companions with the promise of great power were they to swear loyalty to a demon as he did. Despite his apparent brutality Dorn is a surprisingly stable companion, only ever getting in conflict with &lt;a href=\"Anomen\"&gt;Anomen&lt;/a&gt;, as he is aware it is much more valuable to corrupt noble souls than to slay do-gooders.\nDialogues.\nWith &lt;a href=\"Aerie\"&gt;Aerie&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Anomen\"&gt;Anomen&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Anomen has been knighted:\nThrone of Bhaal only, if Anomen failed his test :\nThrone of Bhaal only, if Anomen didn't fail his test :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Cernd\"&gt;Cernd&lt;/a&gt;.\nDuring Dorn's quest, in Resurrection Gorge :\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Edwin\"&gt;Edwin&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Dorn swore loyalty to a demon:\nIf Edwin has been turned into a woman as part of his quest :\nThrone of Bhaal only, if Dorn swore loyalty to a demon:\nThrone of Bhaal only, if Dorn didn't swear loyalty to a demon:\nWith &lt;a href=\"Haer%27Dalis\"&gt;Haer'Dalis&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Hexxat\"&gt;Hexxat&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf no romance with Dorn has started:\nThrone of Bhaal only, if Hexxat hasn't finished her TOB quest :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Korgan\"&gt;Korgan&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Korgan\"&gt;Korgan&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sarevok\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Sarevok is still evil :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Mazzy\"&gt;Mazzy&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal only :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Neera\"&gt;Neera&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal only : \nWith &lt;a href=\"Rasaad\"&gt;Rasaad&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Dorn has sworn loyalty to a demon :\nThrone of Bhaal only, after Rasaad's quest is complete :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Valygar\"&gt;Valygar&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Dorn has sworn loyalty to a demon :\nWith &lt;a href=\"Viconia\"&gt;Viconia&lt;/a&gt;.\nThrone of Bhaal only :"}
{"id": "9849", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9849", "title": "Dorn Il-Khan (quest)", "text": "This page is about &lt;a href=\"Dorn%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Dorn Il-Khan&lt;/a&gt;'s companion quest in \"\".\nQuestline.\nA False Start.\nStarting this questline requires that the party has talked to Dorn before on the first floor of &lt;a href=\"The%20Friendly%20Arm\"&gt;The Friendly Arm&lt;/a&gt;, and that they travel to the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt; from one of &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Carnival\"&gt;Carnival&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Leaf%20Forest\"&gt;Fire Leaf Forest&lt;/a&gt;, or the &lt;a href=\"Gibberling%20Mountains\"&gt;Gibberling Mountains&lt;/a&gt;. Any other method of getting there will not yield his appearance. The party will be waylaid by brigands led by &lt;a href=\"Senjak\"&gt;Senjak&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dorotea\"&gt;Dorotea&lt;/a&gt;, Dorn's former companions. Dorn charges in, clearing three bandits before the fight starts. After the bloodshed, he offers to join you.\nCharmed, I'm Sure.\nWander around with Dorn long enough and he'll eventually comment on his vendetta. His next target is necromancer &lt;a href=\"Kryll\"&gt;Kryll&lt;/a&gt;, another of his former companions, which leads you to &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt;. It's not really necessary to wait until Dorn talks about his next target, though. Speak to &lt;a href=\"Taris\"&gt;Taris&lt;/a&gt; outside the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Inn\"&gt;Nashkel Inn&lt;/a&gt;, then head to the &lt;a href=\"Gibberling%20Mountains\"&gt;Gibberling Mountains&lt;/a&gt;.\nKryll is expecting Dorn near a blood-stained rock (x=2550, y=1500). After satiating Dorn's thirst for her blood, find &lt;a href=\"Letter%20to%20Kryll\"&gt;a letter&lt;/a&gt; for Dorn from Kryll's body and trace it back to Taris to inform her about the misfortune of her husband. Should you wish to choose it, the last dialog option kicks off a forced sequence of responses aimed to torment her with a series of gruesome, although grimly whimsical and honest, details of her husband's demise which eventually leads her to turn hostile. Killing her results in a major reputation penalty.\nAnother One Bites the Dust.\nWhen the party reaches &lt;a href=\"Wyrm%27s%20Crossing\"&gt;Wyrm's Crossing&lt;/a&gt;, Dorn will remark on the proximity to his last former comrade and a revenge opportunity.\nPrepare ahead as &lt;a href=\"Simmeon\"&gt;Simmeon&lt;/a&gt; awaits you north of the inner side of the bridge (x=1090, y=290). It is important to note however that the bridge section where Simmeon awaits will not be accessible prior to .\u00a0Simeon will summon two &lt;a href=\"Thrall%20of%20Azothet\"&gt;Thralls of Azothet&lt;/a&gt; and is accompanied by a mage named &lt;a href=\"Sheila\"&gt;Sheila&lt;/a&gt; and an unnamed priest.\nAfter the fight, Dorn will talk more. From this point forwards, he'll gradually (based on in-game time) fill you with his tales, and his &lt;a href=\"romance\"&gt;romance&lt;/a&gt; route will become open to &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "12847", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12847", "title": "Dorotea", "text": "Dorotea, with &lt;a href=\"Senjak\"&gt;Senjak&lt;/a&gt;, three &lt;a href=\"Archer%20%28creature%29\"&gt;archers&lt;/a&gt; and two &lt;a href=\"bandit\"&gt;bandit&lt;/a&gt;s, ambush the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; when it first travels to the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt; area, as a part of &lt;a href=\"Dorn%20Il-Khan%20%28quest%29\"&gt;Dorn Il-Khan's companion quest&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlhough being heavily attacked by at least Dorotea and Senjak, &lt;a href=\"Dorn%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Dorn&lt;/a&gt; cannot die during this encounter, keeping one &lt;a href=\"Hit%20Dice\"&gt;hit point&lt;/a&gt; at minimum, no matter how hard they hit.\nThe encounter takes place before the party actually reaches the Nashkel Mines area, making it possibly the only non-random encounter to occur in a transition area."}
{"id": "37038", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37038", "title": "Dosia", "text": "Dosia is a female &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; devoted to &lt;a href=\"Ilmater\"&gt;Ilmater&lt;/a&gt; who joins the coalition between Baldur's Gate, Daggerford and Waterdeep to battle the crusade of &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar Argent&lt;/a&gt;. She only appears during the events of .\nLocation.\nThe triage where Dosia works is located in the southwestern \"corner\" of the map, near the High Command Tent.\nQuests.\nDosia gives out the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Uncommon%20Cold\"&gt;The Uncommon Cold&lt;/a&gt;. She is also involved in the quests &lt;a href=\"The%20Wounded%20Zealot\"&gt;The Wounded Zealot&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Memories%20of%20Battles%20Past\"&gt;Memories of Battles Past&lt;/a&gt;, but she will not be able to participate in those quests until The Uncommon Cold has been completed.\nServices.\nAs a cleric of &lt;a href=\"Ilmater\"&gt;Ilmater&lt;/a&gt;, Dosia offers the standard healing and &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt;-boosting donation services of any normal temple. She can only act in this manner once &lt;a href=\"The%20Uncommon%20Cold\"&gt;The Uncommon Cold&lt;/a&gt; has been completed.\nSiege of the Camp.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20the%20Camp\"&gt;Siege of the Camp&lt;/a&gt;, Dosia will stand in the central area and offer two services in-between waves of enemies. The first service is to heal all injuries taken by the party. The second service is to \"take on their suffering\", which fully heals the party and also replenishes all expended spells or other abilities as if the party had completed a rest.\nIf the player has Dosia take on their suffering three times during the course of the battle, she will die of the strain once the enemy has been repelled.\nIf she survives the assault, she will partake in the assault on &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle&lt;/a&gt; in Chapter 11, and can be found offering her services as a temple outside of the gate into the interior keep area once the crusaders have been repelled."}
