{"id": "52339", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52339", "title": "Down with the Drawbridge", "text": "Down with the Drawbridge is a in \"\".\nAcquisition.\nOnce the &lt;a href=\"Wardstone%20%28Siege%20of%20Dragonspear%29\"&gt;Bridgefort Wardstone&lt;/a&gt; is gained, it can be taken to the &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Crusader&lt;/a&gt; encampment at the &lt;a href=\"Boareskyr%20Bridge\"&gt;Boareskyr Bridge&lt;/a&gt;. \nWalkthrough.\n&lt;a href=\"Kharm\"&gt;Kharm&lt;/a&gt; will task you with sneaking inside &lt;a href=\"Bridgefort\"&gt;Bridgefort&lt;/a&gt; and lowering the drawbridge to allow them entrance.\nRevealing that you opened the gate for the Crusaders will cause a loss of 2 &lt;a href=\"Reputation\"&gt;Reputation&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "26694", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26694", "title": "Dra'tan", "text": "Dra'tan can be found on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne%20Headquarters\"&gt;Iron Throne Headquarters&lt;/a&gt;, standing between the two sets of stairs. He'll approach the party upon sight and begin a conversation.\nDialogue.\n\"Where do you think you're going?\"\nHe goes hostile and summons seven &lt;a href=\"Guard\"&gt;Guard&lt;/a&gt;'s.\nThese last two options both result in Dra'tan heading for the stairs and disappearing and a &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; entry in the quest section under the heading: \"Investigating the Iron Throne\""}
{"id": "48702", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48702", "title": "Dracandros", "text": "Dracandros is one of four individuals found inside of a nondescript generic &lt;a href=\"Storehouse%20%28Bridge%20District%29\"&gt;building&lt;/a&gt; located in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt;. He's evil from the get-go and isn't hesitant to start casting spells the second the party enters the premises. The mage will not engage in melee combat, and has no weaponry, other than his immense 22 Strength potential.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes a few changes to this mage. The creature is revised to be a level 14 Conjurer. A new array of spells is provided, some being different than the unmodded selection. With the \"Smarter Mages\" component, the mage is assigned a SCS mage script for better spell casting behavior. A ready to use &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt; is prepared for instant deployment. Expect the mage to summon a Fiend to his aid, right after a string of self-protective buffs are triggered. An SCS random treasure is added to the mage's inventory.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod is installed, the mage's memorized spells will be the SR versions."}
{"id": "5938", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5938", "title": "Draconis", "text": "Draconis is encountered during the and game versions.\nDraconis is the spawn of &lt;a href=\"Abazigal\"&gt;Abazigal&lt;/a&gt;, one of &lt;a href=\"The%20Five\"&gt;The Five&lt;/a&gt;.\nDraconis takes two forms in the game, &lt;a href=\"Draconis%20%28humanoid%20form%29\"&gt;Draconis (humanoid form)&lt;/a&gt; and later &lt;a href=\"Draconis%20%28dragon%20form%29\"&gt;Draconis (dragon form)&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe initial meeting with Draconis takes place in the &lt;a href=\"Abazigal%27s%20Entrance\"&gt;Abazigal's Entrance&lt;/a&gt; location.\nSee the links for details, gameplay, statistics, treasure and further information."}
