{"id": "56244", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56244", "title": "Draconis (dragon form)", "text": "Draconis is encountered during the and game versions.\nThe dragon form of Draconis will appear and replace the &lt;a href=\"Draconis%20%28humanoid%20form%29\"&gt;Draconis (humanoid form)&lt;/a&gt; when the creature is reduced to near death hit point loss. The human form is gone from the map and the dragon form replaces it."}
{"id": "56243", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=56243", "title": "Draconis (humanoid form)", "text": "&lt;a href=\"Draconis%20%28humanoid%20form%29\"&gt;Draconis (humanoid form)&lt;/a&gt; is encountered during the and game versions.\nThe mage will be found in the &lt;a href=\"Abazigal%27s%20Entrance\"&gt;Abazigal's Entrance&lt;/a&gt; area, in front of the gate leading to Abazigal's Lair complex inside a stone cliff face.\nGameplay.\nWhen a party member is within detection range of Draconis, it will initiate dialogue - note that being hidden/invisible won't prevent this.\n&lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; must make a dialogue reply selection, perhaps asking some questions and in-turn receiving several different possible remarks from Draconis - in the end the exchange leads to hostilities.\nDraconis will be able to deploy several contingency/spell trigger actions at this time, and a dialogue trigger will include the instant conjuring of four &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20Stalker\"&gt;Invisible Stalker&lt;/a&gt; foes adjacent to the nearest party member.\nFrom then on, the creature's actions are dictated by the scripted spell casting situation criteria noted on the InfoBox.\nThis creature has a spell casting speed bonus, equivalent to that afforded by the &lt;a href=\"Robe%20of%20Vecna\"&gt;Robe of Vecna&lt;/a&gt;.\nTake note of the many status effect immunities that Draconis has on the InfoBox, and the lack of immunity to physical and some other damage types.\nDraconis is designed to survive and not be instantly killed so that when he is reduced to near death status from Hit Point loss, it allows a dialogue and a transformation to the next stage of the battle.\nHe'll say:\nThe player's display screen will briefly go black, and when the transition is over and the screen display resumes, the humanoid form of Draconis is removed from the map and replaced by the &lt;a href=\"Draconis%20%28dragon%20form%29\"&gt;Draconis (dragon form)&lt;/a&gt;. \nNote that this new creature is in full health, and no beneficial or negative status effects from the first form are transferred to the second form - it is essentially a brand-new opponent.\nSee that article for information about what transpires next.\nMod content.\nIf the player has the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod installed, certain selected mod components and the game difficulty selection will revise this creature to a varying degree - especially its spell casting scripts and variety of magic spell use.\nDraconis will have a randomly determine mage specialist kit assigned (Conjurer, Enchanter, invoker or Necromancer), and the kit determines the memorized spells and contents of the prepared &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Sequencer\"&gt;Minor Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Sequencer\"&gt;Spell Sequencer&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trigger\"&gt;Spell Trigger&lt;/a&gt;.\nOn higher difficulty settings, expect mage &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; use, such as &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Blades%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Energy Blades (wizard)&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Dark%20Planetar\"&gt;Summon Dark Planetar&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Breath%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Dragon's Breath (spell)&lt;/a&gt;, and or &lt;a href=\"Comet\"&gt;Comet&lt;/a&gt;.\nAdditionally, Draconis will now attempt to remove spell and combat protections from opponents, unlike the original game version - such as with &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Thrust\"&gt;Spell Thrust&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Khelben%27s%20Warding%20Whip\"&gt;Khelben's Warding Whip&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spellstrike\"&gt;Spellstrike&lt;/a&gt; and multiple uses of &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt;.\nSCS will make use of the spells from the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod if installed alongside. This usually results in additional steps by the party and Draconis in the spell targeting, and spell removal chess-match dynamic."}
{"id": "9560", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9560", "title": "Dradeel", "text": "Dradeel is an &lt;a href=\"Elf\"&gt;elven&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;, worshipper of &lt;a href=\"Sel%C3%BBne\"&gt;Sel\u00fbne&lt;/a&gt;, and a survivor of &lt;a href=\"Balduran\"&gt;Balduran's&lt;/a&gt; final voyage to the isles of &lt;a href=\"Anchorome\"&gt;Anchorome&lt;/a&gt;. He is originally from &lt;a href=\"Tethyr\"&gt;Tethyr&lt;/a&gt;, a region south of &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; where most of takes place. He dabbles in gourmet cooking, but not all his experiments turn out to be nourishing.\nTales of the Sword Coast.\nHe is trapped in his &lt;a href=\"Dradeel%27s%20Cabin\"&gt;hut&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Lycanthrope%20Island%20North\"&gt;northern&lt;/a&gt; half of the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Isle of Balduran&lt;/a&gt;, besieged by \"beasts\". He will ask &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party to venture into the rotting remains of the &lt;a href=\"Wandering%20Eye\"&gt;Wandering Eye&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Returning%20Dradeel%27s%20Spellbook\"&gt;retrieve&lt;/a&gt; his &lt;a href=\"Dradeel%27s%20Spellbook\"&gt;spellbook&lt;/a&gt; so he can regain the use of his spells. If Gorion's Ward helps him and returns the spellbook, he may show up later in the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran%20South\"&gt;Werewolf Village&lt;/a&gt; after &lt;a href=\"Tailas\"&gt;Tailas&lt;/a&gt; turns the inhabitants against the party. He will direct the party towards the &lt;a href=\"Werewolf%20Caverns\"&gt;warrens&lt;/a&gt; underneath the town as a means of escape, then teleport away.\nThough he is a 20th-level mage, he is only able to cast three spells \u2014 even after his spellbook has been returned:\nAs such, fighting him is inadvisable.\nBaldur's Gate II.\nIn , Dradeel is in a cell in &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;, an asylum where the &lt;a href=\"Cowled%20Wizards\"&gt;Cowled Wizards&lt;/a&gt; keep prisoners (mentally-unbalanced or otherwise) taken into custody for magic-related crimes. He is put there because of what is likely PTSD and possibly schizophrenia. He can give Gorion's Ward a &lt;a href=\"Dradeel%27s%20recipe%20pages\"&gt;recipe&lt;/a&gt; that has no further use, except selling it for economical purposes or keeping it for sentimental reasons, but it does provide a real recipe for cooking or baking.\nGameplay.\nDradeel can be found on the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Main%20Floor\"&gt;Main Floor&lt;/a&gt; of the asylum in Chapter 4. He has his own assigned cell and his off-kilter mannerisms and attitude reflect mental illness.\nThe party may initiate further dialogue by speaking with him in the inmate cellblock area.\nDuring the first meeting with the inmates, including Dradeel, it is not possible to kill any of them as the entire group of loonies is equipped with an &lt;a href=\"MINHP1.ITM\"&gt;amulet&lt;/a&gt; that protects them from death. \nLater, Dradeel will join with the party to defeat Irenicus in the final battle of the Asylum adventure. He will not be a controllable creature during the fight but will take spell casting action as scripted to defend himself and attack Irenicus and any hostile creatures in the battle zone. The conjurer has a well populated spellbook of memorized spells levels 1 through 8.\nLike all of the inmates, he dies during the fight against &lt;a href=\"Irenicus\"&gt;Irenicus&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Basement\"&gt;Spellhold Basement&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nMods.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; revises Dradeel's memorized spells and AI in the BG2 version. The mod also randomly revises mage kit assignment on install, and he could be an Invoker or an Enchanter for example. This will allow a more robust initial pre-buffing of protective spells at the outset of hostilities, especially against Irenicus - who also has a deadlier initial attack phase. \nIn the unmodded game he only applies an initial moderate spell protection and may be insufficient against some spells cast by Irenicus, such as Horrid Wilting or Wail of the Banshee. With SCS he has more staying power and can remain in the fight longer. The mod also furnishes Dradeel with a potion for quaffing use.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod will change his spells to the mod versions."}
