{"id": "26920", "revid": "247443", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26920", "title": "Dradeel's recipe pages", "text": "At &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;, Dradeel gives one of his four recipe pages to the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; when &lt;a href=\"Dradeel\"&gt;the mage&lt;/a&gt; is addressed a second time. While the chances are roughly a third each for three of the , the &lt;a href=\"%23Ruby%20Racks\"&gt;fourth&lt;/a&gt; one will only be obtained in one of ten thousand plays through \"\".\nDradeel's Recipes.\nThe chances which of the four recipes will be given are calculated during a conversation that only happens once, when talking with &lt;a href=\"Dradeel\"&gt;Dradeel&lt;/a&gt; the second time. They aren't equal, and it's highly improbable that \"&lt;a href=\"%23Ruby%20Racks\"&gt;the pride of the book&lt;/a&gt;\" will be obtained. The recipes are ordered here by probability, starting with the highest."}
{"id": "45584", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45584", "title": "Dragomir", "text": "Dragomir the Red is a vampire trapped within &lt;a href=\"Dragomir%27s%20Tomb\"&gt;Dragomir's Tomb&lt;/a&gt; in the \"\" game.\nGame Play.\nDragomir will address the nearest party member when within a moderate distance. Dragomir is somewhat arrogant and demands respect. Various dialogue choices are available, culminating in a hostile reaction from him.\nDragomir has the usual immunities provided to all vampires and most undead. Only weapons with a +2 enchantment or greater can strike him. See the InfoBox for a listing of other abilities and immunities.\nAs a Fighter with grandmastery proficiency in two-handed swords and two-handed Weapon skill at 2 pips, he can strike hard and fast with his +2 enchanted great sword. These blows do not induce a level drain effect like other vampiric touch attacks.\nThe game gave Dragomir no memorized spells, however the AI script provides the creature with a &lt;a href=\"Domination%20%28Innate%29\"&gt;Vampire Domination&lt;/a&gt; that can be discharged multiple times as an innate ability, and he may attempt to use that on anyone in his visual range. A save vs. spell with a small penalty negates. This script looks for races resistant to charms, classes with charm resistance, and items that provide immunity to charm. The creature will then select another target if possible.\nIf you succeed in slaying Dragomir, you can loot the body. You may leave the Cloak of Dragomir laying with his corpse if you wish, as Hexxat will pick it up on her own as she exits the Tomb. If you pick it up into your inventory, Hexxat will have to ask you for it before she can leave.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; makes no changes to the creature but provides a default SCS AI fighter script for improved tactical behavior."}
{"id": "12133", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12133", "title": "Dragomir's Respite", "text": "Dragomir's Respite is a which has a basic capacity for one hundred &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; stacks to store any type of item in it. One of the hundred slots, however, is permanently&lt;a href=\"%23Notes\"&gt;1&lt;/a&gt; occupied by an &lt;a href=\"Empty%20Casket\"&gt;Empty Casket&lt;/a&gt;. The bag has a fixed weight of 5 pounds, no matter the weight or number of items put into it.\nBugs.\nA well-known bug and still present as of v. 2.6.6.0: when you have Dragomir's respite in the inventory while starting TOB, and call Hexxat in the Pocket Plane (even without actually recruiting her for the group), an exact copy of the bag will appear in the inventory of the main char. It contains exact the same items, but they are not copies - if you take something out of one of the bags, it will disappear out of the other too. This can be used to make transfer between characters a bit easier. But putting one of the bags on the floor can destroy most of the items."}
{"id": "13494", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13494", "title": "Dragomir's Tomb", "text": "Dragomir's Tomb is a dungeon in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Graveyard%20District\"&gt;Graveyard District&lt;/a&gt; in \"Shadows of Amn\" campaign of \". It is entered via secret doorway within area AR0811 called \"Crypt (near Arenthis &amp; Risa)\"\". This door will only manifest if you have &lt;a href=\"Clara\"&gt;Clara&lt;/a&gt; in your party and initiated the quest."}
