{"id": "9169", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9169", "title": "Dragon's Breath (item)", "text": "Dragon's Breath is an halberd +4. The blade deals piercing or slashing damage (despite the erroneous weapon description), to which is added 1 point from each of the five types of &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20damage\"&gt;Elemental damage&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis item appears in ' and '.\nAcquisition.\nIt is dropped by &lt;a href=\"Boz\"&gt;Boz&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; when the party leaves &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt; after being asked to rescue &lt;a href=\"Phaere\"&gt;Phaere&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4683", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4683", "title": "Dragon's Breath (spell)", "text": "Dragons Breath is a\u00a0party friendly &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; usable by &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt; classes.\nGameplay.\nDragon's Breath completely ignores &lt;a href=\"MR\"&gt;MR&lt;/a&gt;, thus the spell has its uses against resistant enemies like &lt;a href=\"drow\"&gt;drow&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lich\"&gt;Lich&lt;/a&gt; creatures. \nThe internal effects of this HLA are level 9 &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt;. A &lt;a href=\"Demilich%20%28Watcher%27s%20Keep%29\"&gt;Demilich&lt;/a&gt; in the unmodified game is immune to levels 1 through 9, so this spell will probably not affect such a creature.\nAs the spell is also not a single-target spell, it will not be intercepted by a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt; for example.\nObviously, enemy creatures with &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance are a less desirable target choice for this spell.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this High-level class ability spell, revising its casting time, effects, saving throw, school, and description. See below:\nDragon's Breath\nLevel: Epic\nSchool: Evocation\nRange: Long\nDuration: Instant\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 30\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: Breath partial\nThis spell causes the disembodied head of a red dragon to appear and breathe fire with the strength of an adult red dragon. In addition to the enormous 24d6 fireball, the force of the dragon\u2019s breath knocks opponents away from the caster and leaves them unconscious for 1 round. The victims can save vs. breath at a -2 penalty to take half damage and not be blown backwards. This spell will not harm party members. Magic resistance does not affect this spell."}
