{"id": "46467", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46467", "title": "Dragon (Watchers Keep Final Seal)", "text": "This Dragon is encountered in the or game editions.\nThe creature can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%E2%80%93%20Challenge%20Room%20%28Dragon%29\"&gt;the center challenge room&lt;/a&gt;, accessed via the &lt;a href=\"Helmite%20Ghost\"&gt;Helmite Ghost&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; dungeon level.\nGameplay.\nThe party will eventually have to enter the center gateway (one of three Challenge rooms) after the Helmite Ghost has informed the party that the challenges await them - this is tracked in the &lt;a href=\"Unlocking%20the%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Unlocking the Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; questline and associated journal entries.\nUpon entry, the party is positioned on stone stairs descending below. The look of the stairwell is similar to places the party has probably been before where a dragon has been encountered, such as &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Hideout\"&gt;Firkraag's Hideout&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20%E2%80%93%20Saladrex%20%28Dragon%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep \u2013 Saladrex (Dragon)&lt;/a&gt; areas.\nThe party must be gathered to enter here, and it can't be split. Once this area is entered, it can't be exited until the challenge ahead is resolved.\nAs the party moves forward from the stairs and emerges into a cavernous arched chamber - and when a member is detected, a huge green dragon will rumble an initial two lines of dialogue, and then attack. The creature can &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;, so being hidden won't prevent this. The dragon's hostile action doesn't allow the party to reply or afford an opportunity to engage in dialogue.\nThe first action by the beast is to apply its initial preparatory protection buff of &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Death%20Ward\"&gt;Death Ward&lt;/a&gt; on itself, followed a second later with a &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Magic\"&gt;Remove Magic&lt;/a&gt; directed at the closest party member. These spells can't be interrupted.\nThe next action will probably see the dragon radiating a &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Fear\"&gt;Dragon Fear&lt;/a&gt; aura and a &lt;a href=\"Wing%20Buffet\"&gt;Wing Buffet&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the dragon detects an &lt;a href=\"Incendiary%20Cloud\"&gt;Incendiary Cloud&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Stinking%20Cloud\"&gt;Stinking Cloud&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Death%20Fog\"&gt;Death Fog&lt;/a&gt; it will also initiate a Wing Buffet to disperse those.\nIf the dragon senses any invisibility effects upon the party, it will launch a &lt;a href=\"True%20Sight\"&gt;True Sight&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nWhen the dragon has zero &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; layers remaining it applies another (10-skins).\nThe creature will direct a &lt;a href=\"Plant%20Growth\"&gt;Plant Growth&lt;/a&gt; spell over itself when an enemy is within 15 feet. This spell has a large saving throw penalty and is difficult to block. An affected party member is essentially unable to move from its spot, where it is rooted in a stationary point on the map. The entangled party member may still fight and cast spells but can't maneuver.\nWithin three to four rounds of combat, the dragon will begin to use its &lt;a href=\"Green%20Dragon%20Breath\"&gt;Green Dragon Breath&lt;/a&gt; weapon attack at the closest opponent in range. The breath weapon may affect other party members in the area of effect. This can be done again after several more rounds have transpired.\nWhen the dragon's wounds have reduced its &lt;a href=\"HP\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; below 50%, the beast can initiate a &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; spell, and this completely restores its original HP and can cure several status effects as well.\nFurther along in the battle, if the creature is still functioning, a &lt;a href=\"Summon%20Insects%20%28innate%29\"&gt;Summon Insects (innate)&lt;/a&gt; spell is attempted at a party spell casting class member (Bard, Mage, Druid, Cleric etc.), as long as their &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; is below 50%.\nMuch later in the battle, possibly never occurring, the dragon can attempt a &lt;a href=\"Domination\"&gt;Domination&lt;/a&gt; spell at a party member who has less than 50% magic resistance.\nObviously, party members in melee attack range will also be engaged by the dragon's slashing claw attacks, which will have a good chance of connecting against even superior armor class ratings.\nIf no party members engage the dragon in close quarters combat, the beast will advance and move into melee range on its own.\nWhen the party defeats this beast, almost immediately afterwards the Helmite Ghost materializes in the chamber and delivers a message, saying:\nEach party member receives quest experience points (), and the exit back to the level above is now accessible.\nDon't forget to take the items and gold the dragon carried. You'll need some these to progress the adventure.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; revises this dragon in many ways. Especially if you install the \"Smarter Dragons\" component (which is responsive to the game difficulty selection). \nHis SCS AI improves targeting and recognition of opponent's protections, which means he will fight smarter and not waste attacks on someone he cannot hit or damage. \nIt will also influence his tactical options and attack methods. First, some mention of the dragon's stats and abilities. In most cases, all of the unmodded ones are still applicable:\nImmunities in addition to the unmodded dragon version:\nSpells: The dragon's scripted spell use is revised. It can use the following spells, as determined by the AI's need: \nWith the installation of the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod, some of the dragon's arcane and divine memorized spells will be the SR version.\nGame difficulty settings determine how often the dragon can use &lt;a href=\"Wing%20Buffet\"&gt;Wing Buffet&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Green%20Dragon%20Breath\"&gt;Green Dragon Breath&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe dragon will have a random scroll in its droppable loot."}
{"id": "16771", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16771", "title": "Dragon Blade", "text": "The Dragon Blade is carried by a &lt;a href=\"Rashemen\"&gt;Rashemen&lt;/a&gt; warrior named &lt;a href=\"Rigah\"&gt;Rigah&lt;/a&gt; who's involved in &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt;'s companion quest in , &lt;a href=\"The%20Wychlaran%20and%20the%20Berserker\"&gt;The Wychlaran and the Berserker&lt;/a&gt;. This item can be &lt;a href=\"Importing%23cite_note-5\"&gt;imported&lt;/a&gt; into . It can be found on the corpse of &lt;a href=\"Tazok\"&gt;Tazok&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt; as long as the conditions are met as discussed on the &lt;a href=\"Importing\"&gt;Importing&lt;/a&gt; article (ref: AR1202.bcs).\nGameplay.\nThis weapon's critical hit effect (+2d4 cold damage and slow) can be used consistently at high levels via the &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Strike\"&gt;Critical Strike&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Smite\"&gt;Smite&lt;/a&gt; High-Level Abilities, meaning that even non-Berserkers/Barbarians/Minsc warriors can eventually use it just as effectively.\nThe critical hit chance increase effect will only work with &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Barbarian%20Rage\"&gt;Barbarian Rage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Berserk%20%28ability%29\"&gt;Berserk ability&lt;/a&gt; and cannot be triggered by the actual &lt;a href=\"Berserk\"&gt;Berserk&lt;/a&gt; status effect or by &lt;a href=\"Morale\"&gt;Morale failure: Berserk&lt;/a&gt;. Despite the fact the effect is programmed to last for 2 turns, switching to another weapon will quickly remove it."}
