{"id": "47035", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47035", "title": "Dragon Disciple", "text": "Dragon Disciples are powerful Sorcerers with dragons' blood somewhere in their lineage. Their natural magical talents bring out their draconic heritage, allowing them to cast powerful magical spells and exhibit dragon-like abilities.\nDragon Disciple is the only kit available for the &lt;a href=\"sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt; class. They have access to &lt;a href=\"Breath%20Weapon\"&gt;Breath Weapon&lt;/a&gt; once per day from 3rd level, but are limited to one fewer spell per level per day.\nKit features.\nBreath weapon: The dragon disciple breathes out a gout of flame up to 30 ft long, inflicting 3d8 of damage on all creatures caught within the 140 degree cone. Damage increases with levels.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"https%3A//artisans-corner.com/the-artisans-kitpack/\"&gt;The Artisan's Kitpack&lt;/a&gt; mod revises (and most would say improves) this kit, adding additional features.\n&lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.gibberlings3.net/mods/npcs/glam-npc-pack/\"&gt;Glam's NPC Pack&lt;/a&gt; mod provides a potential BG I party companion Dragon Disciple named \"Flara\" - She is recruitable at the Belching dragon inn in Nashkel."}
{"id": "9227", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9227", "title": "Dragon Eggs", "text": "Dragon Eggs is an item needed in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%205\"&gt;chapter 5&lt;/a&gt; of and . They have been stolen by &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Adalon\"&gt;Adalon&lt;/a&gt; to secure a deal with the &lt;a href=\"drow\"&gt;drow&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;. Adalon enhances the party of &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; with a magical disguise which makes them look like drow. If the player character returns the stolen eggs to Adalon, they will receive &lt;a href=\"Necaradan%27s%20Crossbow\"&gt;Necaradan's Crossbow&lt;/a&gt;. The eggs can alternatively be handed over to the &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Demon%20Lord\"&gt;Lesser Demon Lord&lt;/a&gt; summoned by &lt;a href=\"Matron%20Mother%20Ardulace%20Despana\"&gt;Matron Mother Ardulace&lt;/a&gt;, to receive the halberd &lt;a href=\"Blackmist\"&gt;Blackmist&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "49697", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49697", "title": "Dragon Fear", "text": "Dragon Fear is an innate instantaneous aura that has a 30' area of effect. Depending on the Dragon, this effect may be reapplied at a regular interval, such as once every round or less frequently. It affects only Dragon enemies. The effect is applied almost with no delay using SPIN895.SPL \"Dragon Fear\". The innate spell-like effect has no assigned school or type and has &lt;a href=\"power%20level\"&gt;power level&lt;/a&gt; 0. Enemies not immune to fear must save vs. spell with a -4 penalty or be under an &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt; 24 \"Horror\" effect, also referred to as &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; in the game - for a duration of 10 rounds (60 seconds). \nA failed saving throw will display a \"Panic\" icon in the victim's portrait. Additionally, the victim will also suffer a -2 THAC0 penalty as well. When under a panic effect, the victim will run about aimlessly with a yellow circle around their map screen animation. \nDragon Fear is unaffected by magic resistance or spell level projections (such as Globes of Invulnerability or Spell Deflection). The effect cannot be dispelled. Spells that remove fear will bring the affected victim out of the Horror/Panic state. Additionally, a sound effect will be played if anyone is affected by the Dragon Fear, and another will play when the spell expires.\nThere is another Dragon Fear innate spell in the EE game assigned as OHBDRAG2.SPL. This particular Dragon Fear ability is mostly similar to the above version, but the saving throw has a bonus of +7."}
{"id": "5282", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5282", "title": "Dragon Helm", "text": "Dragon Helm gives the wearer a 25% bonus to resistance to fire, cold and electric resistance. It can be compared to the &lt;a href=\"Gift%20of%20Peace\"&gt;Helmet of Defense&lt;/a&gt;, which provides 5% less resistance, but gives a bonus to saving throw. This item appears in .\nLocation.\nIt can be found in the dungeons of &lt;a href=\"Windspear%20Hills\"&gt;Windspear Hills&lt;/a&gt;. It is placed in a bucket in a well. When the bucket is raised, the party must defeat an air elemental."}
{"id": "43958", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43958", "title": "Dragon Rain", "text": "Dragon Rain is a spell-like ability that is not implemented in-game. While some enemies are immune to it through undroppable items like &lt;a href=\"RING95.ITM\"&gt;RING95.ITM&lt;/a&gt;, nothing in the game actually uses Dragon Rain."}
{"id": "5283", "revid": "280454", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5283", "title": "Dragon Scale Shield", "text": "The Dragon Scale Shield is an enchanted medium shield +2 which offers a bonus to &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; of 3. It also offers 25% resistance to fire, cold and electrical damage, like the &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Helm\"&gt;Dragon Helm&lt;/a&gt;. The shield has a weight of 5 lbs. and requires 12 &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; to wield.\nDespite being made from &lt;a href=\"dragon\"&gt;dragon&lt;/a&gt; scales, this shield is metallic and can't be used by &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt;s."}
