{"id": "40417", "revid": "257377", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40417", "title": "Dragonspear Castle", "text": "Dragonspear Castle is an infamous fortress on the Sword Coast of the Forgotten Realms. Lying within reach of Baldur's Gate, Waterdeep and Athkatla, the castle is built around a portal to &lt;a href=\"Avernus\"&gt;Avernus&lt;/a&gt;, the first of the Nine Hells. At several points in history, devils have used this portal to launch full-scale invasions of the Sword Coast, which have been beaten back, albeit at great cost.\nAs the game's title suggests, Dragonspear Castle is integral to the events of , which revolves around a coalition of forces from Baldur's Gate, Waterdeep and Daggerford laying siege to the castle after it is captured by the &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Shining Crusade&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Caelar%20Argent\"&gt;Caelar Argent&lt;/a&gt;, which seeks to open the portal and launch an invasion of Avernus instead."}
