{"id": "25779", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25779", "title": "Dragonspear Castle Basement", "text": " Missable warning: &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Ten%20%E2%80%93%20Allied%20Siege%20Camp\"&gt;Certain triggers&lt;/a&gt; in this area forward the quest-line unexpectedly,potentially winding up into a point of no return without noticing, be sure to finish allside quests before the triggers\nDragonspear Castle Basement is an area that appears in both &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Ten%20%E2%80%93%20Allied%20Siege%20Camp\"&gt;Chapter Ten&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Eleven%20%E2%80%93%20Dragonspear%20Castle%20Battle\"&gt;Eleven&lt;/a&gt;. In Chapter Ten, you gain access to it via &lt;a href=\"The%20Warrens\"&gt;The Warrens&lt;/a&gt; but the upper portion is locked until chap 11, by when you arrive this area from the upper portion exit to the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Keep%20First%20Floor\"&gt;First Floor&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is briefly possible to obtain a &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Axe%20%2B3\"&gt;Battle Axe +3&lt;/a&gt; from crusaders from the cut-scene just before the portal to Avernus is opened in the portal room in the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Basement\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Basement&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlthough even though a &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Axe%20%2B3\"&gt;Battle Axe +3&lt;/a&gt; can be obtained in without cheats; it is quite hidden and not obvious to do so. A sort of portal door clip is required. Where a party member is 'forced' though the locked door into the portal room before the cut-scene is triggered by dialog. This door clip could be an exploit but it can be done without using cheats and it can be done with various methods in an unmodified game. Then from there multiple traps (such as &lt;a href=\"Skull%20Trap\"&gt;Skull Trap&lt;/a&gt;) must be placed (on top of one another) where the crusaders will spawn during the portal opening cut-scene. A party member must then trigger the cut scene via dialog on the castle basement side of the still locked portal room door. If enough traps were placed effectively before the cut-scene starts, the crusaders will spawn in during the cut-scene and be killed by the traps.\nThe cut-scene crusaders in the portal room of the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Basement\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Basement&lt;/a&gt; drop many magical +1 and +2 weapons and armour; as well as various magical potions, ammunition, wands and mage robes. Some of these magical items include a &lt;a href=\"Composite%20Longbow%20%2B1\"&gt;Composite Longbow +1&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Studded%20Leather%20Armor%20%2B2\"&gt;Studded Leather Armor +2&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=\"https%3A//static.wikia.nocookie.net/baldursgategame/images/c/c8/ILEAT1500000.PNG\"&gt;BG2 v2&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Mail%20%2B2\"&gt;Chain Mail +2&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Quarterstaff%20%2B2\"&gt;Quarterstaff +2&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Halberd%20%2B2\"&gt;Halberd +2&lt;/a&gt;, a duplicate of the Short Sword +2 &lt;a href=\"The%20Whistling%20Sword\"&gt;The Whistling Sword&lt;/a&gt;. Some magical items may even be unique and or first encounters of said items within and ; this is the case for a &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Axe%20%2B3\"&gt;Battle Axe +3&lt;/a&gt;.\nA chest in Hephernan's Chambers contains a &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity&lt;/a&gt; scroll."}
{"id": "25840", "revid": "5653418", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25840", "title": "Dragonspear Castle Exterior", "text": "Dragonspear Castle Exterior is where you arrive from &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;world map&lt;/a&gt; travel, it's shown as \"&lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle&lt;/a&gt;\" on map, for obvious reasons.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Ten%20%E2%80%93%20Allied%20Siege%20Camp\"&gt;Chapter Ten \u2013 Allied Siege Camp&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"The%20Crusade\"&gt;crusaders&lt;/a&gt; camped here don't recognize your identity so you're free to explore and run quests until they do; in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Eleven%20%E2%80%93%20Dragonspear%20Castle%20Battle\"&gt;Chapter Eleven \u2013 Dragonspear Castle Battle&lt;/a&gt;, it will become a battle ground where you must push though enemy waves and venture into the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Keep%20First%20Floor\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Keep First Floor&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe notes in the infobox are for Chapter Ten, except traps, which appear only in Chapter Eleven."}
