{"id": "30781", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30781", "title": "Draw Upon Holy Might (ability)", "text": "Draw Upon Holy Might is an &lt;a href=\"Innate%20abilities\"&gt;ability&lt;/a&gt; that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; may gain during the \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" campaign. It is identical to the 2nd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28spell%29\"&gt;same name&lt;/a&gt;, except that it is not subject to silence (as it is not a spell).\nIt can be gained during &lt;a href=\"Dreams%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;dream sequence 5 and 6&lt;/a&gt; if the party's &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt; is 10 or greater; if it is less, then the protagonist will gain &lt;a href=\"Vampiric%20Touch%20%28ability%29\"&gt;Vampiric Touch&lt;/a&gt; instead.\nWhen a new protagonist is created in \"&lt;a href=\"Shadows%20of%20Amn\"&gt;Shadows of Amn&lt;/a&gt;\", this ability will be granted to them based on their &lt;a href=\"alignment\"&gt;alignment&lt;/a&gt;:"}
{"id": "4897", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4897", "title": "Draw Upon Holy Might (spell)", "text": "Draw Upon Holy Might is a 2nd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; only usable by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt;s. It increases the &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Constitution\"&gt;Constitution&lt;/a&gt; of the caster.\n&lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; may &lt;a href=\"Dreams%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;gain&lt;/a&gt; an &lt;a href=\"innate%20ability\"&gt;innate ability&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Draw%20Upon%20Holy%20Might%20%28ability%29\"&gt;of the same name&lt;/a&gt; during the \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" campaign.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this divine spell, revising its scaling cap, and which spells it can stack with and a new description. See below:\nDraw Upon Holy Might\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Evocation\nSphere: Combat\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 2\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, the priest\u2019s body shudders and glows with a shimmering aura as it becomes a vessel for the power of his god. When he does this, his strength, dexterity, and constitution scores are raised by 1 point for every 3 levels of the caster, to a maximum of 3 points at level 9. This spell is not cumulative with itself or with other similar spells."}
