{"id": "11053", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11053", "title": "Dread Wolf", "text": "A Dread Wolf is a in the .\nDread Wolves belong to the Race of and in the original games and the ' but classified as in the '. They are commonly encountered at cliffs and in the grasslands and plains of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt;, where they are generally thought to be the toughest of their kin, and should be avoided at the &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20One\"&gt;start of the journey&lt;/a&gt; \u2013 which, however, isn't always possible. At most times they are accompanied by weaker wolves, it only seldom happens that an entire group of Dread ones attacks together. In \"\" they only may spawn in one location, &lt;a href=\"Firkraag%27s%20Maze\"&gt;Firkraag's Maze&lt;/a&gt;, if a certain trap isn't &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Find%20/%20Disarm%20Traps\"&gt;disarmed&lt;/a&gt;. They can wake a resting &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Heretic%20Temple\"&gt;Heretic Temple&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThese undead monsters will charge the nearest detected opponents and seek to rend them with biting attacks.\nDread Wolves will attack detected &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; class opponents first.\nSee the infoBox for a breakdown of their immunities and protections."}
