{"id": "34043", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34043", "title": "Dreon's Signet Ring", "text": "Dreon's Signet Ring is the ring of &lt;a href=\"Commander%20Dreon\"&gt;Commander Dreon&lt;/a&gt;, who can be found in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Ten%20%E2%80%93%20Allied%20Siege%20Camp\"&gt;Chapter Ten&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle%20Exterior\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle Exterior&lt;/a&gt;. If &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; or another party member is wearing the &lt;a href=\"Crusader%20Uniform\"&gt;Crusader Uniform&lt;/a&gt; and they speak with Dreon, you can tell him that you have documents that need his signature. He will give you his ring, which is needed for the &lt;a href=\"On%20The%20Fence\"&gt;On The Fence&lt;/a&gt; quest."}
{"id": "2075", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2075", "title": "Dreppin", "text": "Dreppin is a male monk who can be found looking after his cow, Nessa, near the &lt;a href=\"Priests%27%20Quarters\"&gt;Priests' Quarters&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Prologue\"&gt;Prologue&lt;/a&gt;. When you first speak to him, he tells you where to find &lt;a href=\"Phlydia\"&gt;Phlydia's&lt;/a&gt; lost book, whether or not you have already picked up the quest &lt;a href=\"Phlydia%27s%20Book\"&gt;Phlydia's Book&lt;/a&gt; by speaking to her. \nHe has a quest of his own, which he will not tell you about until you speak to him a second time. The lesson here, if there be one, is that persistence sometimes pays off. \nHis \"plans for you\" never amount to anything more than having you find &lt;a href=\"Antidote\"&gt;medicine&lt;/a&gt; for his ailing cow. The lesson here, if there be one, is never trust an NPC.\nDuring &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Six\"&gt;Chapter Six&lt;/a&gt;, he'll still be found near the Priests' Quarters and he'll engage &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; in some brief small talk. If you choose the right dialogue line, he will provide some limited information about some recent visitors to the keep. He'll be found one more time on the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Catacombs%20Level%202\"&gt;second level&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Catacombs\"&gt;Candlekeep Catacombs&lt;/a&gt;, although this time he's really a doppelganger in disguise. After a brief dialogue, the doppelganger will transform and attack\nDialogue.\nPrologue.\n\"...OR...\"\nChapter Six - Candlekeep.\n\"&lt;Gorion's Ward&gt;! I didn't think you were ever coming back! What's it like out there?\""}
{"id": "2246", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2246", "title": "Dreppin's Cow", "text": "Dreppin's Cow, also known as Dreppin and Nessa the cow, is a &lt;a href=\"side%20quest\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Prologue\"&gt;Prologue&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\".\nWalkthrough.\nAfter &lt;a href=\"Phlydia%27s%20Book\"&gt;Phlydia's book&lt;/a&gt; was given back to &lt;a href=\"Phlydia\"&gt;her&lt;/a&gt; or simply by addressing him several times, &lt;a href=\"Dreppin\"&gt;Dreppin&lt;/a&gt; near &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"priests%27%20quarters\"&gt;priests' quarters&lt;/a&gt; tells that the &lt;a href=\"cow\"&gt;cow&lt;/a&gt; Nessa right beside him is \"sick 'n all\" and that he needs \"one of them potions of &lt;a href=\"antidote\"&gt;antidote&lt;/a&gt; off &lt;a href=\"Hull\"&gt;Hull&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nThe latter stands guard at the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;keep's&lt;/a&gt; main gate, south of the priests' quarters and past the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Oghma%20%28Candlekeep%29\"&gt;temple of Oghma&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Storehouse\"&gt;the storehouse&lt;/a&gt;. Hull has a &lt;a href=\"Hull%27s%20Sword\"&gt;request&lt;/a&gt; himself, but already knows about \"old Nessa\" needing an antidote. That one \u2013 together with &lt;a href=\"Hull%27s%20Long%20Sword\"&gt;his sword&lt;/a&gt;, the request \u2013 can be found \"in the chest at the foot of [his] bed on the right side of the &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep%20Barracks\"&gt;barracks&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nThe barracks are to the east, past the &lt;a href=\"bunkhouse\"&gt;bunkhouse&lt;/a&gt;. Fetching the &lt;a href=\"potion\"&gt;potion&lt;/a&gt; from Hull's chest and bringing it Dreppin yields &lt;a href=\"experience\"&gt;experience&lt;/a&gt; and some thoughts from him on the &lt;a href=\"iron%20crisis\"&gt;iron crisis&lt;/a&gt;, either noting that it's good they \"ain't wearin' none of that metal armor\" or warning to do so because of &lt;a href=\"bandit\"&gt;bandit&lt;/a&gt;s if the character talking with him is equipped with &lt;a href=\"Chain%20Mail\"&gt;chain&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"splint%20mail\"&gt;splint mail&lt;/a&gt;.\nUpon speaking again with Dreppin, he tells, however, that Nessa \"liked that potion of Hull's [and that] she's doin' better already.\""}
