{"id": "35327", "revid": "3234315", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35327", "title": "Drow Adamantine Chain +5", "text": "Drow Adamantine Chain +5 is +5 which bestows an &lt;a href=\"armor%20class\"&gt;armor class&lt;/a&gt; of 0 upon the wearer. Like &lt;a href=\"Drow%20Elven%20Chain\"&gt;Drow Elven Chain&lt;/a&gt;, this armor can be worn by &lt;a href=\"stealth\"&gt;stealth&lt;/a&gt;y characters, but with a penalty to their &lt;a href=\"thieving%20abilities\"&gt;thieving abilities&lt;/a&gt;, and it does not disable &lt;a href=\"spell\"&gt;spell&lt;/a&gt;casting;\u00a0unlike that one, however, it does \"not\" offer bonuses to &lt;a href=\"magic%20resistance\"&gt;magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; or the time it needs to cast a spell.\u00a0Like all &lt;a href=\"armor\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; made of adamantine, it will dissolve to &lt;a href=\"Adamantine%20Dust\"&gt;dust&lt;/a&gt; if exposed to sunlight.\nLocations.\n\"Shadows of Amn\".\n&lt;a href=\"Drow%20Priestess%20%28Underdark%29\"&gt;Drow Priestess (Underdark)&lt;/a&gt; wear this armor"}
{"id": "50351", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50351", "title": "Drow Ambush", "text": "Drow Ambush (Underdark) is a mostly unavoidable encounter that is spawned by a party member passing a certain hidden proximity trigger mark on the map in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. This script is called DWSPAWN1.BCS and in turn launches a Cutscene, as well as a script CUT44A.BCS. \nA group of five drow will teleport in near the causeway connecting the main Underdark with the northern Ust Natha (and Dark Cave) side area. A text will display during the Cutscene \"A drow war party teleports into the area, the stench of sinister magic pervading all\".\nOnce the cut scene ends the teleported drow war party will begin attacking.\nThis hostile Drow Patrol party is composed of five variously equipped drow warriors, and an armed priestess. \nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes changes to these creatures. SCS AI scripts are added where appropriate, and the drow priestess has revised spells memorized. Weapon proficiencies and skills are assigned or revised on all creatures. SCS random treasure is added to their inventory. Here is a synopsis of the changes made:"}
{"id": "51486", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51486", "title": "Drow Bartender", "text": "This bartender is the party's point of contact to order drinks and lodging at the Royal rate in the &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha%20Tavern\"&gt;Ust Natha Tavern&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nA variety of local ales, bitters, and mead ranging from to can be purchased and one can sleep it off in a luxurious Royal-rate room available for . \nThere are some Underdark and drow specific rumors that can be obtained if purchasing some beverages. \nThe more exotic and expensive, the greater chance of a quality piece of information. Keep in mind your booze limits or face the &lt;a href=\"Intoxicated\"&gt;Intoxicated&lt;/a&gt; effect. Or perhaps that is exactly the effect you desire? If so, drink up adventurer, and try not to embarrass yourself in the Lust chambers.\nStore content.\nNote that the Drow Bartender has an assigned .STO game file - however in the Enhanced Edition game, the store access dialogue options are disabled, meaning that this shop can't be accessed. Listed below is what the store offered.\nMod content.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod and the &lt;a href=\"Icewind%20Dale\"&gt;Icewind Dale&lt;/a&gt; component, some scrolls will be changed to IWD type.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod, spell scrolls will be changed to the SR versions if applicable.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//github.com/Sampsca/ThrownHammers\"&gt;Throwing Hammers&lt;/a&gt; mod, there will be some ordinary and enchanted throwing War Hammers for purchase."}
{"id": "51484", "revid": "49426621", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51484", "title": "Drow Beast Merchant", "text": "The Drow Beast Merchant (refered to as Drow in the game) is a male mage open for business selling various captured creatures for coin. His stock is limited at the moment, but it may provide an interesting purchase.\nIf any of the beasts are purchased, then for a limited time, the creatures will be under command and obey the party (behaving similar to a summoned creature).\nThe beasts will be able to travel anywhere on the main Ust Natha map but won't be able to transition through doors/gates into other maps (such as the Temple of Lolth or leave the city for the underdark). The party can enter another area, and the party's purchased beast(s) will remain on the Ust Natha map, wherever they were last positioned. The creatures cannot explore and remove the fog of war on their own. The creatures remain under the party control until a standard rest period is taken (such as staying at the tavern). After that, the creatures are hostile - but only to the party.\nStrategic use of these creatures could come in handy if planning on rampaging and fighting the drow city at the end of the &lt;a href=\"The%20Drow%20Summoning%20Ritual\"&gt;The Drow Summoning Ritual&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nSlaughtering the beasts in their cages is possible, and there is no reaction from the beast merchant if this done, even though they are property of the merchant, and one would think if that occurred, he'd be upset and demand compensation for destroying his stock. But nothing happens."}
{"id": "9366", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9366", "title": "Drow Bolt", "text": "Drow Bolts (Drow Bolt +1 in-game) are enchanted bolts +1, very similiar to normal &lt;a href=\"bolts%20%2B1\"&gt;bolts +1&lt;/a&gt;, except that this item turns into &lt;a href=\"Adamantine%20Dust\"&gt;adamantine dust&lt;/a&gt; when its removed from &lt;a href=\"The%20Underdark\"&gt;The Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. It deals 1d8+1 points of damage and it has a +1 bonus to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;. This item appears in and . It's dropped by &lt;a href=\"drow\"&gt;drow&lt;/a&gt; archers."}
