{"id": "50331", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50331", "title": "Drow Patrol", "text": "Drow Patrol (Underdark) is a mostly unavoidable encounter that is spawned by a party member passing a certain hidden proximity trigger mark on the map in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. This script is called HIGHLEVEL and in turn launches SPWNDROW.BCS.\nOnce triggered, the game looks at the experience points accrued by the Player Character and the game difficulty setting to determine what spawns will appear in the encounter. The higher the difficulty setting, the more spawned enemies. If the PC has 400,000 XP, or over 999,999 XP also changes the types of creatures in the spawned Drow Patrol. On the Highest game difficulty setting, \"Legacy of Bhaal\" or \"Insane\" with SCS, then the most challenging spawn will be initiated regardless of the PC's experience level.\nThis patrol will spawn near the Drow Soul Prison device (slightly south of it) in the Underdark caverns, and they will appear well out of sight of the party member who triggers the spawn. Note that a &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20Eye\"&gt;Wizard Eye&lt;/a&gt; will also trigger the Drow Patrol spawn.\nThis hostile Drow Patrol party is composed of various Drow Warriors, Drow Wizards and Drow Priestesses, with differing experience levels. equipment, spells and skills: The exact numbers and group composition varies. The following drow types can be found as part of the Drow Patrol:\nAn example of the Drow Patrol composition on Legacy of Bhaal game difficulty would be:\nThe game only uses these creatures once, and just for this particular encounter spawn.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes changes to these creatures. SCS AI scripts are added where appropriate, and spell casters have revised spells memorized including sequencers and or instant cast triggers to reflect the patrol group being prepared and self-buffed, depending on installed components. Weapon proficiencies and skills might be assigned or revised on some creatures. See the individual creature pages for more details."}
{"id": "9199", "revid": "48635260", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9199", "title": "Drow Piwafwi Cloak", "text": "Drow Piwafwi Cloak is an item that can be had in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%205\"&gt;chapter 5&lt;/a&gt; of and also .\nAnother cloak is available from an encounter within &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; as a looted item from defeating &lt;a href=\"Ameralis%20Zauviir\"&gt;Ameralis Zauviir&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nWhile pursuing &lt;a href=\"Inside%20the%20Drow%20City\"&gt;Inside the Drow City&lt;/a&gt; questline obtained in &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt; the party will probably need to obtain a Drow Piwafwi Cloak for &lt;a href=\"Phaere\"&gt;Phaere&lt;/a&gt;.\nA second cloak can be looted from a battle in Watcher's Keep.\nThe Piwafwi Cloak is infused with the adamantine element used by the drow. The cloak will turn into a &lt;a href=\"Adamantine%20Dust\"&gt;Adamantine Dust&lt;/a&gt; when exposed to the surface world's light.\nHowever, when worn underground or in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;, this cloak offers the wearer a -6 bonus vs. Breath attack saving throws and +75% bonus for Hide in Shadows and Move Silently skills."}
{"id": "50353", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50353", "title": "Drow Priestess (Underdark)", "text": "Drow Priestess (Underdark) is a &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; Cleric that are found throughout the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nThey are often grouped with &lt;a href=\"Drow%20Warrior%20%28Underdark%29\"&gt;Drow Warrior (Underdark)&lt;/a&gt; as a member of an ambush, war party or guards. If forced into melee combat, the Cleric will attack with their Drow Flail. This creature will cast a party friendly or self-defensive buff and then offensive/disabling spells in combat, if not disrupted.\nShe will open up with a instant self-buff spell group of &lt;a href=\"Defensive%20Harmony\"&gt;Defensive Harmony&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Righteous%20Magic\"&gt;Righteous Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Strength%20of%20One\"&gt;Strength of One&lt;/a&gt;. All allied drow nearby may benefit from two of those spells.\nAll of the scripted spells listed in the InfoBox are able to be cast during the battle, barring interruption. Several predetermined healing spells are set to cast when the Priestess is damaged to a predetermined threshold.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a few changes to this creature. Several new and varied extra spells are provided. A single pip in Flail/Morningstar weapon proficiency is provided, and one pip in sword and shield style. If the \"Smarter Priests\" component is installed there will be more aggressive self-buffing and better spell utilization on attack. A default SCS Priest script is assigned for tactical and defensive/healing behavior. An SCS random treasure is in the creature's inventory.\nWith SCS, she will open battle buffed with the following (previously cast) spells: &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spiritual%20Hammer\"&gt;Spiritual Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod is installed, the drow's memorized spells will be the SR versions. If so, then the Spiritual Hammer can strike at distance."}
{"id": "50345", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50345", "title": "Drow Priestess 04", "text": "Drow Priestess 04 is a &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; Cleric that can be included as part of the &lt;a href=\"Drow%20Patrol\"&gt;Drow Patrol&lt;/a&gt; encounter in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. If forced into melee combat, the Cleric will attack with their magical but unenchanted Drow Whip/Flail. The Priestess is clad in Adamantine Drow Elven Chain, which boosts magic resistance by +5%, Casting Time Modifier of +1 speed bonus, and has a +3 Enchantment rating as well. This creature will cast a party friendly or self-defensive buff and then offensive/disabling spells in combat, if not disrupted.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a few changes to this creature. No weapon proficiency is assigned, because it is a \"whip\", and not actually a flail or blunt weapon category. More spells and some different ones are memorized. A default SCS cleric AI script is installed for \"Smarter Cleric\" behavior. An SCS random treasure is in the creature's inventory as well.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; Mod is installed, the drow's memorized spells will be the SR versions."}
{"id": "43018", "revid": "25539483", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43018", "title": "Drow Runaways", "text": "The Drow Runaways is a side quest in that can be discovered in the central northern section of the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt;. It can be obtained by going through the winding path onto the northern side of the river, through the rooms containing &lt;a href=\"Gurgle%20and%20Floss\"&gt;Gurgle and Floss&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bellowgulp%20Bluefingers\"&gt;Bellowgulp Bluefingers&lt;/a&gt;, and then heading north-by-north-east up a small path through a large pair of doors.\nThe party will discover a confrontation between some &lt;a href=\"Crusade\"&gt;Crusade&lt;/a&gt;rs led by &lt;a href=\"Therli\"&gt;Therli&lt;/a&gt; and a group of &lt;a href=\"drow\"&gt;drow&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"drider\"&gt;drider&lt;/a&gt;s led by a female drow named &lt;a href=\"Shapur\"&gt;Shapur&lt;/a&gt;. Both sides will react to the party's presence, with Shapur threatening them and Therli begging for assistance. There is unique dialogue if the player's party contains &lt;a href=\"Viconia%20DeVir\"&gt;Viconia DeVir&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Baeloth%20Barrityl\"&gt;Baeloth Barrityl&lt;/a&gt; at this point. The party has two major options here; Attack or seek a peaceful resolution.\nAttack.\nThe party can attack either or both sides in the conflict.\nIn addition to minor loot from both sides' lesser fighters, &lt;a href=\"Shapur\"&gt;Shapur&lt;/a&gt; drops &lt;a href=\"Storm%20Pike\"&gt;Storm Pike&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Sling%20%2B1\"&gt;Sling +1&lt;/a&gt;, 20 &lt;a href=\"Bullet%20of%20Ice\"&gt;Bullets of Ice&lt;/a&gt;, and a set of &lt;a href=\"Bracers%20of%20Binding\"&gt;Bracers of Binding&lt;/a&gt;, whilst &lt;a href=\"Therli\"&gt;Therli&lt;/a&gt; drops a &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20the%20Gargoyle\"&gt;Cloak of the Gargoyle&lt;/a&gt;.\nDiplomacy.\nIf the party takes the peaceful option, Shapur will explain that her group are looking for a pair of teen drow who have fled their home in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;, and she demands that they retrieve them.\nThese teen drow, &lt;a href=\"Kaelet\"&gt;Kaelet&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Catanzaro\"&gt;Umar&lt;/a&gt;, can be found in the extreme south-west corner of the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20River\"&gt;Underground River&lt;/a&gt;, below the entrance to &lt;a href=\"Kanaglym\"&gt;Kanaglym&lt;/a&gt;. Upon meeting them, the party has several options:\nWhen returning to Shapur:\nRegardless of how the drow are moved on, &lt;a href=\"Therli\"&gt;Therli&lt;/a&gt; will thank the party for their help by giving them his &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20the%20Gargoyle\"&gt;Cloak of the Gargoyle&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5222", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5222", "title": "Drow Scimitar", "text": "Drow Scimitar (Drow Scimitar +3 in-game) is an enchanted +3 weapon. It inflicts 1d8+4 points of slashing damage and it has +3 THAC0 bonus. It has a weight of 3 lbs and it requires 10 strength to wield the weapon. This weapon, like any other adamantite item, will dissolve to &lt;a href=\"Adamantine%20Dust\"&gt;Adamantine Dust&lt;/a&gt; when exposed to sunlight outside of &lt;a href=\"The%20Underdark\"&gt;The Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. It is dropped by &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; warriors."}
