{"id": "45617", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45617", "title": "Drush", "text": "Drush is an &lt;a href=\"ogre%20mage\"&gt;ogre mage&lt;/a&gt; whom &lt;a href=\"Grae\"&gt;Grae&lt;/a&gt; sold &lt;a href=\"Dennis%27s%20Mother%27s%20Gong\"&gt;Dennis's Mother's Gong&lt;/a&gt; to. He asks for a &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Frost\"&gt;Wand of Frost&lt;/a&gt; in exchange of the gong. The party gains for exchanging the wand for the gong.\nGameplay.\nFind Drush in the &lt;a href=\"Ogre%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Ogre's Tower&lt;/a&gt; and then initiate conversation. The Ogre seems affable enough and is not threatening. When the subject of the gong comes up, he admits owning it and will trade for it. If the item he's looking for isn't currently possessed by the party, they could try and get one, and return. \nIf the party is inclined towards violence, the poor sod can be murdered for the gong, as well as several high-end random treasures. The murder option will nix the XP reward. Some of items these can also be purloined via pick pocketing.\nOnce the gong is in hand, continue on with the &lt;a href=\"Limited%20Wish%20Adventure\"&gt;Limited Wish Adventure&lt;/a&gt;."}
