{"id": "10852", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10852", "title": "Ducal Palace", "text": "The Ducal Palace, also known as the High Hall, is a palace in the district of &lt;a href=\"North%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;North Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. It is a place for feasts, court hearings, administrative business, council meetings, and where some of the grand dukes reside. The palace is heavily guarded by the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; and during special occasions they'll demand proof from everyone who enters that they have a right to do so.\nWalkthrough.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;Chapter Seven&lt;/a&gt;, after obtaining the &lt;a href=\"invitation\"&gt;invitation&lt;/a&gt; to the council meeting from &lt;a href=\"Slythe\"&gt;Slythe&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Krystin\"&gt;Krystin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; needs to go to the Ducal Palace and first show the invite to the Flaming Fist Guard &lt;a href=\"Bill\"&gt;Bill&lt;/a&gt; at the entrance, and then again to a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Mercenary%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29\"&gt;Flaming Fist Mercenary&lt;/a&gt; inside. Afterwards, the Ward will observe the coronation proceedings until eventually &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt; (who the dukes are preparing to crown 'Grand Duke') spots the Ward, whereby the six noblemen involved in the procession will transform into &lt;a href=\"doppelganger\"&gt;doppelganger&lt;/a&gt;s and attack &lt;a href=\"Liia%20Jannath\"&gt;Liia Jannath&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Belt\"&gt;Duke Belt&lt;/a&gt; and anyone else in their line of sight. Once the doppelgangers have been killed, Gorion's Ward will then call out Sarevok as a scoundrel, but the Ward must have Sarevok's &lt;a href=\"The_Diary_of_Sarevok\"&gt;diary&lt;/a&gt; or Sarevok's &lt;a href=\"Letter_from_Sarevok_to_Slythe\"&gt;letter to Slythe&lt;/a&gt; to prove that this is the truth, otherwise Duke Belt will immediately kill the Ward. When Belt accepts the Ward's proof of Sarevok's guilt, Sarevok will be transported out of the palace into the &lt;a href=\"Undercity\"&gt;Undercity&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=\"Winski%20Perorate\"&gt;Winski Perorate&lt;/a&gt; and Gorion's Ward must follow him to the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt; where the final showdown with the person who killed &lt;a href=\"Gorion\"&gt;Gorion&lt;/a&gt; takes place.\nGameplay.\nThe fight with the doppelgangers is considered the hardest fight in\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; for solo runs with Legacy of Bhaal difficulty since one has to kill the doppelgangers before Duke Belt dies. This is a challenge since the doppelgangers will concentrate on the dukes.\nIf an invisible mage casts &lt;a href=\"Invisibility\"&gt;Invisibility&lt;/a&gt; on both of the dukes before dialog starts, the doppelgangers can't see the dukes, so they forget the assassination mission. This makes the encounter easier.\nTreasure.\nThird Floor.\nLock difficulties vary between 50-80.\nBasement.\nYou're not supposed to be there, so the Flaming Fist guards will demand to know why you are there, and depending on your answer they might turn hostile."}
{"id": "52156", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52156", "title": "Ducal Palace (SoD)", "text": "The Ducal Palace, also known as the High Hall, is a palace in the district of &lt;a href=\"North%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;North Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. It is a place for feasts, court hearings, administrative business, council meetings, and where some of the grand dukes reside. The palace is heavily guarded and the gates are swarming with both &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt; and protesting &lt;a href=\"Refugee\"&gt;Refugee&lt;/a&gt;s ."}
