{"id": "13199", "revid": "33570924", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13199", "title": "Duergar", "text": "Duergar, also known as gray dwarves, are a subterranean race. They are close kin to the &lt;a href=\"dwarf\"&gt;dwarf&lt;/a&gt; Race, but live in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;. Their kinship to surface dwarves can be compared to that of the &lt;a href=\"drow\"&gt;drow&lt;/a&gt; to surface &lt;a href=\"elf\"&gt;elf&lt;/a&gt; folk.\nDuergar are not available as a selectable race in the original , but will be available as a subrace of dwarves to play in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20III\"&gt;Baldur's Gate III&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "54979", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54979", "title": "Duergar (North Forest)", "text": "Duergar is a male dwarf creature encountered during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"North%20Forest%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;North Forest (Shadows of Amn)&lt;/a&gt; area.\nGameplay.\nThis dwarf is part of an unknown mixed group of adventurers or perhaps mercenaries encountered in about the center of the area map. The whole group is hostile to any intruders that are detected.\nThe dwarf is under leveled, has no weapon proficiency and saving throws and THAC0 are odd - perhaps this Duergar is slave or servant. He only has 1 throwing axe. He also has the GPDOG script. Maybe he is a pet. \nThis creature is essentially no threat.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; fixed this creatures stats and file to be at least a level 8 fighter. Weapon proficiencies are redesignated to 4 pips in Axe and 2 in sword and shield fighting style. Saving throws are adjusted and Base THAC0 is now 13. Perhaps this fighter might be able to hit something now.\nA proper Battle Axe is now provided for melee combat.\nTwo potions are available for scripted use during the battle - for ability boosting/protection and one for healing."}
{"id": "51473", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51473", "title": "Duergar Slave", "text": "Duergar Slave is a dwarf sized male who will approach the party on the &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt; Entry platform, or also known as the Bazaar. \nGameplay.\nAfter rescuing &lt;a href=\"Phaere\"&gt;Phaere&lt;/a&gt; from the Illithid task is complete, the duergar slave will approach the Party and make verbal contact with a request for his master.\nVarious dialogue options are available with the slave. He'll try and answer any questions the party has about who his master is, and what it wants, and if the duergar is being harmed and other things. However, if you do not agree to speak with the master in the tank of water nearby you will be warned. In fact, he may say:\n\"\"Come close to him, and he will speak to your mind. It is the way of his kind. Please do not tarry. He will announce an alarm to the city if you keep him waiting.\"\nIf you ever say to the Slave \"The words come from your mouth, not his. You dare threaten me?! You are dead!\" or should you attack the duergar, then the slave will say:\n\"Then my master is sorry, but you are... oh my... you are no drow! The alarm is sounded! You are no drow!\"\"\nIn effect, not agreeing to go to the master will eventually lead to the City Alarm script being enabled. All potential quests are now impossible to get, Adalon's eggs are forever gone, and further dealings with the drow city inhabitants will treat you as enemies. You have failed to accomplish much of chapter 5 of the saga. The player can try and Reload from a saved game or press on and attempt to and find a way out of the under dark."}
{"id": "6301", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6301", "title": "Duke Belt", "text": "Duke Belt is one of the Grand Dukes of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; as well as a &lt;a href=\"neutral%20good\"&gt;neutral good&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=\"chaotic%20neutral\"&gt;chaotic neutral&lt;/a&gt; member of the Council of Four, along with &lt;a href=\"Entar%20Silvershield\"&gt;Entar Silvershield&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Liia%20Jannath\"&gt;Liia Jannath&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Eltan\"&gt;Eltan&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn the game &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, Duke Belt will be in the &lt;a href=\"Duchal%20Palace\"&gt;Duchal Palace&lt;/a&gt; introducing &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt; as one of the Grand Dukes of the city of Baldur's Gate. After being ambushed by greater doppelgangers, you can give the Duke Sarevok's &lt;a href=\"The%20Diary%20of%20Sarevok\"&gt;diary&lt;/a&gt; to prove Sarevok's guilt.\nFollowing a short battle with Sarevok, who flees to the &lt;a href=\"Undercity\"&gt;Undercity&lt;/a&gt; before he is seriously injured, Belt will transport the party to the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt; to track him down.\nIn the \"\" and in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Shadows of Amn&lt;/a&gt;\", he appears as the main tutor in the &lt;a href=\"tutorial\"&gt;tutorial&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4268", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4268", "title": "Duke Eltan", "text": "Duke Eltan is one of the four Grand Dukes of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28city%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and also the leader of the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist\"&gt;Flaming Fist&lt;/a&gt;. He is a close friend of &lt;a href=\"Scar\"&gt;Scar&lt;/a&gt;, the second-in-command of this mercenary organization.\nBiography.\nDuke Eltan is first encountered by the &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;PC&lt;/a&gt; during the events of &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Five\"&gt;Chapter Five&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Headquarters\"&gt;Flaming Fist Headquarters&lt;/a&gt;. He forces a task upon the party, killing them on the spot if they refuse: To break into the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; headquarters as spies, and see if they can find any proof of the Throne's involvement with the caravan raids. The party will learn that any incriminating evidence would be found on &lt;a href=\"Rieltar%20Anchev\"&gt;Rieltar Anchev&lt;/a&gt;, the Throne's leader in Baldur's Gate, currently in &lt;a href=\"Candlekeep\"&gt;Candlekeep&lt;/a&gt; for business. This prompts Eltan to send them on the trail of Rieltar, giving them a &lt;a href=\"History%20of%20the%20Nether%20Scrolls\"&gt;precious book&lt;/a&gt; which grants entry into the fortified library when given to the &lt;a href=\"Keeper%20of%20the%20Portal\"&gt;Keeper of the Portal&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn the player's temporary absence from the city during &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Six\"&gt;Chapter Six&lt;/a&gt;, Eltan is incapacitated through illness, and his right-hand man Scar is murdered. Eltan's illness is exacerbated, or possibly caused, by a slow poison administered by his personal healer &lt;a href=\"Rashad\"&gt;Rashad&lt;/a&gt; - who is in fact a doppelganger. Eltan's illness means that he is unable to command and thus unable to appoint his own lieutenant to replace Scar in the Flaming Fist: the job thus falls to &lt;a href=\"Angelo%20Dosan\"&gt;Angelo&lt;/a&gt;, a corrupt man in &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt;'s pay. This means that even after Rashad's exposure and death it is not safe for Eltan to remain at the Flaming Fist HQ, and thus he looks for sanctuary with another ally, the &lt;a href=\"Harbor%20Master\"&gt;Harbor Master&lt;/a&gt; of Baldur's Gate.\nHe'll also provide you with a &lt;a href=\"Message%20from%20Sarevok%20to%20Rashad%20the%20doppelganger\"&gt;letter&lt;/a&gt; that details &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok's&lt;/a&gt; plans to have the other two remaining dukes murdered."}
{"id": "4008", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4008", "title": "Duke Eltan's Body", "text": "Duke Eltan's Body is the body of &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Eltan\"&gt;Duke Eltan&lt;/a&gt;, commander of the Flaming Fist. Although he is still alive, he is too weak to move himself. The harbormaster is a good friend of his and will hide from &lt;a href=\"Sarevok\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt;. His body is needed in the main quest &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Eltan%27s%20Illness\"&gt;Duke Eltan's Illness&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "55758", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=55758", "title": "Duke Eltan's Illness", "text": "Duke Eltan's Illness is a main quest that can be started in chapter seven, by hearing from &lt;a href=\"Tamoko\"&gt;Tamoko&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Delthyr\"&gt;Delthyr&lt;/a&gt;, or other potential sources that &lt;a href=\"Duke%20Eltan\"&gt;Duke Eltan&lt;/a&gt; has suspiciously fallen ill amidst &lt;a href=\"Scar\"&gt;Scar's&lt;/a&gt; assassination. Delthyr suggests following Eltan's healer &lt;a href=\"Rashad\"&gt;Rashad&lt;/a&gt;, who reportedly leaves &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Headquarters\"&gt;Flaming Fist Headquarters&lt;/a&gt; every night, but this cannot actually be done as there are no scripts allowing him to spawn outside the building.\nHead directly into the Flaming Fist headquarters and kill anyone between the party and Duke Eltan. Alternatively, sneak in with a strong thief or someone strong and invisible. If you are hiding or invisible, you can avoid a fight with the enemy upstairs too. When you reach the second floor where Duke Eltan normally is, you find him and the man treating him, Rashad, who after a conversation turns out to be a greater doppelganger trying to kill the party. After he is killed, Duke Eltan will ask you to bring him to the &lt;a href=\"Harbor%20Master\"&gt;Harbor Master&lt;/a&gt;, who is good friend of Eltan and can hide him from the loyal followers of &lt;a href=\"Sarevok\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt; until he is recovered.\nNow it's a good time to open to lockpick all containers there and see what kind of valuables are hidden, which includes a &lt;a href=\"Medium%20Shield%20%2B1\"&gt;Medium Shield +1&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Splint%20Mail%20%2B1\"&gt;Splint Mail +1&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen Eltan is brought to the Harbor Master, the latter will hide him and promise to take care of him. The party gains as a reward 2500 experience points and has probably done something good for the future of the city."}
{"id": "50278", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50278", "title": "Dukeem's Guard", "text": "Dukeem's Guard is a human Fighter class warrior ostensibly hired by the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizards%20of%20Thay\"&gt;Red Wizards of Thay&lt;/a&gt; to provide security for the Wizard merchants and &lt;a href=\"Gul%20Dukeem\"&gt;Gul Dukeem&lt;/a&gt; in the shop area of the &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizard%20Enclave\"&gt;Red Wizard Enclave&lt;/a&gt; located in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;. Note that the Game Files for the two \"Dukeem Guards\" are actually listed just as \"Guard\", and the name given on this page to the Guards reflects the term used by the &lt;a href=\"Near%20Infinity\"&gt;Near Infinity&lt;/a&gt; browser/editor program, which is commonly used on this wiki.\nThe guards will become hostile if any theft is detected in the shop area (such as a failed shop lifting action), if any of the merchants are attacked, or if the guards themselves are attacked. The AI script for the guards provides a healing potion use if they are wounded. Other than that, they engage in standard melee attacks with their grandmastery and two-handed weapon style halberd skills, dishing out significant piercing/slashing damage which is unique to halberds. They attack 2.5 times per round."}
