{"id": "42339", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42339", "title": "Durlag's Tower (Third Floor)", "text": "The Third Floor contains no floor traps, but there are several trapped containers. And there are still numerous items you can collect.\nGhost.\nIf you go down the south passageway, you will eventually meet the ghost of &lt;a href=\"Daital\"&gt;Daital&lt;/a&gt; who will mistake you for Durlag. After some back and forth dialogue he will attack you. Killing him nets 3750 XP. During the battle, he will summon an &lt;a href=\"Invisible%20Stalker\"&gt;Invisible Stalker&lt;/a&gt; and cast &lt;a href=\"Chaos\"&gt;Chaos&lt;/a&gt;. This may be a tough battle.\nKirinhale and Riggilo.\nIn the eastern most room is &lt;a href=\"Riggilo\"&gt;Riggilo&lt;/a&gt;. He will talk to you upon sight. If you annoy him he will attack. If you have accepted &lt;a href=\"Kirinhale\"&gt;Kirinhale&lt;/a&gt;'s quest, take the &lt;a href=\"Lock%20of%20Hair%20from%20Kirinhale\"&gt;lock of hair&lt;/a&gt; she gave you and give it to Riggilo. Say it is to prevent a dagger in your backside and he will give you a potion in exchange. Go upstairs and give the potion to Kirinhale. If you talk to Riggilo after this he will attack.\nTreasure.\nSee &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28treasure%29\"&gt;Durlag's Tower (treasure)&lt;/a&gt;"}
