{"id": "46587", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46587", "title": "Belt of Minor Invulnerability", "text": "The Belt of Minor Invulnerability was plundered from a tomb by the adventuring party, the &lt;a href=\"Vagrant%20Blades\"&gt;Vagrant Blades&lt;/a&gt;. It contains the magic of the arcane spell &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffects.\nEquipped abilities:Each time the wearer is hit, there is a 5% chance of them receiving a temporary &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; that lasts for a number of rounds equal to the character's arcane spellcaster level, just like with the original spell. The duration for characters without any such levels is of only 7 rounds.\nCharge abilities:Minor Globe of Invulnerability once per day, cast at max level 20 (therefore, lasting 20 rounds). Unlike the version triggered by getting hit, this effect works the same no matter who's using the belt."}
