{"id": "8081", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8081", "title": "Berena Elkan", "text": "Berena Elkin is a human Fighter, with a berserker kit. He supports &lt;a href=\"Gromnir%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Gromnir Il-Khan&lt;/a&gt; as an ally, turning up at the outset of battle in &lt;a href=\"Gromnir%27s%20Hideout\"&gt;Gromnir's Hideout&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe warrior is strictly a melee fighter. He's got grandmastery in spears and 2 pips in two-handed fighting style. He wears a breastplate.\nAt a predetermined threshold the warrior will quaff healing potions to self-heal damage incurred.\nDespite having a berserker kit, the AI script never uses &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt;. \nMod content.\nWith the &lt;a href=\"Ascension\"&gt;Ascension&lt;/a&gt; mod some revisions are made to this rogue, mostly to enhance its powers and abilities.\nCombined with the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod, an excellent overhaul to the AI and Ascension scripts is made. Using both mods together will improve the challenge and ensure scripts and compatibility with the EE game are realized. \nThe modded content makes some big changes to this creature. It's now a female, and a Level 18 &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20Slayer\"&gt;Wizard Slayer&lt;/a&gt;. Dexterity is changed to 16 and Constitution to 18. Hit points are adjusted to 182. She has 18% innate magic resistance and is immune to &lt;a href=\"Kill%20target\"&gt;Kill target&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Power%20Word%2C%20Kill\"&gt;Power Word, Kill&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe wears &lt;a href=\"Full%20Plate%20Armor%20%2B1\"&gt;Full Plate Armor +1&lt;/a&gt; and uses a special spear +3 in combat that causes all combat protections and specific protections to be removed as an on-hit effect. It also causes a 90 second 25% &lt;a href=\"Miscast%20Magic\"&gt;Miscast Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect on each hit. Multiple hits stack. This can't be dispelled.\nAs a Wizard Slayer she also has other melee on-hit effects applied to the target. She adds an additional +50% miscast magic innately (SPCL123.spl). She now has 5 &lt;a href=\"Attacks%20per%20round\"&gt;Attacks per round&lt;/a&gt; with the spear, with an adjusted &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; of -5.\nThe warrior will use both of her &lt;a href=\"High-level%20class%20ability\"&gt;High-level class ability&lt;/a&gt; innates to include &lt;a href=\"Hardiness\"&gt;Hardiness&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Resist%20Magic\"&gt;Resist Magic&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "50275", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50275", "title": "Berenn", "text": "Fire Giant Cleric in Yaga-Shura's keep. \nLikes to cast Regeneration, followed by Summon Fire Elemental, Aerial Servant and then spams Hold on your party.\nHas near 100% Magic Resistance; it took four castings of Lower Resistance (at 25% a pop) before he stopped shrugging off my spells.\nRetreat to the doorway. He and his Giant companions can't follow you through, but the Fell Cats and elementals will. Keep him pinned down with your archer to make his spells fail until you can lower his MR enough to put a DOT like Insect Plague on him.\nAwarded 40500 exp upon death (normal difficulty, no mods)."}
{"id": "9088", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9088", "title": "Berinvar", "text": "Berinvar is a &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt; and a member of the &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harpers&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found in &lt;a href=\"Galvarey%20Estate\"&gt;Galvarey Estate&lt;/a&gt; (aka Harper Hold) in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Docks District&lt;/a&gt;.\nAfter being allowed into Harper Hold by &lt;a href=\"Rylock\"&gt;Rylock&lt;/a&gt;, once his task of killing &lt;a href=\"Prebek\"&gt;Prebek&lt;/a&gt; is completed, you can find Berinvar near the stairs to the second floor. Although Bernivar is somewhat standoffish, speak with this one, and get more insight towards the Harpers, Jon Irenicus, the Cowled Wizards and the Shadow Thieves."}
{"id": "6565", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6565", "title": "Bernard", "text": "Bernard is the innkeeper and shop keeper at the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Athkatla Slums&lt;/a&gt;. He will rent you rooms and also has a wide variety of goods available for purchase.\nGameplay.\nAside from his function as innkeeper and merchant, he's also well acquainted with &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Harpers\"&gt;Harpers&lt;/a&gt;. She is his primary contact in this region of the world and will consult him during various predicaments.\nIf a party member gets caught trying to steal from him, it results in hostilities. His store will be closed for good to the party. Plus, other problems will result inside the Copper Coronet.\nFood, drink and lodging.\nA variety of local ales ranging from 1- can be purchased and one can sleep it off in one of the Peasant or Merchant rooms available for up to . It is rumored Bernard knows a lot about the various goings on in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;.\nWares for sale and trade.\nWhen the player first enters the Copper Coronet, the shop listing is quite limited and has a standard markup. Bernard can present an improved store in which he forgoes his merchant markup and effectively sells to you at cost. This revolves around resolving the &lt;a href=\"Free%20Hendak%20and%20the%20slaves\"&gt;Free Hendak and the slaves&lt;/a&gt; quest in one of two ways:\nThe improved version of the store is listed here.\nShop versions.\nThe items exclusively available in the limited version are:\nThe items exclusively available in the improved version are:\nSince the store will use a different version of itself, items previously sold to it will become unavailable. Ironically, the &lt;a href=\"Scroll%20Case\"&gt;Scroll Case&lt;/a&gt; is only available in the normal version of the shop and not the improved, however there are many sales points for this container in the game (unlike the &lt;a href=\"Potion%20Case\"&gt;Potion Case&lt;/a&gt;).\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Assassinations\"&gt;Assassinations&lt;/a&gt; mod has content for Bernard."}
