{"id": "2549", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2549", "title": "Berrun Ghastkill", "text": "Berrun Ghastkill is the Mayor of &lt;a href=\"Nashkel\"&gt;Nashkel&lt;/a&gt;. He is concerned for its economy and the safety of its people. You can find him on the road through town at the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Helm%20%28Nashkel%29\"&gt;Temple of Helm&lt;/a&gt;. He gives you lots of information about the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt; and completing &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Two\"&gt;Chapter Two&lt;/a&gt;. He leaves permanently after completing the &lt;a href=\"Troubles%20in%20the%20Region\"&gt;Troubles in the Region&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nKilling him results in reputation loss.\nJournal.\nSpeaking with Berrun completes the &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Two%23Journal\"&gt;Speak to the Mayor of Nashkel&lt;/a&gt; task of the \"Important Events\" quest, and initiates the next task:\nSpeaking with Berrun also adds another entry to the \"Troubles in the Region\" quest. If you spent any time gathering rumors in &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt;, you probably by now have a rather lengthy collection of entries for this quest."}
{"id": "47479", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47479", "title": "Berserk", "text": "Berserk is a status effect that grants a +2 bonus to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and damage at the cost of the character losing control of themselves. Berserk comes in two flavors, one type is dormant until a fight breaks out, at which point both the bonuses and loss of control come into play until end of the fight. Another type is active constantly.\nWhen the Berserk effect is active, the affected character will typically attack whichever creature is closest to them, friend, foe or &lt;a href=\"innocent\"&gt;innocent&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "9807", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9807", "title": "Berserk (ability)", "text": "Berserk is &lt;a href=\"Minsc\"&gt;Minsc&lt;/a&gt;'s exclusive ability."}
{"id": "50243", "revid": "8506165", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50243", "title": "Berserk (effect)", "text": ""}
{"id": "44035", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44035", "title": "Berserk Warrior", "text": "The various horns of Valhalla can summon berserk warriors of various levels. They are equipped with a ring with worn &lt;a href=\"Berserk\"&gt;Berserk&lt;/a&gt; effect and as such will be berserk for the duration they are summoned. The other items they wear are versions that are not droppable, but in other ways identical to the normal items.\nThe Berserk state is unlike those of the Berserker or Barbarian class: it grants a bonus of -2 to THAC0 and +2 to damage, but no other effects (such as immunities or AC penalties) are applied. The creature may attack neutral creatures while in this state and as such should be summoned with care.\nAll use the same AI script, same items and are Human Fighters of chaotic good alignment, without a specialization kit. They have no proficiency in Axes, even though they are equipped with one and no points in the Sword and Shield proficiency.\nEffectively, they will do 1d8+3 at the THAC0 described in the infobox, as they will have a +3 THAC0 penalty from lack of proficiency compensated by -1 bonus from &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; and -2 bonus from Berserk.\nLevel 5.\nWhile it is using a shield and some armor, the creature is not aimed to serve as a tank, as its dexterity and natural AC are suboptimal.\nLevel 7.\nThe level 7 version has an improved attack rating using a lower THAC0 and number of attacks. His hitpoints are 20 more and saves slightly improved. But it still is not a good idea to use the creature defensively.\nLevel 9.\nThe level 9 version has less improvements upon his level 7 brother in arms. No improved attacks per round, but a slightly better THAC0 and saves nonetheless."}
{"id": "9150", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9150", "title": "Berserker", "text": "Berserkers are one of several class kits available to &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt;s in , and . This class kit has a special ability called &lt;a href=\"Enrage\"&gt;Enrage&lt;/a&gt; which can be used once per day for every four levels.\nDuring the 60 seconds they are under this effect, they are a lot more powerful than a normal &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt;, as it gives the berserker a +2 bonus to damage, a -2 bonus to armor class and THAC0, +15 hit points. They also have immunity to the &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;status effects&lt;/a&gt; of charm, confusion, fear, feeblemind, hold, imprisonment, maze, sleep and &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt; while being enraged.\nWhen the Enraged status expires, the berserker takes 15 damage, effectively losing the extra hit points given by the ability (should they have less than 16 hp, their hp is set to 1 and they fall unconscious.) They also become winded for 5 rounds, during which they receive a +2 penalty to armor class and THAC0\u00a0and -2 penalty to damage. Enrage cannot be used while winded.\nThe two disadvantages of this kit are that the berserker can only become proficient (i.e. assign one point of proficiency) in any ranged-only weapons, and that lawful alignments are not available.\u00a0 They can still benefit\u00a0from grand mastery in axes, hammers and daggers when using ranged variants of these.\nThis class kit makes for an excellent dual-class for &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s. Berserker rage is incredibly powerful in BG:EE due to the +15 hit points being a massive increase at low levels and the status immunities rendering most enemy mages ineffective.\nThe berserker-cleric combination will only lose the ability to invest more than one point into , while the mage loses it for all ranged-only weapons.\nCharacter abilities table.\nNote: For the information of this table, the human class was used, because humans don't have any bonuses to the primary abilities and act as a neutral. For all other races, these numbers are slightly different.\nAdvanced Weapon Specialization.\nAdvanced Weapon Specialization raises the number of points that can be invested into a specific proficiency from one point to five points. As a result, fighters may do more damage and hit more often with weapons from the specific proficiency. For more information on proficiency points, see &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20proficiency\"&gt;Weapon proficiency&lt;/a&gt;. Berserkers can only become proficient with bows, , and .\nHigh-level class abilities.\nHigh level class abilities are added the expansion . For all warrior classes and &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt;s, the pool of abilities consist of abilities which can be accesses from the special abilities menu which can be used during battle. These abilities are available to fighters when they nearing 3,000,000 xp. (exact lvl is not known).\nTable for experience, weapon proficiency points and hitpoints.\nFor more information, see &lt;a href=\"Experience%20tables\"&gt;Experience tables&lt;/a&gt;."}
