{"id": "20856", "revid": "52654204", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20856", "title": "Big World Setup", "text": "Big World Setup was an all-in-one mod manager for &lt;a href=\"Infinity%20Engine\"&gt;Infinity Engine&lt;/a&gt; games.\nAdvisory.\nPlayers interested in the EE Mod Tool should be aware that it relies on unauthorized versions of the mods it provides. While it may appear a more user-friendly option than &lt;a href=\"Project%20Infinity%20-%20Mod%20Manager\"&gt;Project Infinity&lt;/a&gt;, it is ultimately not recommended. Mod creators are unable to assist with troubleshooting because they cannot guarantee the quality of the versions provided by this mod tool. For further reading on the problems that the EE Mod Tool can cause (and, indeed, has), please see &lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.gibberlings3.net/forums/topic/31275-roxannes-inofficial-mod-versions/\"&gt;this link&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4783", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4783", "title": "Bigby's Clenched Fist", "text": "A wizard casts the Bigby's Clenched Fist spell to smash, squeeze, and constrict a target creature for up to four rounds.\nGameplay.\nThe wizard directs this spell at a single target creature, the spell's range is 35 feet.\nWhen the spell begins its effects on the target creature, a unique 3D graphics effect renders over the creature's sprite.\nThe targeted creature is immediately affected by several effects that occur each consecutive round - despite the spell description talking about four rounds, it's really only three rounds in duration.\nOn the first round, the target is affected as follows:\nOn the second round, the target gets to try and make a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Paralysis with a -2 penalty. If the save is made, the victim is free of the spell, and for all intents and purposes, the spell's effects are finished, and the victim may move as normal.\nIf the target misses the saving throw, then an additional 4d6 crushing damage is dealt, and the target remains held for another round.\nOn the third round, the target tries another Saving Throw, this time with no penalty. If the save is made, the victim is free of the spell.\nIf the target misses the save, then an additional 6d6 crushing damage is dealt, and the target remains held until the spell expires.\nThe term \"Held\" used in the spell description is actually a form of being made Unconscious - and this spell also includes a quirk in that it disables immunity to that &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt; for the duration of the spell - while knocked out, additional damage will not wake the victim.\nThis spell can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Evocation&lt;/a&gt;, or with a spell protection such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt; and other similar &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 8 blocking protections.\nThis spell can also be removed with various &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects.\n&lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; will function against the crushing damage.\nOtherwise, the targeted creature will experience the damage and disabling effects of this spell potentially each round, for three rounds, and then the spell finishes up and expires.\nTrivia.\nThis spell is one of five of the \"Bigby's Hand\" spells introduced in the Advanced Dungeons and Dragons game. The archmage Bigby devised level 5 through 9 spells including; &lt;a href=\"https%3A//adnd2e.fandom.com/wiki/Bigby%2527s_Interposing_Hand_%28Wizard_Spell%29\"&gt;Bigby's Interposing Hand&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"https%3A//adnd2e.fandom.com/wiki/Bigby%2527s_Forceful_Hand_%28Wizard_Spell%29\"&gt;Bigby's Forceful Hand Hand&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"https%3A//adnd2e.fandom.com/wiki/Bigby%2527s_Grasping_Hand_%28Wizard_Spell%29\"&gt;Bigby's Grasping Hand&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"https%3A//adnd2e.fandom.com/wiki/Bigby%2527s_Clenched_Fist_%28Wizard_Spell%29\"&gt;Bigby's Clenched Fist&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"https%3A//adnd2e.fandom.com/wiki/Bigby%2527s_Crushing_Hand_%28Wizard_Spell%29\"&gt;Bigby's Crushing Hand&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod Content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced Bigby's Clenched Fist arcane spell, with the spell described below:\nBigby\u2019s Icy Grasp\nLevel: 8\nSchool: Evocation\nRange: Long\nDuration: 8 rounds\nCasting Time: 8\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: Special\nThis spell causes a huge, disembodied hand to crush the target and pin it to the ground. Each round the massive hand smashes the target for 2d8 cold damage and holds it for 1 round unless a successful save vs. breath is made at a -2 penalty. After the 8th round, the spell is finished."}
{"id": "4784", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4784", "title": "Bigby's Crushing Hand", "text": "A wizard casts a Bigby's Crushing Hand spell to crush then pin to the ground a target creature for up to three rounds.\nGameplay.\nThe wizard directs this spell at a single target creature, the spell's range is 35 feet.\nWhen the spell begins its effects on the target creature, a unique 3D graphics effect renders over the creature's sprite.\nOn the first round of the spell's duration:\nIf the target makes the saving throw, then for all intents and purposes, the spell is finished, and the victim may move again as normal.\nHowever, if the saving throw is missed then:\nOn the second round of the spell's duration:\nIf the second saving throw is made, the spell is finished.\nOn the third round of the spell's duration:\nThis spell blocks immunity to the Unconsciousness &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt; by disabling the &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt; that provides immunity - this means that every creature and player character in the game can be pinned by this spell, regardless of innate immunity to the Unconscious effect.\nThis spell can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Immunity\"&gt;Spell Immunity: Evocation&lt;/a&gt;, or with a spell protection such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Turning\"&gt;Spell Turning&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt; and other similar &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; 8 blocking protections.\nThis spell can also be removed with various &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effects.\n&lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; will function against the crushing damage.\nOtherwise, the targeted creature will experience the potential damage and disabling effects of this spell until it expires.\nIf made unconscious, the target will be &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt; and not awaken from taking further damage.\nTrivia.\nThis spell is one of five of the \"Bigby's Hand\" spells introduced in the Advanced Dungeons and Dragons game. The archmage Bigby devised level 5 through 9 spells including; &lt;a href=\"https%3A//adnd2e.fandom.com/wiki/Bigby%2527s_Interposing_Hand_%28Wizard_Spell%29\"&gt;Bigby's Interposing Hand&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"https%3A//adnd2e.fandom.com/wiki/Bigby%2527s_Forceful_Hand_%28Wizard_Spell%29\"&gt;Bigby's Forceful Hand&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"https%3A//adnd2e.fandom.com/wiki/Bigby%2527s_Grasping_Hand_%28Wizard_Spell%29\"&gt;Bigby's Grasping Hand&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"https%3A//adnd2e.fandom.com/wiki/Bigby%2527s_Clenched_Fist_%28Wizard_Spell%29\"&gt;Bigby's Clenched Fist&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"https%3A//adnd2e.fandom.com/wiki/Bigby%2527s_Crushing_Hand_%28Wizard_Spell%29\"&gt;Bigby's Crushing Hand&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell - revising its casting time, duration, effects, and description. See below:\nBigby\u2019s Crushing Hand\nLevel: 9\nSchool: Evocation\nRange: Long\nDuration: 1 turn\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 1 creature\nSaving Throw: Special\nThis spell causes a huge, disembodied hand to crush the target and pin it to the ground. Each round the massive hand smashes the target for 2d10 crushing damage and stuns it for 1 round unless a successful save vs. paralyzation is made at a -4 penalty. After the 10th round, the spell is finished."}
