{"id": "6971", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6971", "title": "Billy", "text": "Billy is a &lt;a href=\"bandit\"&gt;bandit&lt;/a&gt; in the \"&lt;a href=\"Lonely%20Peaks\"&gt;Lonely Peaks&lt;/a&gt;\", the area north of Nashkel's carnival. He is part of &lt;a href=\"Ioin%20Gallchobhair\"&gt;Ioin Gallchobhair&lt;/a&gt;'s gang, along with &lt;a href=\"Dribben\"&gt;Dribben&lt;/a&gt;. They demand a \"toll\" from &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party for passing through the area. Although it is not phrased as a \"your money or your life\" threat, that is what it amounts to.\nBilly has 5 &lt;a href=\"Arrow%20%2B1\"&gt;Arrows +1&lt;/a&gt; which he will use first in battle, unless you engage him in melee quickly. The amount of these he drops, as well as for his 40 regular &lt;a href=\"arrow\"&gt;arrow&lt;/a&gt;s, depends on how many shots he's able to launch at you before engaging him in close combat."}
{"id": "50126", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50126", "title": "Bilquis", "text": "Bilquis is one of four human Hakima seen in the first chamber of the &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20the%20Unproved\"&gt;Tomb of the Unproved&lt;/a&gt;. These ghostly appearing figures may be spoken to. Otherwise, they stand impassively on small platforms and coldly stare at your party. Bilquis is part of Hexxat's second quest, to obtain the &lt;a href=\"Shroud%20of%20the%20Unproved\"&gt;Shroud of the Unproved&lt;/a&gt; for her master \"L\". \nGame Play.\nEach Hakima has some dialogue, which will be available if you speak with any of the four. \nIf through specific dialogue or by attacking the Hakima and initiating hostilities, this Fighter will attempt to engage the party with Shortbow and enchanted arrow fire. This Fighter may initiate her \"Called Shot\" Archer ability. If engaged in melee, the creature may swap to an enchanted spear, or continue to attempt arrow fire at close range. This Hakima is innately protected from charm effects, poisoning effects, petrification and backstabbing. She can also see invisible creatures and is under a normal haste effect. Although the Hakima appear to be some kind of spirit, they have no undead immunities, and are actually just human creatures. There is a \"blur\"\" effect applied to them for graphic purposes. \nBilquis won't move from her spot and will prefer to fire enchanted arrows at any in range."}
{"id": "2223", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2223", "title": "Binkos", "text": "Binkos is a messenger for the Grand Dukes in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen we meet him standing close to where the road exits the eastern side of the &lt;a href=\"Lion%27s%20Way\"&gt;Lion's Way&lt;/a&gt; area (&lt;a href=\"coordinates\"&gt;coordinates&lt;/a&gt; 4505, 1785), he explains that he is on his way to the Grand Dukes to inform them of yet another caravan raid northeast of &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt;.\nHis haste may be due to the fact that the &lt;a href=\"Entar%27s%20Son\"&gt;son&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Entar%20Silvershield\"&gt;Entar Silvershield&lt;/a&gt; was among those who were killed in the raid."}
{"id": "15005", "revid": "3539497", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15005", "title": "BioWare", "text": "BioWare is the game studio that created the \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;\" series in cooperation with &lt;a href=\"Black%20Isle\"&gt;Black Isle&lt;/a&gt;. The studio is located in Edmonton/ Canada and was founded in February 1995 by Ray Muzyka, Greg Zeschuk and Augustine Yip.\nBeyond that, the studio created the &lt;a href=\"Infinity%20Engine\"&gt;Infinity Engine&lt;/a&gt; which would become the foundation for all games in the \"Baldur's Gate\" series, the &lt;a href=\"Icewind%20Dale\"&gt;Icewind Dale&lt;/a&gt; series and .\nAfter the release of \"\", the studio would go on to create \"Neverwinter Nights\", \"Knights of the old Republic\", \"Dragon Age\" and \"Mass Effect\", among others. Today BioWare are among the most well known game development studios in the world."}
