{"id": "16767", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16767", "title": "Biter", "text": "Biter is a that can be found in ' and later imported into '.\nAcquisition.\nIt is a reward for retrieving the heirlooms in the &lt;a href=\"Halfling%20Treasures\"&gt;Halfling Treasures&lt;/a&gt; quest line.\nThis item can be &lt;a href=\"Importing%23cite_note-5\"&gt;imported&lt;/a&gt; into . It is later found sold by &lt;a href=\"Jayes\"&gt;Jayes&lt;/a&gt;, the halfling fence of stolen goods - who's available and found only at nighttime for business in the eastern edge of &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;.\nEffects.\nThis weapon is an unlimited-use dart that automatically sets the user's attacks per round to 3.\nOn hit, the dart does an additional point of acid damage, and there's a 10% chance that the target will have their AC reduced by 1 for 1 turn. This penalty is cumulative with repeated hits and failed saving throws by the target."}
