{"id": "41861", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41861", "title": "Black Market Thief", "text": "This Black Market Thief is a not so conspicuous member of the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; who runs a shop where you can offload the items obtained when you were practicing your pick-pocket skill.\nBuy and Sell.\nShe sells at a fairly nice discount. \"Good business, my &lt;LADYLORD&gt;. I don't think I've seen you before... perhaps you might be interested in looking at some well-priced goods that have fallen into my hands?\"\nMod content.\nMods:.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; Mod provides a number of new and or revised content to the Shadow Thief Guildhall and characters. The Black Market Thief gets a major revised inventory of goods for sale, as well as a special category of Rogue centric enchanted and magical items. Having a thief in your party can allow access to these special wares without having to pay an extra fee (using Thieves Cant). Careful trying to steal from this one, she has much increased difficulty to do so, and failure will turn her and the entire guild hostile."}
{"id": "42652", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42652", "title": "Black Market Thief (Athkatla Slums)", "text": "This Black Market Thief is one of two in the game (the other is in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt;). He is a &lt;a href=\"halfling\"&gt;halfling&lt;/a&gt;, tucked away on the roof of the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;, and therefore, easy to miss. You'll have to \"get past\" a few hostile muggers to get to him the first time. Contrary to what his name suggests, he is not a fence, but happy to sell you his own skillfully obtained wares.\nHe's available in the evenings and through the night from 19:30 till 05:30.\nWhile his store is named \"Black Market Thief\", he doesn't actually fence stolen goods.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Rebalancing\"&gt;Rogue Rebalancing&lt;/a&gt; mod adds a few different Mod-only rogue-centric items to the shop inventory. The mod also makes this merchant a \"fence\", as that is basically what a black-market thief should be able to do."}
