{"id": "38527", "revid": "263652", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38527", "title": "Black lotus", "text": "Black lotus is a herbal poison, common for the ' &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt;. It's extracted from the &lt;a href=\"Plants\"&gt;plant&lt;/a&gt;'s petals. Consumed in low doses, it can be used as a psychedelic drug.\nInvolvement.\nDespite being mentioned by several characters throughout the , there's no way to obtain the substance as an &lt;a href=\"item\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; itself. The &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Throne\"&gt;Iron Throne&lt;/a&gt; dealt with the drug.\nA short scene involving black lotus happens at the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20City%20Gates\"&gt;Athkatla City Gates&lt;/a&gt;, where &lt;a href=\"Bandon\"&gt;Bandon&lt;/a&gt;'s wares are searched by a &lt;a href=\"soldier\"&gt;soldier&lt;/a&gt; who finds lotus petals of an \"almost\" black hue among the spices. He receives a bribe for letting Bandon go, then &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; can ask him about black lotus \u2013 without any result."}
{"id": "4560", "revid": "53053884", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4560", "title": "Blackblood", "text": "Blackblood is a unique Club +3 in \"\", which has the normal bonus of +3 to damage and THAC0, but also deals +3 acid damage every time it hits the target, which makes it an excellent weapon for &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;s to slay trolls. However - unlike a normal enchanted club - it has no bonus to speed factor, nor does it have the reduced weight of a typical +3.\nBlackblood is sold in &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt; by an &lt;a href=\"Merchant%20%28Trademeet%20Market%29\"&gt;unnamed merchant&lt;/a&gt; after &lt;a href=\"Dealing%20with%20the%20Trademeet%20genies\"&gt;the genie problem&lt;/a&gt; has been solved."}
