{"id": "15439", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15439", "title": "Blackmist", "text": "Blackmist is a +4 &lt;a href=\"Halberd\"&gt;halberd&lt;/a&gt; that, in , allows the wielder to cast an &lt;a href=\"Game%20Terminology%23A\"&gt;AoE&lt;/a&gt; version of &lt;a href=\"Blindness\"&gt;Blindness&lt;/a&gt; three times per day. In the , the spell is single target.\nLocation.\nThe item bestowed is Blackmist.\nGameplay.\nThe halberd functions normally as one would expect, inflicting &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;piercing&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"slashing%20damage\"&gt;slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; upon a successful hit. It strikes as a +4 enchanted weapon, including THAC0 and damage bonuses.\nWhile the weapon is equipped, the wielder can launch a special Blackmist-only blindness effect (it's not a spell nor an innate ability in the game files). The range is 10' and must be aimed at a single target. When the projectile lands on the target it applies a series of internal effect codes in a 5-foot radius on the target and any in the radius (friend or foe).\nMagic resistance can block the effects. The internal &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; of the blindness effect is 8, and thus certain spell level protections such as &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Trap\"&gt;Spell Trap&lt;/a&gt; can block the attack on the primary target (but not the other creatures in the AoE). Creatures within the AoE can attempt a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus spell to negate the effect.\nIf the &lt;a href=\"Blindness\"&gt;Blindness&lt;/a&gt; effect takes hold, it will last for 2 hours. In addition, if the saving throw is missed, the affected creature will display a coloring and lighting effect over their sprite, and the combat log will show the text \"blinded\". Sound effect also is audible when first blinding the creature (see Bugs, below) if applicable. \nThe effect can be dispelled. A Mirror or reflected Image won't prevent the projectile from striking the correct target.\nThree of these blindness attack \"charges\" can be attempted per day, and the item recharges after a normal adventurer resting period.\nBugs.\nAs of BG2EE 2.6, Blackmist plays two sounds when blinding a target, but one of those sounds is supposed to be an expiry sound when the blindness wears off. This is identified and corrected in &lt;a href=\"The%20Enhanced%20Edition%20Fixpack%20%28EEFP%29\"&gt;The Enhanced Edition Fixpack (EEFP)&lt;/a&gt;. Ref: (halb06.itm)"}
{"id": "15440", "revid": "430029", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15440", "title": "Blackmist +4", "text": ""}
{"id": "8655", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8655", "title": "Blackrazor", "text": "Blackrazor is an long sword +3 with some powerful enchantments for its level. It appears in ' and its ', as well as in \"\".\nAcquisition.\nBaldur's Gate II and the EE.\nBlackrazor can be acquired in the Test of Greed in &lt;a href=\"The%20Abyss\"&gt;The Abyss&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt; Part 2 from the &lt;a href=\"Greed%20%28Fiend%29\"&gt;Greed (Fiend)&lt;/a&gt;. \nHowever, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; must make a choice about what to do with this sword. Either give the sword to the &lt;a href=\"Enslaved%20Genie\"&gt;Enslaved Genie&lt;/a&gt; or to keep the sword and then kill the tormented being. Both choices will free the genie. One choice is the \"good\" path, the other the \"evil\" one. It's up to the player to decide how they'll respond to the test of greed.\nThe Black Pits II: Gladiators of Thay.\nAs a reward item after defeating the Demons and Devils in Tier 2 - Battle 5.\nGameplay.\nThis weapon inflicts 1d8 +3 points of &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;Slashing damage&lt;/a&gt; on a hit, has a -3 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus, a speed factor of 2 and a weight of 4 lbs. \nA\u00a0creature hit by it has a 15% chance to have 4 levels drained, healing the wielder for 20 points, hasting him and raising his &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt; by 3 points for 20 seconds. The strength increase is additive to any existing strength attribute the wielder already has up to the maximum permitted strength score of 25. \nThe wielder also regenerates 1 hit point every 5 seconds and has immunity to &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Creature\"&gt;Charm Creature&lt;/a&gt; type &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt;.\nNote.\nWhen a target creature is killed by the &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0effect, it also suffers a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Disintegrate%20effect\"&gt;Disintegrate effect&lt;/a&gt; which has a high probability to destroy some or all of the items it is carrying. Disabling \"gore\" in gameplay settings will alter the death type to a normal killing, rather than disintegrated. This will prevent items from being destroyed (tested in BG2EE v2.6.6).\nAn undroppable clone of this sword is wielded by the evil version of &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; in the 2nd Pocket Plane challenge \"possibilities\"."}
