{"id": "12886", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=12886", "title": "Blessed Bolt", "text": "Blessed Bolts are a type of crossbow ammunition in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt;\" and its \"\". Despite their description, the bolts are not actually imbued with the &lt;a href=\"Bless\"&gt;Bless&lt;/a&gt; spell, and thus don't give the user any bonuses to morale, saves, or attack rolls. They do, however, kill a &lt;a href=\"Rakshasa\"&gt;Rakshasa&lt;/a&gt; instantly on a successful hit, making these bolts quite useful against said creatures. Additionally, unlike regular bolts, they have a +1 modifier to damage and THAC0.\nThese bolts were from the game and are not available via normal means."}
