{"id": "4626", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4626", "title": "Blindness", "text": "Blindness temporarily reduces the visual range of the victim to only 1 foot.\nGameplay.\nThe wizard directs this spell at one single creature in range.\nUpon completion of the spell casting, a projectile speeds to the targeted creature, and exposes it to the spell's effects.\nThe target creature is allowed a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; versus Spell to negate the effect.\nIf the saving throw is missed, the target is afflicted with the &lt;a href=\"Blinded\"&gt;Blinded&lt;/a&gt; status effect, potentially lasting 2 hours (100 rounds).\nAt this time the victim will show a graphic lighting effect, and a color fade rendered over their sprite - and the combat log will display a text reading \"Blinded\".\nAdditionally, a sound effect is audibled when the saving throw is missed, and again when the spell expires.\nA player character affected by this spell will display an icon (No. 8) on their portrait, labelled \"Blind\".\nA creature made blind by the spell has their visual range reduced to 1 foot and is afflicted with a 4 point &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; penalty.\nVery few creatures are outright immune to blindness, making this spell potentially useful even into late ToB when combined with saving throw penalties such as &lt;a href=\"Greater%20Malison\"&gt;Greater Malison&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Doom\"&gt;Doom&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis spell can be blocked with &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, as well as all of the Spell protections such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Minor Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;.\nCasting Blindness upon a neutral creature will not make them hostile, whether they are blinded or not.\nTo remove or cure blindness, see the InfoBox.\nTrivia.\nThe &lt;a href=\"https%3A//adnd2e.fandom.com/wiki/Blindness_%28Wizard_Spell%29\"&gt;Advanced D&amp;D 2nd Edition - Blindness (Wizard Spell)&lt;/a&gt; allows only a &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect to remove this illusionary effect from a victim, as it isn't some sort of disease ailment that can be cured. The Blindness spell is a 2nd level Wizard's Spell in the 2E ruleset.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has replaced the \"Blindness\" spell with \"Obscuring Mist\". See below for description:\nObscuring Mist\nLevel: 1\nSchool: Conjuration\nRange: Long\nDuration: 6 rounds\nCasting Time: 5\nArea of Effect: 20\u2019 radius\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen this spell is cast, a misty bank of fog billows out from the designated point obscuring all sight. Everyone within the cloud suffer -2 penalty to attack rolls, and have their line of sight halved. Anyone, inside or outside the cloud, trying to attack a creature concealed by the fog with ranged weapons will do so with a -4 penalty to attack rolls. Creatures with blindsight, or that do not rely on sight can fight within the cloud without penalties.\nThe Spell Revision version of &lt;a href=\"True%20Sight\"&gt;True Sight&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"True%20Seeing\"&gt;True Seeing&lt;/a&gt; provides protection from the Blindness.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; provides most Dragons with immunity to Blindness, due to their superior senses."}
{"id": "46383", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46383", "title": "Blink Dog", "text": "Blink Dogs are a class of &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Dog\"&gt;Wild Dog&lt;/a&gt; summoned by &lt;a href=\"Jacil\"&gt;Jacil&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Merchants%27%20League%20Counting%20House\"&gt;Merchants' League Counting House&lt;/a&gt;. They are unique in that they can teleport towards their target enemy just like &lt;a href=\"Phase%20Spider\"&gt;Phase Spider&lt;/a&gt;s and that this is the only game and moment in which they occur."}
{"id": "51371", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51371", "title": "Blizzard Troll", "text": "Blizzard Troll are blue colored trolls of cold and ice found as allies of the evil Ice Elemental Prince &lt;a href=\"Cryonax\"&gt;Cryonax&lt;/a&gt;, encountered as part of the final battle with &lt;a href=\"Amelyssan\"&gt;Amelyssan&lt;/a&gt; in Chapter 10 in the Throne of Bhaal.\nWhen they are brought near to death (a minimum of 1 hit point) they fall unconscious to the ground. They can be killed permanently in that state, but only by &lt;a href=\"Acid%20damage\"&gt;acid&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; damage, and if not done quickly, they recover heath and consciousness.\nThe Blizzard Troll has very rapid regeneration ability at a rate of 6 HP/second. It's melee attack weapon slashes, and applies a damage as well as a potential &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt; drain effect. A &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Breath Attack with a -2 penalty can half the cold damage and negate the Stun and attribute drain."}
{"id": "50842", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50842", "title": "Bloated Spider", "text": "A Bloated Spider is a unique spider introduced with the of and is only found in the &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20the%20Unproved\"&gt;Tomb of the Unproved&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Hexxat%27s%20request\"&gt;Hexxat's request&lt;/a&gt; quest. \nCombat.\nUpon initiation of combat, the bloated spider will begin its 40 foot ranged attack by lobbing greenish-looking poison blasts every 1.5 rounds, at a speed of 3 with zero enchantment, towards the first party member in sight. It has no melee attack ability. This is partly a purposeful attribute since the spider will release five &lt;a href=\"Small%20Spider%20%28Bloated%29\"&gt;Small Spiders&lt;/a&gt; upon death, but only if it is within eyesight of a party member. \nIf the spider is engaged in melee combat, first it will try to run away so it can use its ranged attack. If this is not possible and it is killed (either by a melee hit or a ranged weapon hit), the small spiders will instantly appear and attack. They are &lt;a href=\"Haste\"&gt;hasted&lt;/a&gt; on their movement rate only so their attack damage is not super lethal as they possess no poison ability.\nKilling the bloated spider from beyond of its range of sight, using long range area effect items such as wands or potions or through the use of spells, will not lead to the small spiders being released."}
