{"id": "28953", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28953", "title": "Blood of a Silver Dragon", "text": "The Blood of a Silver Dragon can be obtained if you slay &lt;a href=\"Adalon\"&gt;Adalon&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Adalon%27s%20Lair\"&gt;Adalon's Lair&lt;/a&gt; in ' and '.\nGameplay.\nThe blood can't be pickpocketed from Adalon in the Enhanced Edition. The dragon's sprite is too large for the reach of a rogue's pickpocket, and the item is flagged as \"Can't steal\". \nIf the party delivers the vial of blood to &lt;a href=\"Fael\"&gt;Fael&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;, it can be used to upgrade the &lt;a href=\"Human%20Flesh\"&gt;Human Flesh&lt;/a&gt; armor to Human Flesh +5 armor. This armor is discussed further in the &lt;a href=\"Finish%20the%20leather%20armor%20begun%20by%20Rejiek%20Hidesman\"&gt;Finish the leather armor begun by Rejiek Hidesman&lt;/a&gt; quest line.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Adalon%27s%20Blood\"&gt;Adalon's Blood&lt;/a&gt; mod provides another way to obtain the blood of a silver dragon, rather than having to slay this magnificent creature of good. Note that the task the dragon requires in order to voluntarily furnish some of her blood provides more experience reward than slaying her. Plus, a potentially satisfying new adventure can be had."}
