{"id": "49871", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49871", "title": "Bloodied Tunic of Hayes", "text": "Description.\nThe Bloodied Tunic of Hayes can be found on &lt;a href=\"Hayes\"&gt;Hayes&lt;/a&gt; body if he is slain. Most likely Hayes has died by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; party. The Tunic has no value and isn't some sort of component to make a new magical item from. It is just a grisly souvenir that you can show Hayes wife, &lt;a href=\"Telana\"&gt;Telana&lt;/a&gt;. She will react somewhat poorly to this, and says she needs to think about this information. In fact, She doesn't need to know Hayes is dead, and letting her know does not resolve any kind of open quest. It is up to you to decide if she should be told or not. The cloak has no further use in the game."}
