{"id": "30115", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30115", "title": "Blue Globe", "text": "Colored globes are produced by interacting with the &lt;a href=\"Globe%20Machine\"&gt;Globe Machine&lt;/a&gt;, located on the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; dungeon level.\nSelect which globe color is desired in the dialogue box presented by the machine. The machine can produce red, blue, green and purple globes, and a limit of four of each color. \nWhen the button is pressed to select a globe, the dialogue box displays a text, reading:\nBlue globes - gameplay.\nAll four blue globes look identical, except three of them will have a numeric \"1\" displayed on them, indicating a use \"charge\". This means that particular globe is a consumable/usable item.\nAs there isn't any information about what the globes do, the party would need to experiment and see the results. This feature is avoided by the wiki filling in that information.\nEven so, it may prove difficult to remember which globe does what, especially later in the adventure when managing an inventory. It will be up to the player to come up with some kind of tracking method.\nBugs.\nIn the Enhanced edition, the fourth blue globe produced (GLOBBLU3) has no extended effects data present in the file, including any &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcodes&lt;/a&gt;. Thus, the globe has no abilities. "}
