{"id": "4635", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4635", "title": "Blur", "text": "A Blur spell causes the outline of the caster's form to waver and shift.\nGameplay.\nThis spell is applied to the caster only.\nOnce the spell is applied, the caster's sprite is rendered with a Blur overlay graphic effect, and the combat log displays a text reading \"Blur\".\nAdditionally, a sound effect audibles when the spell is first cast, and another when the spell's duration expires.\nThe spell bestows a 3 point &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; bonus, and all &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; modifiers are improved by 1 point.\nThis spell can be removed by any &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect, as well as certain divination attack spells/abilities such as &lt;a href=\"Detect%20Illusion\"&gt;Detect Illusion&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"True%20Sight\"&gt;True Sight&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs this spell is an illusionary protection type spell, it is not affected by a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell.\nIn the original , multiple instances of Blur could stack; this isn't the case in the \"Enhanced Editions\".\nContrary to the description, Blur does not impose a &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; penalty on enemies, but merely grants an &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt; bonus to the caster. While in most cases the end result is the same, it matters when the general AC cap is reached.\nThis spell caps at caster level 20, lasting up to 44 rounds.\nTrivia.\nThe Advanced Dungeons and Dragons 2nd Edition Wizard spell \"Blur\" behaves differently than BG the game's design. The D&amp;D version causes all missile and melee combat attacks against the caster to be made with -4 penalties on the first attempt and -2 penalties on all successive attacks, and +1 saving throw to direct \"magical attacks\".\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod has changed this arcane spell, revising its effects, duration, and description:\nBlur\nLevel: 2\nSchool: Illusion\nRange: Personal\nDuration: 5 turns\nCasting Time: 2\nArea of Effect: Caster\nSaving Throw: None\nA Blur spell causes the mage\u2019s form and spirit to become blurred, shifting and wavering. This distortion causes all melee and missile attacks against the caster to be made with -3 penalties, whereas all saves vs. spell are made by the caster with a +3 bonus. Multiple castings of this spell are not cumulative."}
{"id": "5482", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5482", "title": "Blushing Mermaid", "text": "The Blushing Mermaid is a tavern and inn located in the western portion of &lt;a href=\"Northeast%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Northeast Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. The inn is comprised of two floors and has the only above ground entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Undercellar\"&gt;Undercellar&lt;/a&gt;.\nLayout.\nThe ground floor contains a main room that serves as a place to drink and mingle. Several &lt;a href=\"commoner\"&gt;commoner&lt;/a&gt;s can be found either sitting at tables or meandering about the area. A &lt;a href=\"Serving%20Wench\"&gt;serving wench&lt;/a&gt; is also busy keeping the patrons well supplied with drinks. There is a large storage room with multiple lootable containers located on the opposite side of the room from the entrance. A bedroom is located behind what appears to be the the bar area for the inn.\nUpon entering the inn, an &lt;a href=\"ogre\"&gt;ogre&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Larze\"&gt;Larze&lt;/a&gt; will hail you and tell you that he must kill you. It is possible to persuade him that you are not the person he is looking for, in which case he will walk away to check a photo to see if it is actually you or not, and ask you to stay where you are while he checks. He will then leave and never return. However, it is possible that you can't persuade him you are not the target and then fighting will commence.\n&lt;a href=\"Bork\"&gt;Bork&lt;/a&gt; is the proprietor and can be found near the bar. The bedroom behind the bar is where the entrance to the Undercellar is located. A woman named &lt;a href=\"Vivienne\"&gt;Vivienne&lt;/a&gt; is also in the bedroom and will approach you upon sight and engage you in brief conversation then leave through the exit to the Undercellar.\nThe second floor serves as a gambling hall with various gaming tables as well as several circular tables for use by patrons scattered throughout the floor. &lt;a href=\"Gamesman\"&gt;Gamesmen&lt;/a&gt; and commoners are the only people to be found on this floor. A small room is located on the opposite side from the stairs.\nLoot.\nOn the ground floor there is a total of thirteen lootable containers of various types. Only the locked chest in the bedroom contains treasure which includes: 350 , a &lt;a href=\"Gold%20Ring\"&gt;Gold Ring&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"Dagger%20%2B1\"&gt;Dagger +1&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere are no lootable containers on the second floor.\nQuests.\nUpstairs on the second floor &lt;a href=\"Marek\"&gt;Marek&lt;/a&gt; can be found standing near the back of the room. Killing him will allow you to obtain the second half of the antidote (&lt;a href=\"Lothander\"&gt;Lothander&lt;/a&gt; has the other half) for the '&lt;a href=\"Marek%20and%20Lothander\"&gt;Marek and Lothander&lt;/a&gt;' side quest.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Scar%27s%20Death\"&gt;Scar's Death&lt;/a&gt; quest comes to a conclusion when you hear &lt;a href=\"Ivanne\"&gt;Ivanne&lt;/a&gt;'s tale of how he was killed.\nFor &lt;a href=\"The%20Sea%20Charts\"&gt;The Sea Charts&lt;/a&gt; quest, a side quest that takes place within &lt;a href=\"The%20Reclusive%20Scholar\"&gt;The Reclusive Scholar&lt;/a&gt; quest in , you will need to come here and get a jug of &lt;a href=\"De%27Tranion%27s%20Baalor%20Ale\"&gt;De'Tranion's Baalor Ale&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"De%27Tranion\"&gt;De'Tranion&lt;/a&gt; who can be found standing next the large rectangular table near the fire pit. Giving the jug to &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Tollar%20Kieres\"&gt;Captain Tollar Kieres&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Merchants%27%20League%20Counting%20House\"&gt;Merchants' League Counting House&lt;/a&gt; will allow you to obtain the &lt;a href=\"Sea%20Charts\"&gt;sea charts&lt;/a&gt; that are required for the journey to the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Isle of Balduran&lt;/a&gt;.\nReputation Trap.\nIf your Reputation is lower than 3 you will be attacked by a group of three &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Enforcer%20%28Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23FLAMPUN\"&gt;Flaming Fist Enforcers&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Scout\"&gt;Flaming Fist Scout&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Battle%20Wizard\"&gt;Flaming Fist Battle Wizard&lt;/a&gt; as soon as you enter the inn."}
{"id": "18122", "revid": "264723", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18122", "title": "Boareskyr Bridge", "text": "The Boareskyr Bridge is an in \"\".\nDescription.\nIn addition to their ongoing siege of &lt;a href=\"Bridgefort\"&gt;Bridgefort&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Shining%20Crusade\"&gt;Crusade&lt;/a&gt; also holds Boareskyr Bridge, one of the few paths to &lt;a href=\"Dragonspear%20Castle\"&gt;Dragonspear Castle&lt;/a&gt;, and have rigged it to explode. must find a way to enter Bridgefort, most easily done by using a magical circle in the eastern part of the area that can be activated by a wardstone obtained from the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple%20of%20Bhaal\"&gt;Ruined Temple of Bhaal&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Wyrms\"&gt;Forest of Wyrms&lt;/a&gt;.\nAreas.\nThe forest.\nEastward and north of the starting area is a treed area on the banks of a large river. To lies a hostile group of 8 &lt;a href=\"Hobgoblin%20Scout\"&gt;Hobgoblin Scout&lt;/a&gt;s and two &lt;a href=\"Hobgoblin%20Veteran\"&gt;Hobgoblin Veteran&lt;/a&gt;s.\nFurther up is a pack of 2 &lt;a href=\"BDGOB05.CRE\"&gt;Goblin Worg Rider&lt;/a&gt;s, 2 &lt;a href=\"BDWORG.CRE\"&gt;Worg&lt;/a&gt;s, 5 &lt;a href=\"BDGOB01.CRE\"&gt;Goblin Archer&lt;/a&gt;s, all lead by a &lt;a href=\"BDGOB06.CRE\"&gt;Goblin Raid Leader&lt;/a&gt;. \nBeside them is the magic circle that can be used to enter &lt;a href=\"%23Bridgefort\"&gt;Bridgefort&lt;/a&gt; and behind them is a group of 2 &lt;a href=\"Bombardier%20Beetle\"&gt;Bombardier Beetle&lt;/a&gt;s. just south of the &lt;a href=\"Goblin%20Cave\"&gt;Goblin Cave&lt;/a&gt;.\nCrusader Encampment.\nTo the west of the initial starting point is the Crusader encampment, guarding both the main entrance to Bridgefort and the bridge that bears the zone's name. The camp can be entered several ways.\nNear the center of the camp is Crusader Lieutentant &lt;a href=\"Kharm\"&gt;Kharm&lt;/a&gt;, uncle to &lt;a href=\"Keherrem\"&gt;Keherrem&lt;/a&gt; and the training officer for the camp's recruits. If the party possesses the &lt;a href=\"Wardstone%20%28Siege%20of%20Dragonspear%29\"&gt;wardstone&lt;/a&gt; to Bridgefort, they can \"volunteer\" to &lt;a href=\"Down%20with%20the%20Drawbridge\"&gt;bring down the drawbridge&lt;/a&gt;.\nTo the northwest is a guarded gate to the actual Boareskyr Bridge, which is barred to by the magic of the nearby mage, &lt;a href=\"Oloneiros\"&gt;Oloneiros&lt;/a&gt;. Despite muttering to himself about trying to find , he is slow to realize who he's speaking to, though the reveal is quite an \"achievement\". Also nearby is the Revered Priest of Caelar &lt;a href=\"Hormorn\"&gt;Hormorn&lt;/a&gt;, who is known to hold prayer sessions at night that draw in many of the camps notable figures.\nSouthwest of the bridge is the former &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizards%20of%20Thay\"&gt;Thayan Wizard&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Vichand\"&gt;Vichand&lt;/a&gt;, who is the current focus of &lt;a href=\"Edwin%20Odesseiron\"&gt;Edwin&lt;/a&gt;'s hate and to south of that is a the makeshift prison area. Here can be found a caged &lt;a href=\"Dorn%20Il-Khan\"&gt;Dorn Il-Khan&lt;/a&gt;, who can be released (gaining , and either immediately recruited to the party, or sent to the Flaming Fist camp. A nearby chest holds his starting gear or whatever he had at the end of \"Baldur's Gate\", if he was recruited in that game. Just south of there are two caged trolls, who demanded to be released.\nTo the northeast of the main camp is the drawbridge of Bridgefort, which is being assaulted by Crusader forces. Any of the party that enters the area between the barricades and bridge (a pointless action if the drawbridge is still up), will take random damage from the defenders attacks. Just out of bowshot from the walls, the camp commander &lt;a href=\"The%20Barghest\"&gt;The Barghest&lt;/a&gt; is overseeing the attack.\nBridgefort.\nThe only entrance to the fort that is available at first is the teleport circle in the forest to the east.\nThe bridge.\nOnce the bridge has been cleared of Crusaders, the party can exit to the northwest toward the &lt;a href=\"Coalition%20Camp\"&gt;Coalition Camp&lt;/a&gt;. Along the way is a strange &lt;a href=\"%23The%20old%20well\"&gt;old well&lt;/a&gt; that might bear investigating.\nThe old well.\nAcross the Boareskyr Bridge is an old well. Depending on what is put in, various effects may occur.\nCreatures.\nPeople.\nBridgefort.\nSee &lt;a href=\"Bridgefort\"&gt;Bridgefort&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5944", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5944", "title": "Bodhi", "text": "Bodhi is an &lt;a href=\"Elf\"&gt;elven&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; who was expelled from &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt;, which would lead to her becoming undead. At the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%201\"&gt;start of \"Shadows of Amn\"&lt;/a&gt;, she has formed &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Vampire%20Coven\"&gt;Bodhi's Vampire Coven&lt;/a&gt; to challenge and destroy the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;. She and her group of controlled vampires will also be able to assist her brother's machinations.\nBackstory.\nMuch of Bodhi's backstory prior to is left ambiguous. Once an elf living in Suldanesellar, she was a close confidante to &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt;, a powerful &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;spellcaster&lt;/a&gt; who refers to her as a \"sister\". She assisted him in his attempt to become a god and suffered the same punishment as him when the plan failed. Both Bodhi and Irenicus were stripped of their connection to the elven race and were cast out of the elven city. It is implied that the nature of the punishment significantly shortened Bodhi's lifespan, as she voluntarily turned into a vampire as means of survival.\nIn the beginning of Shadows of Amn Bodhi has settled in Athkatla, and formed a &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Vampire%20Coven\"&gt;Coven of vampires&lt;/a&gt; to eliminate her enemies. She is also inextricably involved in Irenicus' plot to drain the &lt;a href=\"Tree%20of%20Life\"&gt;Tree of Life&lt;/a&gt; and become immortal.\nQuests.\n&lt;a href=\"Meeting%20with%20Valen%27s%20mistress\"&gt;Meeting with Valen's mistress&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt; of Shadows of Amn, &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; must choose whether to side with Bodhi and her vampires or &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; and his Shadow Thieves and work for the chosen side during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt;. This is introduced to the party via &lt;a href=\"Valen\"&gt;Valen&lt;/a&gt;, who delivers a message to you for a requested meeting. The trigger for this event is looking for a quantity of gold saved up and in the party's purse. It should trigger if you have near 15,000 gold (the fee for passage to &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt;).\nBodhi plays an important role in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%204\"&gt;Chapter 4&lt;/a&gt; where she confronts Gorion's Ward in &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;. She also obtains a portion of &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Bhaalspawn\"&gt;divine soul&lt;/a&gt; as means to further her dream of immortality.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20final%20battle%20with%20Bodhi\"&gt;The final battle with Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; of Shadows of Amn, Gorion's Ward is confronted by Bodhi in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Athkatla Graveyard&lt;/a&gt; regardless of the choice made previously.\nFacing Bodhi in combat.\nDepending on the party's choices of either siding with the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; or Bodhi, will determine when the party will have to actually fight Bodhi.\nIn Chapter 3, if you have sided with the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; and are undertaking a task by &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; to disrupt and destroy Bodhi and vampires in the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Lower Tombs&lt;/a&gt;, then you will face Bodhi. This creature is a version that can't actually be destroyed and only damaged and forced to flee. However, this version can still seriously hurt, and level drain the party, and even kill. The battle with Bodhi will continue until she incurs enough hit point loss in order to reach the \"flee\" the battlefield point. \nIn Chapter 4, in &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;, the party will again meet Bodhi, and eventually have to face her in combat again, as the party navigates the various hurdles and impediments associated with that Dungeon. Bodhi will appear and will attack. The Protagonist will involuntarily change into the &lt;a href=\"Slayer%20Form\"&gt;Slayer Form&lt;/a&gt;, which will eventually drive Bodhi away again. She can't be killed in this chapter, and frankly, she won't kill the protagonist here either. \nIn Chapter 6, the final battle with Bodhi will occur back in her original lair in the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Lower Tombs&lt;/a&gt;. In this battle, she can be destroyed for good when she retreats to her coffin, and she is \"staked\" within.\nAbilities in combat.\nIn Chapters 3 and 4, the Bodhi creature files, and associated abilities are equivalent to an &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20%28Ancient%29\"&gt;Vampire (Ancient)&lt;/a&gt; creature - see that page for abilities and its immunities (with minor differences). The game has scripted these versions to put up a fight, then when a certain damage level is incurred or another trigger is reached, will flee the encounter. These versions of Bodhi are equipped with the &lt;a href=\"MINHP1.ITM\"&gt;MINHP1.ITM&lt;/a&gt; or a similar MINHP20 version, which blocks final death by any means. \nIn Chapter 6, the Bodhi version is the one reflected on this page's Info Box. It is the strongest version of Bodhi in the game, exceeding that of a &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20%28Ancient%29\"&gt;Ancient Vampire&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis version of Bhodi is still equipped with the &lt;a href=\"MINHP1.ITM\"&gt;MINHP1.ITM&lt;/a&gt;, making bodhi immune to being killed and able to transition to her coffin. In order to get rid of this, the party must \"weaken\" the Vampires in the lair, by using the &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Holy%20Water\"&gt;Elven Holy Water&lt;/a&gt; in the room where she is located (add it to one of the blood fonts).\nMod content.\nMods:.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Alternatives\"&gt;Alternatives&lt;/a&gt; mod allows changes to how the party can deal with the Shadow Thieves and Bodhi. Now there is no need to side with either faction in order to undertake a trip to Brynnlaw and search for &lt;a href=\"Imoen\"&gt;Imoen&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Spellhold\"&gt;Spellhold&lt;/a&gt;. The alternative choices presented mean the party can take down both the Shadow Thieves as well as Bodhi. \nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod offers two choices regarding what kind of Bodhi will appear in the game. These are:&lt;br&gt;\nImproved Bodhi&lt;br&gt;\nThis component is inspired by the Improved Bodhi in Westley Weimer's Tactics mod. To quote from the readme to that mod:&lt;br&gt;\n\"Sigh. Bodhi is worth 91K XP -- more than almost anything else in the game. And yet she is a mere brute-force melee fighter who doesn't even drink healing potions. We make her more intelligent ... and give her some impressive pseudo-magical powers associated with vampires of myth and legend. Bodhi gains dominion over bats, the cold, the ground and the grave.\"\nThe SCS version of Improved Bodhi is updated to use modern WeiDU coding (to help with compatibility-friendliness) and SCS AI scripting.&lt;br&gt;\nYou can fight Bodhi in chapters 3 and 6; in chapter 3 (again, following Tactics) she'll pull her punches.&lt;br&gt;\nThis component is sensitive to the difficulty setting:&lt;br&gt;\nBASIC: Bodhi is protected only by &lt;a href=\"Fledgling%20Vampire\"&gt;fledgling vampires&lt;/a&gt; and by a few other undead and uses few supernatural abilities.&lt;br&gt;\nIMPROVED: Bodhi uses her \"Buried Alive\" (slowing and weakening), Touch of Death (vampiric touch) and \"Call of the Mistress\" (control undead) supernatural powers; her allies include two full-strength &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;vampires&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;\nTACTICAL: Bodhi also uses her \"Cloud of Bats\" (similar to Insect Plague), \"Abyssal Darkness\" (blindness) and \"Sepulchral Sleep\" (unconsciousness). Her allies now include four &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20%28Elder%29\"&gt;adult vampires&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;\nHARDCORE: Bodhi also uses her \"Chill of the Grave\" (cold damage) supernatural power; she is served by two vampire mages.&lt;br&gt;\nINSANE: Bodhi's physical abilities and resistances are substantially enhanced (matching the original Tactics version); she gains a permanent \"Deathly Shroud\" (cold fire shield) and is immune to first and second level spells. Two &lt;a href=\"Vampire%20%28Ancient%29\"&gt;Ancient Vampires&lt;/a&gt; join her defenders.&lt;br&gt;\nImproved Vampires\" component: See the &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt; article page and the \"Mod content\" section for discussion. This component does affect Bodhi, but only if you don't install the \"Improved Bodhi\" component (in other words, if you want Bodhi to use her original-game abilities more effectively but don't want to give her the extra powers of that component, install Improved Vampires but not Improved Bodhi).&lt;br&gt;\nEven with just the Improved Vampires component installed, the SCS Chapter 3 and 6 Bodhi has the following revisions:&lt;br&gt;\nLevel 25/25 Fighter/Thief Class, HP: 228, STR 24, DEX 24, CON 20, Effective AC: -10, Adjusted THAC0: -9, APR: 4&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Physical%20damage\"&gt;Physical damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance: 25%&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Magical%20damage\"&gt;Magical damage&lt;/a&gt; resistance: 50% (such as &lt;a href=\"Sunray\"&gt;Sunray&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Bolt%20of%20Glory\"&gt;Bolt of Glory&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br&gt;\nSee Invisible Creatures by Script&lt;br&gt;\nImmune to &lt;a href=\"Turn%20Undead\"&gt;Turn Undead&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nImmune to &lt;a href=\"Slay\"&gt;Slay&lt;/a&gt; effect (example &lt;a href=\"Mace%20of%20Disruption\"&gt;Mace of Disruption&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Azuredge\"&gt;Azuredge&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br&gt;\nMovement Modifier +12&lt;br&gt;\nBackstab damage modifier X5 (if attacking from invisibility)&lt;br&gt;\nTwo melee attack choices: Level Drain (5 levels) and 'Blood Drain\" (3 Con) from victim and she gains +15 HP per hit. The second is when opponent is protected from &lt;a href=\"Level%20drain\"&gt;Level drain&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nShape change into Mist, Bat, or Wolf Form at will. All have different powers in that form&lt;br&gt;\n\"Cloud of Bats\" innate ability&lt;br&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"Domination%20%28Innate%29\"&gt;Vampire Domination&lt;/a&gt; attempted several times during each turn if not protected from &lt;a href=\"Charm%20Creature\"&gt;Charm Creature&lt;/a&gt; effects&lt;br&gt;\nInnately and instantly force-cast &lt;a href=\"Heal\"&gt;Heal&lt;/a&gt; upon self when only 10% HP remain&lt;br&gt; \nWith the Improved Bodhi component, she will use some specific powers when facing the party:&lt;br&gt;\nDuring Chapter 3 Encounter: Deathly Shroud, Sepulchral Sleep, Touch of Death, Shapeshift Bat. Note that the \"Deathly Shroud\" is like a &lt;a href=\"Fireshield%20%28Blue%29\"&gt;Fireshield (Blue)&lt;/a&gt;, but any hit on Bodhi reduces the attacker's saving throws temporarily. &lt;br&gt;\nDuring Chapter 6 Encounter: Cloud of Bats, Abyssal Darkness, Deathly Shroud, Sepulchral Sleep, Touch of Death, Shapeshift Bat, Buried Alive, Chill of the Grave."}
{"id": "44954", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44954", "title": "Bodhi's Black Heart", "text": "Bodhi's Heart is, as its name suggests, the heart of &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;, the cursed &lt;a href=\"elf\"&gt;elf&lt;/a&gt; outcast turned &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt;, cut from her chest after she has met her final death at the hands of &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; via a &lt;a href=\"Wooden%20Stake\"&gt;Wooden Stake&lt;/a&gt;. This item is needed in &lt;a href=\"The%20final%20battle%20with%20Bodhi\"&gt;The final battle with Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; quest to revive &lt;a href=\"Aerie\"&gt;Aerie&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Anomen\"&gt;Anomen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Viconia\"&gt;Viconia&lt;/a&gt; from death.\nAcquisition.\nBodhi's Heart is obtained automatically from Bodhi's coffin, located on the 2nd level of &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Lair\"&gt;Bodhi's Lair&lt;/a&gt; after she has been defeated and slain for good with the use of a &lt;a href=\"Wooden%20Stake\"&gt;Wooden Stake&lt;/a&gt;. It will not be of any use if the player has not engaged in a romance with &lt;a href=\"Aerie\"&gt;Aerie&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Anomen\"&gt;Anomen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Viconia\"&gt;Viconia&lt;/a&gt;, and thusly not triggered the kidnapping of said party member and their conversion into a vampire. Romances with &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;Companions&lt;/a&gt; added in \"does not\" result in them becoming vampires.\nInvolvement.\nBodhi's heart is required as part of a quest to remove the curse of vampirism from the party member &lt;a href=\"romance\"&gt;romance&lt;/a&gt;d by &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;. After slaying Bodhi and the \"vampirized\" party member, a trapped chest in a small room to the northwest of the chamber where Bodhi is confronted on in her &lt;a href=\"Bodhi%27s%20Lair\"&gt;lair&lt;/a&gt; will be discovered several books on vampirism, annotated with a comment by Bodhi that she needs to confront the monks at the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Oghma\"&gt;Temple of Oghma&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Docks\"&gt;Athkatla Docks&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the player visits the Temple of Oghma and speaks with either the &lt;a href=\"Priest%20of%20Oghma%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;priest&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Monk%20%28Oghma%29\"&gt;monk&lt;/a&gt; with the books, the heart, and the body of their lover in their inventory, they will be directed to a book trader in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Inn\"&gt;Imnesvale Inn&lt;/a&gt;. With dialogue he will reveal an ancient ritual calling upon &lt;a href=\"Amaunator\"&gt;Amaunator&lt;/a&gt; that allows one to cure vampirism. Both the afflicted corpse and the Heart of the vampire that caused the affliction are needed in the ritual.\nThe player must travel to the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20Ruins\"&gt;Temple Ruins&lt;/a&gt; of Amaunator that also lie in the greater &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; region and enter the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Ruined Temple&lt;/a&gt; itself, seeking out the statue of Amaunator within, which can be distinguished by the way it holds it arms out as if to cradle something.\nOnce the player has placed Bodhi's heart and the body of their slain lover within the statue's arms, the ritual will begin automatically, and the party member will be restored fully and returned to life, free of the vampiric affliction. Much dialogue will follow from the romanced party member."}
