{"id": "35872", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35872", "title": "Bodhi's Lair", "text": "Bodhi's Lair is the underground den of the vampire &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;. It is accessible from her &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;hideout&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Graveyard District&lt;/a&gt;. While part of the Lower Tombs below the Graveyard District is accessible beginning in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%202\"&gt;Chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;, this area isn't accessible until &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt;. At the end of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; the party must enter it again in order to confront and slay Bodhi.\nPlot.\nChapter 3.\nIf you sided with &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; in the war between the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt;s, access to the area is gained when Aran requests that the party go to Lower Tombs and eliminated the vampire menace. The vampire &lt;a href=\"Lassal\"&gt;Lassal&lt;/a&gt; will entice the party to follow him down here where they must battle several different types of enemies (see enemies below) only to have Lassal head back up into the room of blood and blades for the final showdown with him.\nChapter 6.\nWhen the player emerges from the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt; and begins Chapter 6, the &lt;a href=\"elf\"&gt;elf&lt;/a&gt; leader &lt;a href=\"Elhan\"&gt;Elhan&lt;/a&gt; sets the player with the mission to &lt;a href=\"Retrieve%20the%20Rhynn%20Lanthorn\"&gt;Retrieve the Rhynn Lanthorn&lt;/a&gt;, which requires that they enter Bodhi's lair and slay the vampiric sister of &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt;. Only by achieving this goal can the party begin &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%207\"&gt;Chapter 7&lt;/a&gt; and confront the mad archmage in the besieged city of &lt;a href=\"Suldanessellar\"&gt;Suldanessellar&lt;/a&gt;.\nCreatures.\nNPC's.\n\"Chapter 3\"&lt;br&gt;\n\"Chapter 6\"&lt;br&gt;\nEnemies.\n\"Chapter 3\"\n\"Chapter 6\"\nTreasure.\n\"Chapter 3\"\n\"Chapter 6\""}
{"id": "50738", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50738", "title": "Bodhi's Vampire Coven", "text": "Bodhi's Vampire Coven is an unnamed dictatorial organization that has been formed by &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; and is being controlled by her in order to confront the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt; as well as further Bodhi's plans to assist her brother &lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt;. This group is encountered during the \"\" campaign only. "}
{"id": "51311", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51311", "title": "Boiling Rain Storm", "text": "Boiling Rain Storm is an innate ability effect available to most &lt;a href=\"Steam%20Mephit\"&gt;Steam Mephit&lt;/a&gt; creatures in the game saga.\nEffects.\nThe spell effect is uninterruptable and takes almost no time to deploy. A projectile is launched at a single target in range, but it has an area of effect that can also apply the detrimental boiling rain to any enemies in that radius. A &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Breath will negate.\nIf the target fails the saving throw the affected creature will be &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stunned&lt;/a&gt;, display a \"Stun\" icon on their portrait, and be &lt;a href=\"Helpless\"&gt;Helpless&lt;/a&gt; for 1 round. Additionally, the victim will also suffer damage. As the boiling rain has the equivalent of 2 spell power, a spell protection such as &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt; or similar will stop it, as well as &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;."}
