{"id": "2812", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2812", "title": "Bolt", "text": "A Bolt is ammunition for the . \nGameplay.\nThey deal 1d8 points of &lt;a href=\"Missile%20damage\"&gt;Missile damage&lt;/a&gt; and they have a theoretical projectile range of 100'. \nBecause the &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"cavalier\"&gt;cavalier&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0can't use crossbows, they can't equip bolts, either. \nBolts are sold at almost all weapon stores for per 20 in Baldur's Gate or for 40 in Baldur's Gate II. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, and ."}
{"id": "4889", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4889", "title": "Bolt +1", "text": "Bolts +1 are &lt;a href=\"Magical%20item\"&gt;magical&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Enchanted%20item\"&gt;enchanted&lt;/a&gt; crossbow projectiles that have a -1 &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; bonus when compared to normal &lt;a href=\"bolt\"&gt;bolt&lt;/a&gt;s. In Baldur's Gate 1, they also have a +1 damage bonus, but this is removed in Baldur's Gate 2. These bolts will harm creatures immune to normal weapons, provided they are not further protected from magical weapons."}
{"id": "4886", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4886", "title": "Bolt +2", "text": "A Bolt +2 is an enchanted bolt with a +2 bonus to &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; in all games. In Baldur's Gate 1, this bolt also has a +2 bonus to damage, which is removed in the second game. The item value is also 5 points lower in BG2."}
