{"id": "4134", "revid": "50866439", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4134", "title": "Bolt of Biting", "text": "Bolts of Biting are bolts designed with a barbed tip coated in poison. They deal 1d8 points of &lt;a href=\"Piercing%20damage\"&gt;Piercing damage&lt;/a&gt;, and if the target fails a &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;save&lt;/a&gt; vs Death, they also apply a &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison effect&lt;/a&gt; which inflicts 2 points of &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage\"&gt;Poison damage&lt;/a&gt; per second for 15 seconds. Although offering no bonus to THAC0, damage, or speed, they can bypass &lt;a href=\"IMMUNE1.ITM\"&gt;non-magic weapon&lt;/a&gt; immunity some creatures have. \nThe effect is cumulative, so for example if 3 bolts manage to poison the same creature successfully, 3 poison effects will be running concurrently.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Enhanced%20Edition\"&gt;Enhanced Edition&lt;/a&gt;s, the bolts will not try to apply the Poison effect to &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt;, and creatures with at least 100% .\nGameplay.\nThese bolts are very useful for interrupting enemy spellcasters, especially bards and mages (due to their poor death saving throws)."}
