{"id": "13072", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13072", "title": "Bolt of Polymorphing", "text": "Bolts of Polymorphing are rare, expensive, and occasionally dropped as treasure (in single units). The bolt is available in the first opus of Baldur's Gate. \nThey can be found as random treasure. More details linked &lt;a href=\"Random%20treasure%23RNDMAG01BG1\"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe bolt strikes for standard 1d8 &lt;a href=\"Missile%20damage\"&gt;Missile damage&lt;/a&gt; as any other crossbow bolt and forces a save vs petrify/polymorph. \nIf the target fails, it is transformed into a specific version of a common &lt;a href=\"squirrel\"&gt;squirrel&lt;/a&gt;, although it is even weaker and more defenseless than the natural animal.\nThe bolt's polymorphing effects can be blocked by &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe squirrel creature is so fragile and easy to hit, that any damage will slay it.\nThe polymorph lasts for about 42 days game days, but it can be reverted with a successful &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nWhile these bolts exist in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II&lt;/a&gt; files, they are entirely unused by the game, and aren't included as random treasure either.\nMod content.\nThis bolt is now provided into BG1 (as well as numerous other items) with the installation of the &lt;a href=\"Unfinished%20Business%20for%20BG1\"&gt;Unfinished Business for BG1&lt;/a&gt; mod's revisions to various store stocks. \nA limited number of the bolt of polymorphing can be purchased, such as at &lt;a href=\"Ulgoth%27s%20Beard%20Inn\"&gt;Ulgoth's Beard Inn&lt;/a&gt;, from &lt;a href=\"Thalantyr%20the%20Conjurer\"&gt;Thalantyr the Conjurer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Sundries\"&gt;Sorcerous Sundries&lt;/a&gt;. \nIt will still potentially appear as a random treasure as well."}
