{"id": "36029", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=36029", "title": "Bone Golem", "text": "Bone Golems are a type of &lt;a href=\"Golem\"&gt;Golem&lt;/a&gt; fashioned from bones, serving as counterparts to &lt;a href=\"Flesh%20Golem\"&gt;Flesh Golem&lt;/a&gt;s. They are quite popular with &lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;necromancers&lt;/a&gt; for reasons that should be obvious. They only appear in where they resemble enormous, hunch-backed skeletons with elongated, mantis-like bladed arms, making them easy to discern from the other golem types.\nGameplay.\nBone golems can only be harmed by magical or enchanted weapons. Like a &lt;a href=\"skeleton\"&gt;skeleton&lt;/a&gt;, a bone golem has 50% resistance to &lt;a href=\"Slashing%20damage\"&gt;slashing&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"piercing%20damage\"&gt;piercing damage&lt;/a&gt;, and like a Demilich, they are immune to all spells and effects from &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power levels&lt;/a&gt; 1 through 9.\nThey also have 50% resistance to &lt;a href=\"Missile%20damage\"&gt;Missile damage&lt;/a&gt;, 100% resistance to &lt;a href=\"Fire%20damage\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cold%20damage\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Electricity%20damage\"&gt;Electric&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Acid%20damage\"&gt;Acid&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Poison%20damage%23Technical_note\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; damage as well as 100% &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;.\nNote that despite their appearance, these golems are not &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; creatures.\nLocations.\nBone golems are one of the rarest golem types in the game. They can be found at the following locations:\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Dungeon%20Crawl\"&gt;Dungeon Crawl&lt;/a&gt; mod will pit the party against several Bone Golems.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod adds extra Bone Golems to spawned undead encounters, to go along with any spawned Lich creatures. An example would be during the &lt;a href=\"Investigate%20the%20Deaths%20in%20the%20Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Investigate the Deaths in the Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; questline, and the &lt;a href=\"Ruined%20Temple\"&gt;Ruined Temple&lt;/a&gt;. There may be two Liches, and if so, at least two Bone Golems. Two liches may be in &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Bodhi%27s%20Hunt%20Level%202\"&gt;Spellhold Bodhi's Hunt Level 2&lt;/a&gt;, and therefore two Bone Golems also.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Golem%20Construction%20for%20Spellcasters\"&gt;Golem Construction for Spellcasters&lt;/a&gt; mod provides certain dropped bone fragment components when a Bone Golem is destroyed - components needed to construct your own Bone Golem variety.\nAlso with this mod, a Bone Golem is bestowed with an innate ability spell effect that casts an area of effect &lt;a href=\"Panic\"&gt;Panic&lt;/a&gt; around itself called \"Hideous Laughter\". Each enemy creature exposed to the Horror must save vs. spell with a -2 penalty or suffer a panic effect for a variable duration. The Hideous Laughter bypasses spell protections and magic resistance. It is a Necromancy School and disabling type spell. It cannot be dispelled."}
{"id": "30107", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30107", "title": "Bone Wardstone", "text": "The Bone Wardstone is needed to disable the carpet trap in the rune carpet room located on &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower%20%28Labyrinth%20Level%20Four%29\"&gt;labyrinth level 4&lt;/a&gt; beneath &lt;a href=\"Durlag%27s%20Tower\"&gt;Durlag's Tower&lt;/a&gt;. It is found in the trapped kiln in the center of the forge room. Inserting into the machine in the machine room will disable the trap."}
