{"id": "54910", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54910", "title": "Book Merchant (Imnesvale Inn)", "text": "Book Merchant is a male with the look of a Nobleman in dress and appearance. He's found in and the Enhanced Edition only.\nGameplay.\nHe's found within the &lt;a href=\"Imnesvale%20Inn\"&gt;Imnesvale Inn&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"Umar%20Hills\"&gt;Umar Hills&lt;/a&gt; village of Imnesvale.\nIf a party member speaks with him, he'll reply politely but is in between resupply of his book merchandise. He no tomes to sell at the moment and nothing interesting to say.\nIn chapter six it's possible that the &lt;a href=\"Priest%20of%20Oghma%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Priest of Oghma (Shadows of Amn)&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Oghma%20%28Athkatla%29\"&gt;Temple of Oghma (Athkatla)&lt;/a&gt; referenced this book merchant as a possible source of information regarding the party's inquiry into curing vampirism.\nShould the party travel to find and see this merchant, then he will answer a question from the party - phrased as:\nThe dialogue and story told by the merchant will answer the questions the party is seeking. See &lt;a href=\"The%20final%20battle%20with%20Bodhi\"&gt;The final battle with Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; page and the \"Spoiler\" section if the player can't figure out what to do next."}
{"id": "4792", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4792", "title": "Book of Infinite Spells", "text": "The Book of Infinite Spells is a book which can be equipped in, and used from, the quick item slot by any class (except Wizard Slayer). It allows the casting of one spell per day, at &lt;a href=\"Item%20mechanics%23Caster_level\"&gt;caster level&lt;/a&gt; 10. It can also be used to turn to one of ten random pages, which swap the spell the book can cast, but if it randomly turns to the last page (Burning Hands), you cannot turn the pages anymore, and the spell becomes fixed. It can be gained from &lt;a href=\"Perth%20the%20Adept\"&gt;Perth the Adept&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Brynnlaw\"&gt;Brynnlaw&lt;/a&gt; who guards the Asylum Wardstone as well. This item appears only in \"\".\nThe Book begins on the Fireball page when first acquired. From there, the player has two choices: keep the page open to its existing spell (fireball), or elect to turn to a random page. Once the page is turned, a new random spell will be castable from the book. However, once the page has been turned, the previous spell will no longer be castable, unless it happens to appear again when turning to another random page. There are a total of 10 possible spells which the book can turn to, but if it ever turns to the spell Burning Hands, then the pages hold fast, and the book will be stuck on that spell forever more.\nThe spell chosen by the book when turning a page is entirely random, and can repeat spells multiple times.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Revisions\"&gt;Spell Revisions&lt;/a&gt; mod, if installed, will provide its versions of the spells in this book. As such there will be some changes to what the spells do and even entirely new spells."}
