{"id": "4598", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4598", "title": "Boomerang Dagger", "text": "The Boomerang Dagger (Boomerang Dagger +2 in-game) is an enchanted dagger +2 which can be used in melee combat or be thrown, and as the name says, it will return to the owner. This dagger has the same bonus to damage and &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; as a &lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20the%20Golem\"&gt;dagger +2&lt;/a&gt;, but a base damage of 2d4 instead of the usual 1d4 and a speed factor of 1 instead of 0. When used in melee it also retains an APR of 2, making it an excellent melee weapon even through the late game. It can be obtained if the group of mercenaries in &lt;a href=\"Delosar%27s%20Inn\"&gt;Delosar's Inn&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Bridge%20District\"&gt;Bridge District&lt;/a&gt; is killed. Can also be obtained by &lt;a href=\"Limited%20Wish%20Adventure\"&gt;wishing for a quest like no other&lt;/a&gt; from the same group or by simply pickpocketing &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Dennis\"&gt;Captain Dennis&lt;/a&gt;.\nLocations.\n\"Throne of Bhaal\".\n Worn by &lt;a href=\"Alorgoth\"&gt;Alorgoth&lt;/a&gt; during &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%27s%20Journey\"&gt;Rasaad's Journey&lt;/a&gt;, yet he cannot be killed."}
