{"id": "51402", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51402", "title": "Boon of Lathander", "text": "Boon of Lathander is an innate spell ability available to &lt;a href=\"Priest%20of%20Lathander\"&gt;Priest of Lathander&lt;/a&gt; Cleric kits in the game saga.\nEffects.\nThe spell effect is interruptible and has a casting time of 3 (about 1.8 seconds). The priest casts this ability upon oneself only. If successful, a \"\"Boon of Lathander\" and \"Negative Plane Protection\"\" icons will appear in the creature's portrait. \nOnce initiated upon the caster, the Priest receives the bonuses and protection stated in the description above, which will remain in force until the innate ability expires, or the spell is removed/dispelled. As the spell is classified as secondary type \"combination\" it will not be subject to a &lt;a href=\"Breach\"&gt;Breach&lt;/a&gt; spell or effect, but it can be targeted by &lt;a href=\"Dispel%20Magic\"&gt;Dispel Magic&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe internal &lt;a href=\"Opcode\"&gt;Opcode&lt;/a&gt; mechanics of the innate spell include a scripting state modifier that does not prevent this spell from stacking. Even the additional attacks per round stack. Adding another Boon onto an existing one will not extend the first's duration however."}
