{"id": "14297", "revid": "35448340", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=14297", "title": "Boots of Phasing", "text": "The Boots of Phasing appear in \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Black%20Pits\"&gt;The Black Pits&lt;/a&gt;\" and in \"\" (though unimplemented in normal gameplay).\nGameplay.\nThey are perhaps the most useful cursed item in the game as their effect of teleporting to an enemy every 3 seconds (the description given in the game is wrong) is often considered an advantage. This can be a great way to move in on enemy archers or spell casters (provided they can be seen) quickly from a distance if hiding in the shadows, invisible, or using spells such as &lt;a href=\"Farsight\"&gt;Farsight&lt;/a&gt;. It can also allow a surrounded and trapped character to get out to the open.\nWhen teleporting to an enemy the game will by default try to place you behind an enemy in sight, setting up a potential backstab for hidden characters. Each teleportation will also reset any enemy targeting forcing enemies to select a different target than the wearer if any are available.\nEquipped abilities : Armor Class -2 bonus, *Cursed*.\nCombat abilities: Wearer phases to a random opponent every 2 rounds 3 seconds (when an enemy is in sight).\nThese boots and the &lt;a href=\"Boots%20of%20Avoidance\"&gt;Boots of Avoidance&lt;/a&gt; are among the only boots that give a boost to AC.\nNote.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Chaos%20%28Creature%29\"&gt;Chaos (Creature)&lt;/a&gt; encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Heeding%20the%20Spirit%20of%20the%20Grove\"&gt;Heeding the Spirit of the Grove&lt;/a&gt; Druid stronghold quest line is equipped with these boots and can lead to a frustrating fight if multiple party members are involved in trying to attack it in melee."}
