{"id": "3394", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3394", "title": "Bracers of Archery", "text": "Bracers of Archery, also known by the name of The Dale's Protector are a pair a bracers which helps the wearer to increase his/her accuracy. It offers +2 THAC0 bonus for missiles, increasing the chance of hitting the target, but this cannot be equipped by &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Kensai\"&gt;Kensai&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"mage\"&gt;mage&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"sorcerer\"&gt;sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;s. It has a weight of 2 lbs. For accuracy in melee and ranged, &lt;a href=\"Xarrnous%27s%20Second%20Sword%20Arm\"&gt;Xarrnous's Second Sword Arm&lt;/a&gt;, which offers +1 thac0 bonus, is a good choice or &lt;a href=\"Gauntlets%20of%20Weapon%20Expertise\"&gt;Gauntlets of Weapon Expertise&lt;/a&gt;, which also adds a bonus to damage of +2. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, and and it will also appear in ."}
{"id": "3763", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3763", "title": "Bracers of Binding", "text": "Bracers of Binding is a pair of cursed bracers which makes it very difficult for the wearer to participate in combat, as they lower damage by 5 points, increase spell failure to 75% and give the wearer a +5 penalty to THAC0. Since they are cursed, they can't be unequiped without a &lt;a href=\"Remove%20Curse\"&gt;Remove Curse&lt;/a&gt; spell or the services of a priest. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;, , , and .\nIn Baldur's Gate, a pair can be found on the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Balduran\"&gt;Isle of Balduran&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn Siege of Dragonspear, they can be acquired as part of the quest &lt;a href=\"Drow%20Runaways\"&gt;Drow Runaways&lt;/a&gt; by either convincing the titular runaways to return to &lt;a href=\"Shapur\"&gt;Shapur&lt;/a&gt; (who, in an homage to their lore, will place them on &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and then summon a &lt;a href=\"Hook%20Horror\"&gt;Hook Horror&lt;/a&gt;), or by killing Shapur and taking them from her corpse.\nIn Baldur's Gate II, it can be looted from a window on one of the buildings in the Drow city of &lt;a href=\"Ust%20Natha\"&gt;Ust Natha&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4631", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4631", "title": "Bracers of Blinding Strike", "text": "The Bracers of Blinding Strike give the wearer of the bracers the ability to become &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Improved Hasted&lt;/a&gt; once per rest day, for 20 seconds. The bracers have a weight of 2 lbs. This item appears in , where it can be gained from Kuo-Toan prince in his dungeon in the &lt;a href=\"Underdark\"&gt;Underdark&lt;/a&gt;."}
