{"id": "17395", "revid": "5653418", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17395", "title": "Bracers of Defense AC 5", "text": "Bracers of Defense AC 5\u00a0\u00a0give the wearer an armor class rating of 5. If the armor class is lower than 5 or the same as 5 at the moment of equipping, this set of bracers has no effect on the armor class. Note that the bracers only set the base Armor Class to a certain number so they don't stack with body armor."}
{"id": "3761", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3761", "title": "Bracers of Defense AC 6", "text": "Bracers of Defense AC 6, also known as the Bracers to the Death, offer an &lt;a href=\"Armor%20Class\"&gt;Armor Class&lt;/a&gt; of 6 if there is no other armor or item equipped that offers a lower AC. They have a weight of 2 lbs. This item appears in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; and ."}
