{"id": "51278", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51278", "title": "Breathes Grit", "text": "Breathes Grit is an innate ability effect available to most &lt;a href=\"Air%20Mephit\"&gt;Air Mephit&lt;/a&gt; creatures in the game saga. \nEffects.\nThe spell effect is uninterruptable and takes almost no time to deploy. A cone effect projectile is launched at a single target in range, but it has an area of effect that can also apply the detrimental grit to any in that cone. It is similar to the &lt;a href=\"Cone%20of%20Cold\"&gt;Cone of Cold&lt;/a&gt; in terms of its range and spreading arc.\nThe innate ability has no saving throw, ignores magic resistance and has &lt;a href=\"power%20level\"&gt;power level&lt;/a&gt; 0, and thus cannot be blocked by spell protections like &lt;a href=\"Spell%20Deflection\"&gt;Spell Deflection&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Minor%20Globe%20of%20Invulnerability\"&gt;Minor Globe of Invulnerability&lt;/a&gt;. Any creatures in the AoE cone will suffer 1d6 damage. The effect can be absorbed with a &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "26938", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26938", "title": "Bregg", "text": "Bregg and his companion &lt;a href=\"Cohrvale\"&gt;Cohrvale&lt;/a&gt; are found northeast of the right entrance to &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Athkatla Slums&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Cohrvale\"&gt;Cohrvale&lt;/a&gt; will initiate the dialogue with &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt;.\nNote: Bregg's THAC0 is seemingly incorrect for a level 10 Fighter, and no weapon proficiencies are assigned.\nMod content.\nPeople involved.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod changes Bregg and assigns a default SCS tactical AI script for better combat behavior. Additionally, 5 pips in short sword weapon proficiency and 2 pips in single-weapon style are given to match up with a 10th level fighter's experience. Bregg's base THAC0 is corrected from 17 to 11 as well. SCS random treasure is also supplied."}
{"id": "6673", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6673", "title": "Brelm", "text": "Brelm is a &lt;a href=\"dwarven\"&gt;dwarven&lt;/a&gt; cobbler who can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Adventurer%20Mart\"&gt;Adventurer Mart&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nHe is a 'friend' of &lt;a href=\"Ribald%20Barterman\"&gt;Ribald Barterman&lt;/a&gt; and, as the latter claims, he got drunk in his store four months earlier and never left, despite Brelm saying that they met during an adventure in Shadowdale. He tends to tell a lot of tall tales and half-truths and, when spoken to, he will provide some rather amusing dialogue."}
{"id": "9056", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9056", "title": "Brendak", "text": "Brendak is the light armor in \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Black%20Pits\"&gt;The Black Pits&lt;/a&gt;\".\nThe reason he is not speaking to &lt;a href=\"Magda\"&gt;Magda&lt;/a&gt;, his wife, is because &lt;a href=\"Baeloth%20Barrityl\"&gt;Baeloth&lt;/a&gt; kept him from her, as revealed after Baeloth's death in the final battle.\nBrendak (store).\nAs a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt;, Brendak has specialized in selling mostly and related items, while his market stall neighbor &lt;a href=\"Gorch%20the%20Armorer\"&gt;Gorch the Armorer&lt;/a&gt; attends to customers who prefer . His palette increases with the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt;'s progress throughout the various \"Tiers\" of the arena battles. &lt;a href=\"Item\"&gt;Item&lt;/a&gt;s from earlier Tiers will be still available later and previously purchased ones restocked.\nHe sells at 145% of an item's base value and buys far more than only weapons for 30% item value, at a &lt;a href=\"depreciation%20rate\"&gt;depreciation rate&lt;/a&gt; of 5. Prices might be further modified through high &lt;a href=\"charisma\"&gt;charisma&lt;/a&gt; or an other-than-average &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is not possible to steal from his store."}
{"id": "7738", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7738", "title": "Brendan", "text": "Brendan is one of four &lt;a href=\"Red%20Wizards%20of%20Thay\"&gt;Red Wizards of Thay&lt;/a&gt; who are found standing on the remains of an ancient temple in the &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Wood\"&gt;Spider Wood&lt;/a&gt; area. Along with &lt;a href=\"Diana\"&gt;Diana&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lasala\"&gt;Lasala&lt;/a&gt;, he is part of &lt;a href=\"Denak\"&gt;Denak's&lt;/a&gt; group, which will attack your party if &lt;a href=\"Edwin%20Odesseiron\"&gt;Edwin Odesseiron&lt;/a&gt; is not in it.\nBrendan begins combat by casting &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; on himself, then begins casting the offensive spells &lt;a href=\"Horror\"&gt;Horror&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt; at the party."}
