{"id": "11767", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11767", "title": "Brennan Risling (Baldur's Gate)", "text": "Brennan Risling is a commoner encountered in &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Seven\"&gt;Chapter Seven&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; near the north entry point to &lt;a href=\"South%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;South Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. He approaches &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party on sight, speaking of the rising tensions with &lt;a href=\"Amn\"&gt;Amn&lt;/a&gt; and the increasing possibility of war with the southern nation, the potential \"plague and pestilence\" that could follow in its wake and the growing local sentiment that &lt;a href=\"Sarevok%20Anchev\"&gt;Sarevok&lt;/a&gt; is the best choice for a new Grand Duke.\nDialogue.\n\"Ayup, there be tensions rising 'tween us 'n Amn. There'll be war soon, 'n plague, 'n pestilence. Better them than us, I say.\"\nEither one of these dialogue trees leads to the following entry in the quest section of your &lt;a href=\"Journal\"&gt;Journal&lt;/a&gt; under the title \"The Rise of Sarevok\":"}
{"id": "7370", "revid": "283613", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7370", "title": "Brennan Risling (Shadows of Amn)", "text": "Brennan Risling is a &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; and a member of an adventuring party that is found on the second floor of the &lt;a href=\"Den%20of%20the%20Seven%20Vales\"&gt;Den of the Seven Vales&lt;/a&gt;. He'll be with &lt;a href=\"Mencar%20Pebblecrusher\"&gt;Mencar Pebblecrusher&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Smaeluv%20Orcslicer\"&gt;Smaeluv Orcslicer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Pooky\"&gt;Pooky&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Sorcerous%20Amon\"&gt;Sorcerous Amon&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf the encounter escalates and he gets injured, he will attempt to flee taking with him all his carried equipment.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some revisions to the creature. An SCS Thief default AI script is assigned for smarter tactical behavior and threat recognition. The thief also receives 1 pip in sword and shield style, which boosts his armor class vs. missile fire by +2. SCS will aggressively utilize backstabbing attacks with thieves. It will target unprotected and weakened opponents over those well protected. Much of the original scripts for Brennan are retained for use, such as potion use and when he decides to try and flee the battle if he is severely hurt. With Brennan's incredible luck score, expect his backstabs to deal more than forty piercing damage on any successful hit."}
