{"id": "8217", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8217", "title": "Wiven", "text": "Wiven is one of four members of the &lt;a href=\"Thieves%27%20Guild\"&gt;Thieves' Guild&lt;/a&gt; in the locked &lt;a href=\"Generic%20homes%20%28southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate%29%23AR1101\"&gt;house&lt;/a&gt; directly south of &lt;a href=\"Ye%20Olde%20Inn\"&gt;Ye Olde Inn&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. She will approach &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; and party, claiming she has them surrounded and, if you won't surrender, she and her three companions &lt;a href=\"Dirk\"&gt;Dirk&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sath\"&gt;Sath&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Meakin\"&gt;Meakin&lt;/a&gt; will attack. If you attack her before she speaks to you, those three won't spawn.\nProgressing too far in &lt;a href=\"Rasaad%20yn%20Bashir\"&gt;Rasaad's&lt;/a&gt; companion quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Enemies%20of%20My%20Friend\"&gt;The Enemies of My Friend&lt;/a&gt; will prevent her from appearing, as her location is used for a quest event as well; she will, however be back when one day has passed after these events."}
