{"id": "8854", "revid": "269096", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8854", "title": "Wooden Stake", "text": "A Wooden Stake is an essential item needed to permanently destroy a &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; that has been defeated and retreated from the battle area using its innate \"Gas Cloud\" form. The stake is used while the previously damaged vampire has retreated to its hidden coffin to recover.\nThe player will use these stakes in certain plot required portions of the game. Not all vampires defeated on the battlefield will be hunted down back to their coffin. \nGameplay.\nThe stakes can be bought at certain temples such as the temple of &lt;a href=\"Helm\"&gt;Helm&lt;/a&gt; and the temple of &lt;a href=\"Lathander\"&gt;Lathander&lt;/a&gt;, as well as from the merchant &lt;a href=\"Wallace\"&gt;Wallace&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Trademeet\"&gt;Trademeet&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; will provide the party with some during the main &lt;a href=\"Aran%27s%20tasks%20to%20receive%20the%20Shadow%20Thieves%27%20aid\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt; if you side with the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Thieves\"&gt;Shadow Thieves&lt;/a&gt;.\nIronically enough, they are also found in a couple of containers in &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;'s hideout in the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Lower Tombs&lt;/a&gt; under the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Graveyard\"&gt;Graveyard District&lt;/a&gt;.\nWooden stakes are only utilized about nine separate times, one of which takes place during SoD, eight in SoA, and none in ToB. In SoA, three are needed when siding with the Shadow Thieves in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%203\"&gt;Chapter 3&lt;/a&gt;, used for the first assault upon &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Bodhi's Lair&lt;/a&gt; to stake the vampires &lt;a href=\"Durst\"&gt;Durst&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gellal\"&gt;Gellal&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Lassal\"&gt;Lassal&lt;/a&gt; once they retreat to their coffins. One is used in the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Bodhi%27s%20Hunt%20Level%202\"&gt;Spellhold Dungeon&lt;/a&gt; to finish the vampire &lt;a href=\"Dace%20Sontan\"&gt;Dace Sontan&lt;/a&gt; after besting him in combat. Lastly, whether you sided with the Shadow Thieves or not, four are needed for the second assault on Bodhi's Lair in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; to put an end to the vampires &lt;a href=\"Valen\"&gt;Valen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Del\"&gt;Del&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Tanova\"&gt;Tanova&lt;/a&gt; in the same coffin room as Chapter 3, and finally the head vampire &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt;, forced to retreat into her gondola coffin.\nThe vampire &lt;a href=\"Tsolak\"&gt;Tsolak&lt;/a&gt; in can also be staked in that game edition."}
{"id": "11186", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=11186", "title": "Worg", "text": "Worgs are unusually intelligent offshoots of &lt;a href=\"Dire%20Wolf\"&gt;dire wolves&lt;/a&gt; (even being capable of speech, though this trait is not depicted in the games) and somewhat common enemies found in many wilderness areas, especially forests.\nDespite their 18 &lt;a href=\"Strength\"&gt;Strength&lt;/a&gt; with a 40-percentile exceptional strength boost, they are no more dangerous than normal &lt;a href=\"wolves\"&gt;wolves&lt;/a&gt;. They travel alone and in packs and may be dangerous to low-level parties.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Monster%20Summoning%20I\"&gt;Monster Summoning I&lt;/a&gt; spell can summon 1 or 2 of these animals, which is randomly determined at the time of casting."}
