{"id": "2377", "revid": "773742", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2377", "title": "Worn-out Boots", "text": "Worn-out Boots are that may be encountered in \"&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate (game)&lt;/a&gt;\" (and '), ', and ' (and ').\nAcquisition.\nIn , these boots belong to the husband of &lt;a href=\"Landrin\"&gt;Landrin&lt;/a&gt;. They can be found in &lt;a href=\"Landrin%27s%20Home\"&gt;Landrin's home&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Beregost\"&gt;Beregost&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn , they can be found in a box outside the entrance to the lower level of &lt;a href=\"Bridgefort\"&gt;Bridgefort&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn , they are worn by &lt;a href=\"Reynald%20de%20Chatillon\"&gt;Reynald de Chatillon&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rindus\"&gt;Rindus&lt;/a&gt; who can be encountered during the side quest &lt;a href=\"Seek%20Out%20and%20Investigate%20the%20Fallen%20Paladins\"&gt;Seek Out and Investigate the Fallen Paladins&lt;/a&gt;.\nFunction.\nThey are a pair of normal &lt;a href=\"boots\"&gt;boots&lt;/a&gt; which offer no bonuses or any other type of enhancement but can be worn by all &lt;a href=\"class\"&gt;class&lt;/a&gt;es. In the Baldur's Gate 1, the only real use for is to bring them back to Landrin to complete a portion of &lt;a href=\"Landrin%27s%20Possessions\"&gt;her quest&lt;/a&gt;. \nIn other games, they are junk items without a use."}
