{"id": "16683", "revid": "49135869", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16683", "title": "Writhing Fog", "text": "Writhing Fog is a 2nd level &lt;a href=\"priest%20spell\"&gt;priest spell&lt;/a&gt; only usable by &lt;a href=\"shaman\"&gt;shaman&lt;/a&gt;s. \nGameplay.\nAll shamans automatically receive this spell and do not have to select it on level-ups. The shaman himself is immune to the effects of this spell and so are creatures 100% resistant to cold damage. \nThis spell's effects don't stack. So if a creature is hit by one instance of Writhing Fog, it can't be hit by another (in technical terms, the spell gives targets protection against the Writhing Fog spell itself for 5 seconds right after hitting them). "}
