{"id": "47067", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47067", "title": "Wulfgar", "text": "Wulfgar is a companion with &lt;a href=\"Drizzt%20Do%27Urden\"&gt;Drizzt Do'Urden&lt;/a&gt;. The group can be encountered only in &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt;. This can first occur after the player's party exits the &lt;a href=\"Elven%20Temple%20at%20Underdark%20Exit\"&gt;Elven Temple at Underdark Exit&lt;/a&gt; area and selects another destination from the &lt;a href=\"World%20Map\"&gt;World Map&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nWulfgar's first appearance is covered in the &lt;a href=\"Encounter%20-%20Drizzt%20Do%27Urden\"&gt;Encounter - Drizzt Do'Urden&lt;/a&gt; page.\nHis second potential appearance is outlined in &lt;a href=\"The%20final%20battle%20with%20Bodhi\"&gt;The final battle with Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; page. If he is killed in the first encounter, then the second encounter is moot.\nIf the party is engaged in combat with Wulfgar (this can happen in the first encounter with Drizzt), he behaves as a melee attacking fighter. He'll throw his war hammer at detected targets, usually the closest to him, and or engage in melee combat with the hammer in close quarters.\nThe combat script will often have him quaff a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Stone%20Giant%20Strength\"&gt;Potion of Stone Giant Strength&lt;/a&gt;. He can also consume the &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Extra%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Extra Healing&lt;/a&gt; when HP falls to 50% of original.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod changes the AI scripting used by Wulfgar, to improve tactical behavior and item usage.\nSCS adds 2 pips in single-weapon fighting style to the warrior.\nAn additional potion is added to Wulfgar for use."}
{"id": "48478", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48478", "title": "Wurn", "text": "Wurn is a &lt;a href=\"cleric\"&gt;cleric&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Ertof%20Dand\"&gt;Ertof Dand's&lt;/a&gt; bandit group who have heard that &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; has amassed many valuable items worth stealing.\nIf Gorion's Ward is a male &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"elf\"&gt;elf&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"half-elf\"&gt;half-elf&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"halfling\"&gt;halfling&lt;/a&gt;, and if the romance with &lt;a href=\"Jaheira\"&gt;Jaheira&lt;/a&gt; has reached a certain point (Jaheira's Local variable LoveTalk = 27), the bandits might appear any time the party is resting outdoors. Otherwise, this encounter will never happen.\nThe party wakes to find a blade at Jaheira's throat, and an ultimatum to hand over all their possessions or else. Gorion's Ward will then have a few different dialog options, which may affect the outcome of the romance.\nMod content.\n&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod revises Wurn. A new default SCS \"Smarter Cleric\" AI script is assigned for better tactical behavior and spell casting choice. Has 1 pip in quarterstaff weapon proficiency and 1 pip in two handed weapon weapon fighting style. Will self-buff at the opening of hostilities, attempt to heal allies or self, and has many other Priest spells to choose from compared to the unmodified version. He opens with a previously cast contingency type budd of &lt;a href=\"Armor%20of%20Faith\"&gt;Armor of Faith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spiritual%20Hammer\"&gt;Spiritual Hammer&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Free%20Action%20%28spell%29\"&gt;Free Action (spell)&lt;/a&gt;."}
