{"id": "3749", "revid": "270446", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3749", "title": "Xan", "text": "Xan is a lawful neutral elf &lt;a href=\"Enchanter\"&gt;Enchanter&lt;/a&gt; and a potential &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt; in , , and . He is also the owner of a powerful &lt;a href=\"Moonblade%20%28Nashkel%20Mines%29\"&gt;Moonblade&lt;/a&gt;, which can only be used by him.\nBackground.\nXan is an\u00a0enchanter\u00a0and a Greycloak\u00a0of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Evereska\"&gt;Evereska&lt;/a&gt; sent to investigate the political turmoil of the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt;. Unfortunately, he was captured and held prisoner by &lt;a href=\"Mulahey\"&gt;Mulahey&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt; &amp;.\nRecruitment.\nXan is encountered near the end of &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Two\"&gt;Chapter Two&lt;/a&gt;, or the beginning of &lt;a href=\"Chapter%20Three\"&gt;Chapter Three&lt;/a&gt; if the party deals with &lt;a href=\"Mulahey\"&gt;Mulahey&lt;/a&gt; first. He is found held captive in a cave room next to Mulahey's makeshift throne room in the &lt;a href=\"Nashkel%20Mines\"&gt;Nashkel Mines&lt;/a&gt;, and will ask to help the party defeat him if they haven't already done so. Note that he will leave permanently if you turn him down at this point, but if his offer to join the party (whether Mulahey has already been killed or not) is accepted he can subsequently be released from the party and he will remain wherever he is until recruited again.\nHe also appears in the tutorial of \u00a0and the Enhanced Editions, where he explains how the wizard spells work.\nGameplay.\nXan's &lt;a href=\"Specialist%20Mage\"&gt;specialization&lt;/a&gt; is Enchanter, so he can't scribe and cast Evocation spells from his spellbook, either powerful offensive ones like &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fireball\"&gt;Fireball&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Bolt\"&gt;Lightning Bolt&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Cloudkill\"&gt;Cloudkill&lt;/a&gt;, or good defensive ones like &lt;a href=\"Shield_%28spell%29\"&gt;Shield&lt;/a&gt;. But alternatively he can use all the powerful arcane wands, like the &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Wand of Fire&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Wand%20of%20Lightning\"&gt;Wand of Lightning&lt;/a&gt;, and also items like the &lt;a href=\"Shield%20Amulet\"&gt;Shield Amulet&lt;/a&gt; instead of some of the spells. Combined with the casting of non-evocation \"nukes\" (like &lt;a href=\"Melf%27s%20Acid%20Arrow\"&gt;Melf's Acid Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Flame%20Arrow\"&gt;Flame Arrow&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Skull%20Trap\"&gt;Skull Trap&lt;/a&gt;), Xan can deal significant spell damage when required.\nHowever, his specialization means that his Enchantment spells are more powerful against enemies, who receive a -2 penalty to their saving throws. Being able to hinder or even shut down enemy groups \u2014 and a good way to do this is with Enchantment spells like for example &lt;a href=\"Sleep\"&gt;Sleep&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hold%20Person%20%28wizard%29\"&gt;Hold Person&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Chaos\"&gt;Chaos&lt;/a&gt; \u2014 might be even more crucial in Baldur's Gate (being a low level setting) than dealing a lot of damage.\nWhen first encountered he is injured and has no spells memorized, though there is a &lt;a href=\"Moonblade%20%28Nashkel%20Mines%29\"&gt;Moonblade&lt;/a&gt; in a nearby chest which can only be wielded by Xan. It is very powerful, but due to Xan's low constitution he should really only use the weapon either defensively (with high enough fire resistance, fire damage will actually heal Xan) or to finish off disabled enemy units.\nHis low hit points mean that spells like &lt;a href=\"Mirror%20Image\"&gt;Mirror Image&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stoneskin\"&gt;Stoneskin&lt;/a&gt; might be crucial for him. Also, using potions like the &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Fortitude\"&gt;Potion of Fortitude&lt;/a&gt; when needed can raise his survival chances by a lot.\nPersonality.\nXan is a wellspring of pessimistic dialogue, often making defeatist comments and expressing surprise at the party's positive achievements. His excessive gloom, despondency and moroseness is received differently by players; some find the character humorous, others are annoyed by him.\nA closer inspection of Xan's &lt;a href=\"%23Quotes\"&gt;voiced remarks&lt;/a&gt; against other NPCs, however, reveals a sarcastic \u2013 even snide \u2013 nature to his comments (especially against &lt;a href=\"Ajantis%20Ilvastarr\"&gt;Ajantis&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Eldoth%20Kron\"&gt;Eldoth&lt;/a&gt;), which adds a new dimension to his personality by keeping the player guessing about how serious he actually is with his pessimism. This conflicting persona is reflected by how the character wields a Moonblade \u2013 an extremely powerful, semi-sentient, good-aligned magical weapon that will actually kill a user it deems unworthy of wielding it.\nMod content.\nWith installation of the &lt;a href=\"Xan%20BG2%20NPC\"&gt;Xan BG2 NPC&lt;/a&gt; mod, Xan can be met again in &lt;a href=\"Athkatla\"&gt;Athkatla&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Government\"&gt;Government district&lt;/a&gt; and once more become a &lt;a href=\"companion\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt;."}
