{"id": "51042", "revid": "35642161", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51042", "title": "Xan BG2 NPC", "text": "The Xan BG2 NPC mod adds &lt;a href=\"Xan\"&gt;Xan&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;BG1&lt;/a&gt; character, to &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II\"&gt;BG2&lt;/a&gt; as a &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;joinable NPC&lt;/a&gt;.\nNPC background.\nXan is depressed, pessimistic, and loathes human cities.\nAs a Greycloak\u00a0of\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Evereska\"&gt;Evereska&lt;/a&gt;, he was sent to the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast\"&gt;Sword Coast&lt;/a&gt; to investigate the political turmoil there. He was captured and held prisoner by &lt;a href=\"Mulahey\"&gt;Mulahey&lt;/a&gt;, but freed by (and traveled with) &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; during the events of the &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20%28game%29\"&gt;\"Baldur's Gate\"&lt;/a&gt; game. Now they meet again in Amn...\nNPC class.\nWhile Xan is originally an &lt;a href=\"Enchanter\"&gt;Enchanter&lt;/a&gt;, the mod's installer lets you alternatively choose &lt;a href=\"Fighter/Mage\"&gt;Fighter/Mage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wild%20Mage\"&gt;Wild Mage&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer\"&gt;Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt; as his class.\nCrossmod content.\nThe following portrait pack mods provide an alternative portrait for Xan:\nThe \"&lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.gibberlings3.net/mods/npcs/crossmod/\"&gt;Crossmod Banter Pack&lt;/a&gt;\" adds banters between Xan and the following other mod NPCs:"}
{"id": "3764", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3764", "title": "Xarrnous's Second Sword Arm", "text": "The Gauntlets of Weapon Skill, better known as Xarrnous's Second Sword Arm, are a pair of &lt;a href=\"gauntlets\"&gt;gauntlets&lt;/a&gt; in \"Baldur's Gate\", made to increase the chances of hitting enemies successfully: they offer a bonus of -1 to the wearer's &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "34741", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34741", "title": "Xei Win Toh", "text": "Xei Win Toh will spawn when the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20Key\"&gt;Heart Key&lt;/a&gt; is turned to unlock the western pedestal in &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20Final%20Seal\"&gt;Watcher's Keep Final Seal&lt;/a&gt; dungeon.\nShe is a demonic fighter that \"dual wields\" a pair of highly enchanted bastard swords with deadly effect.\nGameplay.\nPrimarily an opponent that seeks to get into close quarters combat, she will typically rush toward the first enemy seen - however, if there are choices then she prioritizes spell casting classes like the mage, cleric, bard and sorcerer.\nXei Win will apply a &lt;a href=\"War%20Cry\"&gt;War Cry&lt;/a&gt; at the outset of combat, and then when an enemy is within a certain range, empower herself with the &lt;a href=\"Whirlwind%20Attack\"&gt;Whirlwind Attack&lt;/a&gt; ability, and wail away.\nLater on, her next special power will be to use is the &lt;a href=\"Kai\"&gt;Kai&lt;/a&gt; ability.\nShe is immune to a number of &lt;a href=\"Status%20Effects\"&gt;Status Effects&lt;/a&gt; and has a moderate &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt; rating.\nWhen her &lt;a href=\"HP\"&gt;HP&lt;/a&gt; falls below 50% she'll quaff a &lt;a href=\"Potion%20of%20Superior%20Healing\"&gt;Potion of Superior Healing&lt;/a&gt; and will try and do the same when the HP drops below 20% - this can be done up to four times and then her supply runs out.\nParty members that are struck by her in melee will be at risk of substantial damage, as well various detrimental status effects.\nEach strike from her swords has equal probability to either:\nA &lt;a href=\"Saving%20throw\"&gt;Saving throw&lt;/a&gt; vs. Breath with a 4-point penalty negates these effects.\nThe duration of these effects is 1 turn, and they bypass &lt;a href=\"Magic%20resistance\"&gt;Magic resistance&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Power%20level\"&gt;Power level&lt;/a&gt; protection, and can't be dispelled.\nUpon death she drops some valuable gems.\nBugs.\nXei Win Toh's regeneration ability timing mode is set as permanent, but that setting requires a duration to work, and it has no duration, and therefore it doesn't operate correctly. This is an issue throughout the game in several other creatures as well. This issue is included in &lt;a href=\"The%20Enhanced%20Edition%20Fixpack%20%28EEFP%29\"&gt;The Enhanced Edition Fixpack (EEFP)&lt;/a&gt; and is already identified to Beamdog for possible fixing in the future.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod will make some revisions to this creature.\nShe is now a level 25 &lt;a href=\"Kensai\"&gt;Kensai&lt;/a&gt; rather than just a fighter.\nHer weapon proficiencies are boosted to 5 pips in bastard sword and 3 pips in two-weapon fighting style.\nKensai passive bonuses are also configured, boosting weapon speed factor by 6, armor class by 2, &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; by 8, and attack damage bonus +8.\nAs a Kensai, the undroppable armor is removed, and thus she loses some armor class rating, the fire resistance and immunity to &lt;a href=\"Kill%20target\"&gt;Kill target&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt;.\nHowever, her final &lt;a href=\"THAC0\"&gt;THAC0&lt;/a&gt; improves to -19 with the main hand and -17 in the off hand, and her final attack damage bonus is now +10, not including the weapon damage and strength bonus.\nOther abilities and special powers remain the same as the original."}
{"id": "9059", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9059", "title": "Xithiss", "text": "Xithiss is a &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;mind flayer&lt;/a&gt; under &lt;a href=\"Baeloth%20Barrityl\"&gt;Baeloth's&lt;/a&gt; control in \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Black%20Pits\"&gt;The Black Pits&lt;/a&gt;\".\nHis mind is incomplete, or so he says.\nXithiss (store).\nThe &lt;a href=\"Mind%20Flayer\"&gt;mind flayer&lt;/a&gt; sells and magically enhanced . His palette increases with the &lt;a href=\"party\"&gt;party&lt;/a&gt;'s progress throughout the various \"Tiers\" of the arena battles. &lt;a href=\"Item\"&gt;Item&lt;/a&gt;s from earlier Tiers will be still available later and previously purchased ones restocked.\nXithiss sells at 145% of an item's base value and buys far more than only weapons for 30% item value, at a &lt;a href=\"depreciation%20rate\"&gt;depreciation rate&lt;/a&gt; of 5. Prices might be further modified through high &lt;a href=\"charisma\"&gt;charisma&lt;/a&gt; or an other-than-average &lt;a href=\"reputation\"&gt;reputation&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is not possible to steal from his store."}
