{"id": "13594", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13594", "title": "Yarrow", "text": "Yarrow is a character in the \"\". She will gate in when the party has wounded &lt;a href=\"Treadsoft\"&gt;Treadsoft&lt;/a&gt; enough. She can teleport the party into the lower part of &lt;a href=\"Resurrection%20Gorge\"&gt;Resurrection Gorge&lt;/a&gt;. The party can also teleport into the lower part of the gorge using &lt;a href=\"Acorn%20of%20Yarrow\"&gt;Acorn of Yarrow&lt;/a&gt; which can be found in her body if she's killed or pickpocketed from her."}
{"id": "10842", "revid": "31124876", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10842", "title": "Ye Olde Inn", "text": "The Ye Olde Inn is located in the district of &lt;a href=\"Southwest%20Baldur%27s%20Gate\"&gt;Southwest Baldur's Gate&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Flaming%20Fist%20Headquarters\"&gt;Flaming Fist Headquarters&lt;/a&gt; is next door and the &lt;a href=\"Potion%20Shop\"&gt;Potion Shop&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"General%20Store%20%28AR1116%29\"&gt;general store&lt;/a&gt; are located across the street.\nWhen you first enter, it is being overrun by five &lt;a href=\"Green%20Slime\"&gt;green slimes&lt;/a&gt;. The bartender is covered in green slime and in the process of being dissolved. He gets out one last message to you before he dies.\nWith the proprietor dead, Ye Olde Inn is just a building with a few &lt;a href=\"Commoner\"&gt;Commoner&lt;/a&gt;s wandering about in a stupor - if you saved any. If any of the patrons survived you can question them to discover that the mage &lt;a href=\"Ramazith\"&gt;Ramazith&lt;/a&gt; is responsible for the green slimes. There is no quest related to Ramazith and the slimes but he can be killed without consequence during the quest &lt;a href=\"The%20Captive%20Nymph\"&gt;The Captive Nymph&lt;/a&gt;.\nBesides the melting bartender, there are six commoners and four green slimes in the main room and one commoner and one green slime in the kitchen. Killing a green slime gives your party 65 XP but no loot. There's a barrel in the kitchen with 15 in it. There are six empty containers upstairs. There isn't an actual cellar where these slimes supposedly came from."}
{"id": "54942", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54942", "title": "Yeanasha", "text": "Yeanasha is an NPC introduced during the \"\" saga and the enhanced edition. \nGameplay.\nYeanasha only appears during &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%206\"&gt;Baldur's Gate II Chapter 6&lt;/a&gt; with two other Shadow Thieves, including &lt;a href=\"Arkanis%20Gath\"&gt;Arkanis Gath&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Gofus\"&gt;Gofus&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe shadow thief's appearance only occurs if &lt;a href=\"Gorion%27s%20Ward\"&gt;Gorion's Ward&lt;/a&gt; asked for assistance against the vampire coven when seeing &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail\"&gt;Aran Linvail&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Aran%20Linvail%27s%20Hideout\"&gt;Aran Linvail's Hideout&lt;/a&gt;.\nIf Aran agreed, then all the thieves will appear in the central chamber (with the large table) in the &lt;a href=\"Lower%20Tombs\"&gt;Lower Tombs&lt;/a&gt;.\nYeanasha is not controllable by the player, but the creature's script will follow the PC and engage in melee combat with red circled enemies when they are detected.\nThe Kensai's actions are centered around combat outcomes with &lt;a href=\"Tanova\"&gt;Tanova&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Hareishan%20%28Shadows%20of%20Amn%29\"&gt;Hareishan&lt;/a&gt; vampires while the party is present in the same area. When those two are defeated, Arkanis Gath will dismiss Gofus and Yeanasha and they'll depart the area.\nYeanasha is scripted to use his &lt;a href=\"Kai\"&gt;Kai&lt;/a&gt; ability initially, and then again 30 game seconds later if still in combat. The game has not properly configured the creature file to match up with a level 16 Kensai kit, and no passive bonuses are included in the file design. He just uses &lt;a href=\"Kai\"&gt;Kai&lt;/a&gt; as the only special ability.\nMod content.\nInstallation of the &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; Mod makes some changes to Yeanasha. He is now a level 9/13 &lt;a href=\"Fighter%20/%20Thief\"&gt;Fighter / Thief&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Kensai\"&gt;Kensai&lt;/a&gt;. Yeanasha is now properly configured as a Kensai kit, with all the commensurate passive kit bonuses included into his abilities. Since some SCS vampires require +3 weapons to hit them, he now wields a &lt;a href=\"Katana%20%2B3\"&gt;Katana +3&lt;/a&gt;. Worn armor is removed, and a &lt;a href=\"Cloak%20of%20Protection%20%2B1\"&gt;Cloak of Protection +1&lt;/a&gt; is equipped.\nSeveral potions are now supplied for scripted use by the Kensai to boost abilities at the start of combat and heal itself when damage is accrued to a set value. A scroll in a quick slot can be used as well."}
