{"id": "51150", "revid": "44830706", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51150", "title": "Yochlol", "text": "A Yochlol is a type of lesser Tanar'ri demon that were normally used by the Queen of Spiders to infiltrate undetected into &lt;a href=\"Drow\"&gt;Drow&lt;/a&gt; societies. This particular yochlol is found in the &lt;a href=\"Watcher%27s%20Keep%20-%20Tahazzar%20%28AR3012%29\"&gt;Watcher's Keep - Tahazzar (AR3012)&lt;/a&gt; area. More of these can be encountered in the Teleport Maze as random spawns when the party attempts to rest in certain rooms.\nGameplay.\nThe Yochlol will engage in melee combat with the nearest enemy detected with an enchanted +3 attack, from an undroppable &lt;a href=\"Drow%20Scimitar\"&gt;Drow Scimitar&lt;/a&gt;.\nSeveral spells are triggered for use and initiated by the \"ReallyForceSpell\" AI command. They are cast depending on certain combat conditions as shown on the InfoBox.\nThe creature is under a permanent normal &lt;a href=\"Haste%20effect\"&gt;Haste effect&lt;/a&gt;, and thus has a double movement modifier and an extra attack per round.\nThe she demon has many status effect immunities and is able to &lt;a href=\"See%20the%20invisible\"&gt;See the invisible&lt;/a&gt;.\nMod content.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Sword%20Coast%20Stratagems\"&gt;Sword Coast Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; mod makes a few revisions to the Yochlol including raising the creatures Hit Dice to 15. The creature's AI is improved and looks for enemy weaknesses and immunities to help make decisions in tactical combat situations. All spells cast are now innate ability cast spells, and not Wizard spells.\nYochlols (cast at 15th level):&lt;br&gt;\nFlame Strike, once per five rounds&lt;br&gt;\nSpider Spawn, once per three rounds&lt;br&gt;\nDomination, Improved Invisibility, Remove Magic and Teleport without Error, at will&lt;br&gt;\nHeal, three times per day&lt;br&gt;\nNote that the innate domination spell has a Saving throw penalty of -4. The Spider Spawn is actually a Monster Summoning IV innate spell and will produce 4 spider enemies."}
{"id": "7715", "revid": "36786428", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7715", "title": "Yondalla", "text": "Yondalla, also known as the Protector and Provider, the Nurturing Matriarch and the Blessed One, is a &lt;a href=\"lawful%20good\"&gt;lawful good&lt;/a&gt; greater &lt;a href=\"deity\"&gt;deity&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0of\u00a0protection, fertility, the &lt;a href=\"halfling\"&gt;halfling&lt;/a&gt; race, children, security, leadership, diplomacy, wisdom, the cycle of life, creation, family and familial Love, tradition, community, harmony and prosperity.\nShe is the creator of halfling race and matriarch of its pantheon. A lot of her portfolios are shared with the latter one's other members."}
{"id": "4494", "revid": "49482971", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4494", "title": "Yoshimo", "text": "Yoshimo is a true neutral human &lt;a href=\"Thief%23Bounty%20Hunter\"&gt;bounty hunter&lt;/a&gt; and a potential &lt;a href=\"Companions\"&gt;companion&lt;/a&gt; during the \"\" campaign.\nBackground.\nYoshimo is from &lt;a href=\"Kara-Tur\"&gt;Kara-Tur&lt;/a&gt;.\nBaldur's Gate II: Shadows of Amn.\nRecruitment.\nYoshimo is available to recruit from &lt;a href=\"Baldur%27s%20Gate%20II%20Chapter%201\"&gt;Chapter 1&lt;/a&gt; where you will meet him when you reach the &lt;a href=\"Irenicus%27s%20Dungeon%202nd%20Floor\"&gt;second level&lt;/a&gt; of Irenicus's Dungeon. Yoshimo claims himself to be an escaping prisoner just like you, and will offer to join the party to increase the survival chance.\nHe joins the party at level 10, with &lt;a href=\"Weapon%20Proficiency\"&gt;weapon proficiencies&lt;/a&gt; in: Katana, Dagger, Short Bow, and Single Weapon Style.\nIf you decide to exclude him from party he will go to &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt;. \nAfter you gather 15000 gold for Chapter 3 start and you will decide to join to &lt;a href=\"Bodhi\"&gt;Bodhi&lt;/a&gt; he will disappear from Copper Coronet permanently (he will stay if you join to shadow thieves side). If you exclude him after Chapter 3 and you side with Bodhi, he will disappear permanently too (EE 2.6).\nYoshimo the companion plot.\n&lt;a href=\"Jon%20Irenicus\"&gt;Jon Irenicus&lt;/a&gt; or his disguised form as the &lt;a href=\"Coordinator\"&gt;Coordinator&lt;/a&gt; will eventually reveal his plan to draw Gorion's Ward into a carefully laid trap. It is at this juncture that Yoshimo is revealed to be his puppet. This occurs after the prison cells tour while navigating the &lt;a href=\"Spellhold%20Main%20Floor\"&gt;Spellhold Main Floor&lt;/a&gt; area. It doesn't matter which method the party managed to get inside Spellhold, whether via &lt;a href=\"Desharik\"&gt;Desharik&lt;/a&gt; or using the &lt;a href=\"Wardstone%20for%20Asylum\"&gt;Wardstone for Asylum&lt;/a&gt;. In both cases Yoshimo's plot will occur.\nThe party will speak of their disgust over this betrayal. Once the party is incapacitated by a sleep gas - Yoshimo is present with Irenicus while he performs a procedure to drain the Bhaalspawn's soul essence.\nDuring your escape you'll encounter Yoshimo again, he will teleport into the laboratory during the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20with%20Irenicus%20in%20Spellhold\"&gt;Battle with Irenicus in Spellhold&lt;/a&gt; at the same time that Irenicus is escaping the battle due to damage. Following that, Yoshimo delivers some dialogue and then goes hostile. Seconds later the &lt;a href=\"Murderer\"&gt;Murderer&lt;/a&gt; thieves will begin to attempt to enter the lab as well. It's also revealed by Yoshimo that Irenicus has somehow probably placed sort of &lt;a href=\"geas\"&gt;geas&lt;/a&gt; upon him, forcing him to obey his will or die instantly. After Yoshimo's inevitable death, you may pick up &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo%27s%20Heart\"&gt;his heart&lt;/a&gt; and bring it to a priest of &lt;a href=\"Ilmater\"&gt;Ilmater&lt;/a&gt; later to grant him final rest in the afterlife, you earn for doing so.\nHowever, if you dismiss him and ask him to stay in the &lt;a href=\"Copper%20Coronet\"&gt;Copper Coronet&lt;/a&gt; before entering Spellhold, he will not be mentioned by Jon Irenicus at all after the inmate cells tour. \nOnce the party returns to Athkatla in chapter 6, if the party visits the Copper Coronet, Yoshimo automatically dies when you step inside. There will no heart to collect. Thus ends Yoshimo's appearance in the saga. \nThere are also tricks in to keep him alive, at least until \"\". However, this isn't recommended, as the game has no dialogue for Yoshimo after a certain game point and wasn't designed for him to be present. Circumnavigating or using various exploits to achieve this is outside the scope of the wiki, although it can be found on the internet if the player wishes to investigate that exploit. \n&lt;noinclude&gt;&lt;br&gt;\nGameplay.\nHe is the only pure (non-dual class) &lt;a href=\"thief\"&gt;thief&lt;/a&gt; in \"Baldur's Gate II: Shadows of Amn\". In both BG2 and BG2EE he has the kit &lt;a href=\"Bounty%20Hunter\"&gt;Bounty Hunter&lt;/a&gt;.\nYoshimo has the following items when joining the party: &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo%27s%20Katana\"&gt;his katana&lt;/a&gt; which can only be used by him, a short bow, studded leather armor and some arrows.\nYoshimo can &lt;a href=\"dual-class\"&gt;dual-class&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"fighter\"&gt;fighter&lt;/a&gt;. If you do so before leaving Irenicus's Dungeon in Chapter 1 he can become a strong archer, thanks to his 18 Dexterity and potential for grandmastery (due to the large experience gain upon completing the prologue). However, this is not advised for new players unless they have a backup thief until he regains his thief skills.\nDialogues.\n&lt;br&gt;\nTrivia.\n Interestingly, the game files include a line of dialogue for Yoshimo when the party enters the &lt;a href=\"Abyss\"&gt;Abyss&lt;/a&gt;, which\u00a0suggests that the developers of the original game initially had different plans for his role in the plot.\n&lt;br&gt;\nMod content.\nFurther interaction with Yoshimo is available through the &lt;a href=\"https%3A//github.com/SpellholdStudios/YoshimoFriendship\"&gt;Yoshimo Friendship&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"http%3A//downloads.weaselmods.net/download/yoshimo-romance/\"&gt;Yoshimo Romance&lt;/a&gt; mods.\nThe &lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.gibberlings3.net/mods/npcs/yoshi/\"&gt;Keeping Yoshimo&lt;/a&gt; mod allows players to retain Yoshimo past Spellhold."}
{"id": "9577", "revid": "46775035", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9577", "title": "Yoshimo's Heart", "text": "Yoshimo's Heart needs to be taken to any temple of &lt;a href=\"Ilmater\"&gt;Ilmater&lt;/a&gt;. There is a temple dedicated to this deity on top of the Copper Coronet in the &lt;a href=\"Athkatla%20Slums\"&gt;Athkatla Slums&lt;/a&gt;, and another one in &lt;a href=\"Waukeen%27s%20Promenade\"&gt;Waukeen's Promenade&lt;/a&gt;. For this simple deed, the party will receive 200,000 XP, and it will help &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo\"&gt;Yoshimo&lt;/a&gt; greatly."}
{"id": "4226", "revid": "47673695", "url": "https://baldursgate.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4226", "title": "Yoshimo's Katana", "text": "Yoshimo's Katana +1 is like an ordinary &lt;a href=\"katana%20%2B1\"&gt;katana +1&lt;/a&gt;, but this weapon is enchanted in such a way it can only be used by &lt;a href=\"Yoshimo\"&gt;Yoshimo&lt;/a&gt;. This weapon is in the possession of Yoshimo when he joins the party."}
